/4050-115640/" data-ref-id="4050-115640">Iron Man: I Am Iron Man</a> (#200)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-epic-collection-stark-wars/4050-79615/" data-ref-id="4050-79615">Iron Man Epic Collection: Stark Wars</a> (#215-232)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-armor-wars-prologue/4050-32283/" data-ref-id="4050-32283">Armor Wars Prologue</a> (#215-224)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-armor-wars/4050-27515/" data-ref-id="4050-27515">Armor Wars</a> (#225-232)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-epic-collection-the-captain/4050-138272/">Captain America Epic Collection: The Captain</a> (#228)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/iron-man-epic-collection-return-of-the-ghost/4050-117588/">Iron Man Epic Collection: Return of the Ghost</a> (#233-244)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-adventures-iron-man-and-spider-man/4050-32315/">Marvel Adventures: Iron Man and Spider-Man</a> (#234)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-iron-man/4050-122490/">Marvel-Verse: Iron Man</a> (#234)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-epic-collection-doom/4050-108102/" data-ref-id="4050-108102">Iron Man Epic Collection: Doom</a> (#245-257)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/acts-of-vengeance-avengers/4050-124684/">Acts of Vengeance: Avengers</a> (#251-252)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/taskmaster-anything-you-can-do/4050-125196/">Taskmaster: Anything You Can Do...</a> (#254)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-armor-wars-ii/4050-33386/" data-ref-id="4050-33386">Armor Wars II</a> (#258-266)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-epic-collection-war-games/4050-72418/" data-ref-id="4050-72418">Iron Man Epic Collection: War Games</a> (#258-277)</li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/iron-man-armored-vengeance/4050-68189/" data-ref-id="4050-68189">Armored Vengeance</a> (#258.1-258.4)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-dragon-seed-saga/4050-27133/" data-ref-id="4050-27133">Dragon Seed Saga</a> (#270-275)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-epic-collection-operation-galactic-storm/4050-103068/" data-ref-id="4050-103068">Avengers Epic Collection: Operation Galactic Storm</a> (#278-279)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/iron-man-epic-collection-war-machine/4050-126294/">Iron Man Epic Collection: War Machine</a> (#278-289)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-war-machine/4050-30279/" data-ref-id="4050-30279">War Machine</a> (#281-291)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-infinity-crusade-omnibus/4050-133099/">The Infinity Crusade Omnibus</a> (#294-295)</li><li><a href="/venomnibus-1-volume-1/4000-680257/" data-ref-id="4000-680257">Venomnibus Volume 1</a> (#302)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hulk-vs-the-avengers/4050-127273/">Hulk vs. The Avengers</a> (#305)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-epic-collection-man-without-a-coun/4050-89584/" data-ref-id="4050-89584">Captain America Epic Collection: Man Without A Country</a> (#326)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengersiron-man-first-sign/4050-67287/" data-ref-id="4050-67287">Avengers/Iron Man: First Sign</a> (#326-331)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-epic-collection-worldengine/4050-111591/">Thor Epic Collection: Worldengine</a> (#326)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-collection-iron-man/4050-119465/">Avengers Collection: Iron Man</a> (#127-128 &amp; #232) (German)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/maestros-marvel-john-romita-jr/4050-104383/" data-ref-id="4050-104383">Maestros Marvel. John Romita Jr.</a> (#128) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#197) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/best-of-marvel-essentials-iron-man-la-guerra-de-la/4050-41921/" data-ref-id="4050-41921">Best of Marvel Essentials: Iron Man - La Guerra de las Armaduras</a> (#225-232) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-5-iron-man-la-2a-guerr/4000-612210/" data-ref-id="4000-612210">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Iron Man - La 2ª Guerra de las Armaduras</a> (#258-266) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-35-iron-man-la-semilla/4000-612243/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Iron Man: La semilla del dragón</a> (#267-275) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issues <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-iron-man/4050-41951/" data-ref-id="4050-41951">#1-157</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1968', '336', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2466955-ironman001.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2410', 'Nick Fury, Agent of SHIELD', 'Who Is Scorpio?', '31', '<p>Nick Fury, the super-spy takes center stage in his own ongoing series with beautiful art-work by Jim Steranko. The series spun-off from <a href="../../strange-tales/49-18066/" rel="nofollow ">Strange Tales</a> #168. The series lasted for 15 issues. After that, the series was cancelled, with the story continuing into <em> <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-avengers-72-did-you-hear-the-one-about-scorpio/4000-10617/">The Avengers issue 72</a>. </em>One year later, the series returned as a reprint series for issue 16,17 and 18.</p><p>A year and a half later, the series was sort of revived for a few issues with a new number one in <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/nick-fury-and-his-agents-of-shield/4050-2642/">Nick Fury and His Agents of SHIELD</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/shield-the-complete-collection/4050-85133/" data-ref-id="4050-85133">S.H.I.E.L.D.: The Complete Collection</a> (#1-15)</li><li>Marvel Masterworks: Nick Fury, Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. Vol. 2 (#1-3)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/shield-by-steranko-the-complete-collection/4050-67342/" data-ref-id="4050-67342">Shield By Steranko: The Complete Collection</a> (#1-3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/steranko-is-revolutionary/4050-129904/">Steranko Is… Revolutionary!</a> (#1-3 &amp; 5)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-10-nick-furia-agente-d/4000-612215/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes: Nick Furia: Agente de SHIELD</a> (#1-3) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1968', '18', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117930/2694258-nick_fury_aos__1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2411', 'The Silver Surfer', 'The Origin of the Silver Surfer', '31', '<p><a href="/stan-lee/4040-40467/" data-ref-id="4040-40467">Stan Lee</a> launched the solo title The Silver Surfer. <a href="/john-buscema/4040-3800/" data-ref-id="4040-3800">John Buscema</a> was penciller for the first 17 issues of the series, with <a href="/jack-kirby/4040-5614/" data-ref-id="4040-5614">Jack Kirby</a> returning for the 18th and final issue. The first seven issues, which included anthological "Tales of the Watcher" backup stories, were 72-page (with advertising), 25-cent "giants", as opposed to the typical 36-page, 12-cent comics of the time. Thematically, the stories dealt with The Silver Surfer''s exile on <a href="/earth/4020-57183/" data-ref-id="4020-57183">Earth</a> and the inhumanity of man as observed by this noble yet fallen hero. Though short-lived, the series became known as one of Lee''s most thoughtful and introspective works.</p><p>Following this series'' cancellation, <a href="/silver-surfer/4005-2502/" data-ref-id="4005-2502">Silver Surfer</a> made sporadic appearances as a guest star or antagonist in such comic books as <a href="/thor/4050-2294/" data-ref-id="4050-2294">Thor</a>, <a href="/the-defenders/4050-2569/" data-ref-id="4050-2569">The Defenders</a>, and <a href="/fantastic-four/4050-2045/" data-ref-id="4050-2045">Fantastic Four</a>. Lee remained partial to the Surfer, and with Kirby collaborated on a seminal 1978 <a href="/the-silver-surfer-the-ultimate-cosmic-experience/4050-20444/" data-ref-id="4050-20444">graphic novel</a> starring the character.</p><h3>Collections</h3><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-15-volume-15-the-silver-surfer/4000-32227/" data-ref-id="4000-32227">Marvel Masterworks Vol. 15</a> (#1-5)</li><li><a href="/fantasy-masterpieces/4050-3003/" data-ref-id="4050-3003">Fantasy Masterpieces Vol. 2</a> (#1-14, individual issues)</li><li><a href="/essential-silver-surfer-1-volume-1/4000-157715/" data-ref-id="4000-157715">Essential Silver Surfer Vol. 1</a> (#1-18)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-19-volume-19-the-silver-surfer-/4000-33695/" data-ref-id="4000-33695">Marvel Masterworks Vol. 19</a> (#6-18)</li><li><a href="/spiderman-silver-surfer/4050-87462/" data-ref-id="4050-87462">Spider-Man: Silver Surfer</a> (#14)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-silver-surfer-1-volume-one/4000-228379/" data-ref-id="4000-228379">Marvel Masterworks: Silver Surfer Vol. 1</a> (#1-6)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-silver-surfer-2-volume-two/4000-228380/" data-ref-id="4000-228380">Marvel Masterworks: Silver Surfer Vol. 2</a> (#7-18)</li></ul>', '1968', '18', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2403460-ss1.png', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2413', 'Sub-Mariner', 'Years Of Glory, Day Of Doom', '31', '<p>The series was launched following the Sub-Mariner stories from <a href="/tales-to-astonish/4050-2008/" data-ref-id="4050-2008">Tales To Astonish</a>. The series is a continuation from the one-shot <a href="/iron-man-and-sub-mariner/4050-18547/" data-ref-id="4050-18547">Iron Man and Sub-Mariner</a> comic which picks up the story arc from <a href="/tales-to-astonish-where-walk-the-immortalsand-evil-shall-beckon/4000-108670/" data-ref-id="4000-108670">Tales To Astonish #101</a>. The series started in 1968 and lasted until 1974 for a total of 72 issues. The series also had a <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/sub-mariner-annual/4050-2521/">Sub-Mariner Annual </a>companion series.</p><p>This is the first solo <a href="/namor/4005-1476/" data-ref-id="4005-1476">Sub-Mariner</a> series published by <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel Comics</a>, the previous “<a href="/sub-mariner/4050-1642/" data-ref-id="4050-1642">Sub-Mariner</a>" and “<a href="/sub-mariner-comics/4050-18548/" data-ref-id="4050-18548">Sub-Mariner Comics</a>” having been published by Marvel’s predecessors <a href="/atlas/4010-75/" data-ref-id="4010-75">Atlas</a> and <a href="/timely/4010-21/" data-ref-id="4010-21">Timely</a> respectively.</p><h3>Writers</h3><ul><li><a href="/roy-thomas/4040-42067/" data-ref-id="4040-42067">Roy Thomas</a> #1-40</li><li><a href="/gerry-conway/4040-40871/" data-ref-id="4040-40871">Gerry Conway</a> #41-49</li><li><a href="/bill-everett/4040-6103/" data-ref-id="4040-6103">Bill Everett</a> #45(reprint) 50, 52-55, 57-61, 63</li><li><a href="/mike-friedrich/4040-51799/" data-ref-id="4040-51799">Mike Friedrich</a> #51-52, 54, 56</li><li><a href="/dan-adkins/4040-11274/" data-ref-id="4040-11274">Dan Adkins</a> #56</li><li><a href="/steve-gerber/4040-41456/" data-ref-id="4040-41456">Steve Gerber</a> #58-69</li><li><a href="/howard-chaykin/4040-2424/" data-ref-id="4040-2424">Howard Chaykin</a> #62, 63-64</li><li><a href="/marv-wolfman/4040-41478/" data-ref-id="4040-41478">Marv Wolfman</a> #70-71</li><li><a href="/steve-skeates/4040-44731/" data-ref-id="4040-44731">Steve Skeates</a> #72</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-2-volume-two/4000-232081/" data-ref-id="4000-232081">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 2</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-3-volume-three/4000-232082/" data-ref-id="4000-232082">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 3</a> (#2-13)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-4-volume-four/4000-265711/" data-ref-id="4000-265711">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 4</a> (#14-25)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-epic-collection-a-separate-reality/4050-95006/" data-ref-id="4050-95006">Doctor Strange Epic Collection: A Separate Reality</a> (#22)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-5-volume-5/4000-442428/" data-ref-id="4000-442428">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 5</a> (#26-38)</li><li><a href="/the-defenders-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-842243/" data-ref-id="4000-842243">The Defenders Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#34-35)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-vs-hulk/4050-104825/" data-ref-id="4050-104825">Thor vs. Hulk</a> (#35)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-6-volume-6/4000-479396/" data-ref-id="4000-479396">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 6</a> (#39-49)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-7-volume-7/4000-510946/" data-ref-id="4000-510946">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 7</a> (#50-60)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner/4050-35188/" data-ref-id="4050-35188">Marvel Masterworks: Sub-Mariner, Vol. 8</a> (#61-72)</li></ul><p>Issues <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-namor-1/4000-285570/" data-ref-id="4000-285570">#62-66</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1968', '72', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2803744-submariner01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2466', 'Super DC Giant', 'Binky', '10', '<p>Notes: This series starts at issue 13..</p>', '1970', '15', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/47418-2466-56802-1-super-dc-giant.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2469', 'Amazing Adventures', 'Beware the Inhumans!; Then Came the Black Widdow', '31', '<p>Amazing Adventures began life as another of Marvel''s tried and tested "double feature" comics - in the mould of <a href="/tales-of-suspense/4050-2007/" data-ref-id="4050-2007">Tales of Suspense</a> / <a href="/tales-to-astonish/4050-2008/" data-ref-id="4050-2008">Tales to Astonish</a>. Its original features were the <a href="/inhumans/4060-11427/" data-ref-id="4060-11427">Inhumans</a> and <a href="/black-widow/4005-3200/" data-ref-id="4005-3200">Black Widow</a>. However, this dual feature lasted only 8 issues, before the headline feature became "<a href="/black-bolt/4005-4329/" data-ref-id="4005-4329">Black Bolt</a> and the Inhumans" for a further 2 issues. Then, from the pages of the <a href="/x-men/4060-3173/" data-ref-id="4060-3173">X-Men</a> (who at this time did not have their own book) came "<a href="/beast/4005-1462/" data-ref-id="4005-1462">The Beast</a>", who took centre stage for the next 7 issues before super heroes gave way to space fantasy with "War of the Worlds", where the hero <a href="/killraven/4005-7233/" data-ref-id="4005-7233">Killraven</a>, Warrior of the Worlds, made his debut. His series filled in the remaining 22 issues of the title.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/kingsize-kirby/4050-83141/" data-ref-id="4050-83141">King-Size Kirby</a> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/civil-war-ii-xmen/4050-95724/" data-ref-id="4050-95724">Civil War II: X-Men</a> (#9)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-epic-collection-its-always-darkest-before-th/4050-120262/">X-Men Epic Collection: It''s Always Darkest Before the Dawn</a> (#11-17)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/killraven-epic-collection-warrior-of-the-worlds/4050-139434/">Killraven Epic Collection: Warrior of the Worlds</a> (#18-39) (Killraven Stories)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-killraven-1-volume-1/4000-685850/" data-ref-id="4000-685850">Marvel Masterworks: Killraven Volume 1</a> (#18-39) (Killraven Stories)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kingsize-kirby/4050-104017/" data-ref-id="4050-104017">King-Size Kirby</a> (#1-2) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-22-viuda-negra-red-de-/4000-612227/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes: Viuda Negra: Red de intrigas</a> (#1-8) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1970', '39', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/9942-2469-10946-1-amazing-adventures.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2470', 'Astonishing Tales', 'Unto you is Born the Doomsman; The Power of Ka-zar', '31', '<p>The line up of features in Astonishing Tales changed several times. It first featured Ka-Zar and Doctor Doom. The double feature lasted only 8 issues, before Ka-Zar took over the book completely upto issue 20, when his adventures continued in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ka-zar/4050-2692/">Ka-Zar Volume 2</a>. Following 4 issues of IT - the Living Collosus, the remaining issues featured the debut and continuing adventures of Deathlok the Demolisher (apart from #29, which was a reprint comic starring the Guardians of the Galaxy).</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ka-zar-1-volume-1/4000-380710/" data-ref-id="4000-380710">Marvel Masterworks: Ka-Zar Volume 1</a> (#1-16)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mockingbird-bobbi-morse-agent-of-shield/4050-92762/" data-ref-id="4050-92762">Mockingbird: Bobbi Morse, Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.</a> (#10, 13-13 &amp; 15-20)</li><li><a href="/man-thing-by-steve-gerber-the-complete-collection-/4000-502866/" data-ref-id="4000-502866">Man-Thing by Steve Gerber: The Complete Collection Vol. 1</a> (#12-13)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ka-zar-2-volume-2/4000-663576/" data-ref-id="4000-663576">Marvel Masterworks: Ka-Zar Volume 2</a> (#17-20)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-omnibus/4050-121088/">Marvel Horror Omnibus</a> (#21-24)</li><li><a href="/deathlok-the-demolisher-the-complete-collection/4050-77316/" data-ref-id="4050-77316">Deathlok The Demolisher: The Complete Collection</a> (#25-28 &amp; 30-36)</li></ul>', '1970', '36', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/9944-2470-10948-1-astonishing-tales.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2471', 'Conan the Barbarian', 'The Coming of Conan!', '31', '<p>The series lasted for 275 issues, after that Marvel revamped the series into <a href="../../conan-the-adventurer/49-5288/" rel="nofollow ">Conan the Adventurer</a> with a new number 1. This second series was however short lived and after that Marvel published many mini-series up until 1998, when they lost the rights to publish Conan.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/chronicles-of-conan-tower-of-the-elephant-other-stories/4000-150363/" data-ref-id="4000-150363">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 1</a> (#1-8)</li><li><a href="/conan-the-barbarian-the-original-marvel-years-omni/4000-714448/" data-ref-id="4000-714448">Conan the Barbarian: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#1-26)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/conan-the-barbarian-epic-collection-the-original-m/4050-129254/">Conan the Barbarian Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years: The Coming of Conan</a> (#1-13)</li><li><a href="/chronicles-of-conan-rogues-in-the-house-other-stories/4000-150370/" data-ref-id="4000-150370">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 2</a> (#9-13 &amp; 16)</li><li><a href="/chronicles-of-conan-the-monster-of-the-monoliths-and-other-stories/4000-150371/" data-ref-id="4000-150371">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 3</a> (#14, 15, 17-22)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/conan-the-barbarian-epic-collection-the-original-m/4050-134428/">Conan the Barbarian Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years: Hawks From the Sea</a> (#14-26)</li><li><a href="/chronicles-of-conan-the-song-of-red-sonja-and-other-stories/4000-150372/" data-ref-id="4000-150372">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 4</a> (#23-26)</li><li><a href="/chronicles-of-conan-the-shadow-in-the-tomb-and-other-stories/4000-150373/" data-ref-id="4000-150373">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 5</a> (#27-34)</li><li><a href="/conan-the-barbari