e-crom/4000-558374/" data-ref-id="4000-558374">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 33</a> (#259-267)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-chronicles-of-conan-34-betrayal-in-zamora-and-/4000-587371/" data-ref-id="4000-587371">The Chronicles of Conan vol. 34</a> (#268-275)</li></ul>', '1970', '275', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10040-2471-11052-1-conan-the-barbarian.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2475', 'Ka-Zar', 'In His Footsteps, the Huntsman of Zeus!; The Mystery of the Midnight Stalker; The Coming of... Ka-Zar!', '31', '<p>Ka-Zar''s first (mini) series. It was three issues long and had adventures of Ka-Zar with the X-men, Daredevil and the Amazing Spider-man. It where new stories along with a back-up reprint.</p>', '1970', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/9953-2475-10957-1-ka-zar.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2500', 'DC 100-Page Super Spectacular', 'Weird Mystery Tales', '10', NULL, '1971', '19', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10159-2500-11183-1-dc-100-page-super-sp.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2504', 'Mister Miracle', 'The Murder Missile Trap!', '10', '<p><span>Collected Editions</span></p><ul><li><a href="/jack-kirbys-mister-miracle/4050-43657/" data-ref-id="4050-43657">Jack Kirby''s Mister Miracle</a> (#1-10)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/jack-kirbys-fourth-world-omnibus-1-vol-1/4000-287539/">Jack Kirby''s Fourth World Omnibus Vol. 1</a> (#1-3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mister-miracle-by-jack-kirby/4050-104491/" data-ref-id="4050-104491">Mister Miracle by Jack Kirby</a> (#1-18)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/jack-kirby-the-fourth-world-omnibus/4050-106680/" data-ref-id="4050-106680">Jack Kirby: The Fourth World Omnibus</a> (#1-18)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/jack-kirbys-fourth-world-omnibus-2-jack-kirbys-fou/4000-287874/">Jack Kirby''s Fourth World Omnibus Vol. 2</a> (#4-6)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/jack-kirbys-fourth-world-omnibus-3-vol-3/4000-287876/">Jack Kirby''s Fourth World Omnibus Vol. 3</a> (#7-9)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/female-furies/4050-123657/">Female Furies</a> (#9)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/jack-kirbys-fourth-world-omnibus-4-vol-4/4000-287878/">Jack Kirby''s Fourth World Omnibus Vol. 4</a> (#10-18)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mister-miracle-by-steve-englehart-and-steve-gerber/4050-125642/">Mister Miracle by Steve Englehart and Steve Gerber</a> (#19-25)</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: This series was canceled as a result of the so-called DC Implosion of 1978.</p>', '1971', '25', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4017660-mm1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2510', 'Captain America Annual', 'The Origin of Captain America', '31', '<p>Annuals to the Captain America series. It ran from 1971 until 1994. There were no annuals published from 1995-1997. Starring In 1998 four more annuals and a team-up with <a href="/iron-man/4005-1455/" data-ref-id="4005-1455">Iron Man</a> were released, with unique titles;</p><ul><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/captain-america-annual-98/4050-60452/" data-ref-id="4050-60452">Captain America / Citizen V ''98</a></li><li><a href="/iron-man-captain-america-annual-98/4050-30391/" data-ref-id="4050-30391">Iron Man / Captain America ''98</a> (<a href="//www.comicvine.com/iron-man-annual/4050-2905/" data-ref-id="4050-2905">Iron Man Annual</a>)</li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/captain-america-annual-99/4050-60453/" data-ref-id="4050-60453">Captain America 1999</a></li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/captain-america-annual-2000/4050-60454/" data-ref-id="4050-60454">Captain America 2000</a></li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/captain-america-annual-2001/4050-60455/" data-ref-id="4050-60455">Captain America 2001</a></li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-captain-america-10-volume-10/4000-676702/" data-ref-id="4000-676702">Marvel Masterworks: Captain America Volume 10</a> (#3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-and-the-falcon-the-swine/4050-27520/">Captain America and the Falcon: The Swine</a> (#3-4)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-captain-america-11-volume-11/4000-713508/" data-ref-id="4000-713508">Marvel Masterworks: Captain America Volume 11</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="/captain-america-epic-collection-dawns-early-light/4050-71799/" data-ref-id="4050-71799">Captain America Epic Collection: Dawn''s Early Light</a> (#5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-epic-collection-monsters-and-men/4050-131207/">Captain America Epic Collection: Monsters and Men</a> (#6)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/wolverine-vs-the-marvel-universe/4050-99881/" data-ref-id="4050-99881">Wolverine vs. The Marvel Universe</a> (#8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-epic-collection-justice-is-served/4050-100563/" data-ref-id="4050-100563">Captain America Epic Collection: Justice Is Served</a> (#8)</li><li><a href="/captain-america-epic-collection-streets-of-poison/4050-82670/" data-ref-id="4050-82670">Captain America Epic Collection: Streets of Poison</a> (#9-10)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-gold-capitan-america-6-la-era-de-la-bomba-l/4000-631321/">Marvel Gold. Capitán América - La era de la "Bomba Loca"</a> (#3-4) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1971', '13', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10189-2510-11218-1-captain-america-annu.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2512', 'Creatures on the Loose', 'The Skull of Silence; Trull the Unhuman!', '31', '<p>Continued from <a href="/tower-of-shadows/4050-2448/" data-ref-id="4050-2448"> Tower of Shadows</a> issue 9. The series started out as a comic with reprint stories of horror and monster comics, but from issue 16 and on became the home for Marvel stars such as Gullivar Jones, Thongor and John Jameson, aka the Man-Wolf!. It lasted until issue 37.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kull-the-destroyer-the-original-marvel-years-omnib/4050-139959/">Kull the Destroyer: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus</a> (#10)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/man-wolf-the-complete-collection/4050-121739/">Man-Wolf: The Complete Collection</a> (#30-37)</li></ul>', '1971', '28', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/8117036-9077662688-96029.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2515', 'Marvel Feature', 'The Day of the Defenders!; The Sub-Mariner and the Icebergs; The Return', '31', '<p>A small series with a large legacy; It features the formation and first appearance of the Defenders. This series is somewhat continued in <a href="../../marvel-two-in-one/49-2696/" rel="nofollow ">Marvel Two-In-One</a>. That series started two months after this series was cancelled and continues the Thing''s story that started here in the last two issues of Marvel Feature.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-epic-collection-a-separate-reality/4050-95006/" data-ref-id="4050-95006">Doctor Strange Epic Collection: A Separate Reality</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-1-volume-1/4000-231493/" data-ref-id="4000-231493">Marvel Masterworks: The Defenders Volume 1</a> (#1-3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-defenders-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-842243/" data-ref-id="4000-842243">The Defenders Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#1-3)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ant-mangiant-man-3-volume-3/4000-673021/" data-ref-id="4000-673021">Marvel Masterworks: Ant-Man/Giant-Man Volume 3</a> (#4-10)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-marvel-two-in-one-1-volume-1/4000-433434/" data-ref-id="4000-433434">Marvel Masterworks: Marvel Two-In-One vol. 1</a> (#11-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-two-in-one-epic-collection-cry-monster/4050-112694/">Marvel Two-In-One Epic Collection: Cry Monster</a> (#11-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-by-jim-starlin-the-complete-collect/4050-95814/" data-ref-id="4050-95814">Captain Marvel By Jim Starlin: The Complete Collection</a> (#12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-thanos-wars-infinity-origin/4050-118000/">The Thanos Wars: Infinity Origin</a> (#12)</li></ul>', '1971', '12', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2845968-marvelfeature01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2516', 'Marvel Spotlight', 'Red Wolf', '31', '<p>The first volume of Marvel Spotlight from the 1970''s. This series introduced some mayor Marvel Characters, such as Ghost Rider, Werewolf by Night, the Spider-woman and Devil Slayer. It also gave some heroes such as Son of Satan and Moon Knight their first solo adventures.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/werewold-by-night-omnibus/4050-85148/" data-ref-id="4050-85148">Werewolf By Night Omnibus</a> (#2-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/werewolf-by-night-the-complete-collection-1-volume/4000-626305/" data-ref-id="4000-626305">Werewolf By Night: The Complete Collection Volume 1</a> (#2-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengersdoctor-strange-rise-of-the-darkhold/4050-114044/">Avengers/Doctor Strange: Rise of the Darkhold</a> (#3-4)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ghost-rider-1-volume-1/4000-721798/" data-ref-id="4000-721798">Marvel Masterworks: Ghost Rider Volume 1</a> (#5-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-universe-by-frank-miller-omnibus/4050-116073/">Marvel Universe by Frank Miller Omnibus</a> (#8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-son-of-satan-classic/4050-95033/" data-ref-id="4050-95033">The Son of Satan Classic</a> (#12-24)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hellstrom-evil-origins/4050-129473/">Hellstrom: Evil Origins</a> (#12-13 &amp; 24)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-lives-again-omnibus/4050-131205/">Marvel Horror Lives Again! Omnibus</a> (#24)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-lords-of-fear/4050-107359/" data-ref-id="4050-107359">Doctor Strange: Lords of Fear</a> (#26)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-omnibus/4050-121088/">Marvel Horror Omnibus</a> (#26)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-sub-mariner-8-volume-8/4000-654055/" data-ref-id="4000-654055">Marvel Masterworks: The Sub-Mariner Volume 8</a> (#27)</li><li><a href="/moon-knight-epic-collection-bad-moon-rising/4050-77333/" data-ref-id="4050-77333">Moon Knight Epic Collection: Bad Moon Rising</a> (#28-29)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/moon-knight-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-824088/" data-ref-id="4000-824088">Moon Knight Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#28-29)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-mighty-thor-15-volume-15/4000-520206/" data-ref-id="4000-520206">Marvel Masterworks: The Mighty Thor Volume 15</a> (#30)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-the-warriors-three/4050-43096/">Thor: The Warriors Three</a> (#30)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/siege-prelude/4050-30960/">Siege Prelude</a> (#30)</li><li><a href="/shield-the-complete-collection/4050-85133/" data-ref-id="4050-85133">S.H.I.E.L.D.: The Complete Collection</a> (#31)</li><li><a href="/spiderwoman-spiderverse/4050-82710/" data-ref-id="4050-82710">Spider-Woman: Spider-Verse</a> (#32)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-spider-woman-1-volume-1/4000-505913/" data-ref-id="4000-505913">Marvel Masterworks: Spider-Woman Volume 1</a> (#32)</li><li><a href="/deathlok-the-demolisher-the-complete-collection/4050-77316/" data-ref-id="4050-77316">Deathlok The Demolisher: The Complete Collection</a> (#33)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-el-universo-marvel-segun-fr/4050-105405/">Colección Frank Miller. El Universo Marvel según Frank Miller</a> (#18) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-65-caballero-luna-1-cu/4000-612301/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Caballero Luna 1: Cuenta atrás hacia la oscuridad</a> (#28-29) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1971', '33', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10704-2516-11788-1-marvel-spotlight.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2520', 'Special Marvel Edition', 'Into the Blaze of Battle!; To Kill a Thunder God!; Tales of Asgard - The Golden Apples; The Day of the Destroyer!', '31', '<p>The series started out as a reprint series up until issue #15 where in Marvel''s Master of Kung Fu <a href="/shang-chi/4005-12716/" data-ref-id="4005-12716">Shang-Chi</a> made his first appearance. After just two issues with Shang-Chi in Special Marvel Edition, the series was renamed and continued as <a href="/master-of-kung-fu/4050-2697/" data-ref-id="4050-2697"> Master of Kung Fu</a> with issue #17.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/shang-chi-master-of-kung-fu-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-533502/" data-ref-id="4000-533502">Shang-Chi Master of Kung-Fu Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#15-16)</li><li><a href="/master-of-kung-fu-epic-collection-weapon-of-the-so/4050-109201/" data-ref-id="4050-109201">Master of Kung Fu Epic Collection: Weapon of the Soul</a> (#15-16)</li></ul>', '1971', '16', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10201-2520-11230-1-special-marvel-editi.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2521', 'Sub-Mariner Annual', 'The Start of the Quest!', '31', '<p>Annuals to the <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/sub-mariner/4050-2413/">Sub-Mariner</a> series. The annual series where actually named "Specials".</p>', '1971', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4106193-sman1nm92m085.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2527', 'I Fantastici Quattro', NULL, '184', '<br/>', '1971', '259', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/4/48397/1332683-fpb7r9.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2528', 'Il Mitico Thor', NULL, '184', '<p>Numbering continues into <a href="/thor-e-i-vendicatori/4050-131531/" data-ref-id="4050-131531">Thor e i Vendicatori</a> #103.</p>', '1971', '102', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10330-2528-11370-1-mitico-thor-il.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2569', 'The Defenders', 'I Slay by the Stars!', '31', '<p>The first ongoing Defenders series. It starred a variety of superheroes such as Doctor Strange, Namor, Hulk, Nighthawk, Hellcat, Valkyrie, Silver Surfer and many others. With issue 125, the series was duped "the New Defenders" and starred an almost entirely different cast. It ended with issue 152 after half the team seemingly died, and the rest of the team (Beast, Angel and Iceman) joined <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-factor/4050-3657/">X-Factor</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-1-volume-1/4000-231493/" data-ref-id="4000-231493">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 1</a> (#1-6)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-defenders-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-842243/" data-ref-id="4000-842243">The Defenders Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#1-19)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-2-volume-2/4000-307503/" data-ref-id="4000-307503">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 2</a> (#7-16)</li><li><a href="/avengersdefenders-war/4050-30226/" data-ref-id="4050-30226">Avengers/Defenders War</a> (#8-11)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-epic-collection-the-avengersdefenders-war/4050-109747/">Avengers Epic Collection: The Avengers/Defenders War</a> (#8-11)</li><li><a href="/avengers-omnibus-4-volume-four/4000-703935/" data-ref-id="4000-703935">Avengers Omnibus Volume 4</a> (#8-11)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-vs-hulk/4050-104825/" data-ref-id="4050-104825">Thor vs. Hulk</a> (#10)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-epic-collection-its-always-darkest-before-th/4050-120262/">X-Men Epic Collection: It''s Always Darkest Before the Dawn</a> (#15-16)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-3-volume-3/4000-445309/" data-ref-id="4000-445309">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 3</a> (#17-21)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-4-volume-4/4000-445310/" data-ref-id="4000-445310">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 4</a> (#22-30)</li><li><a href="/guardians-of-the-galaxy-earth-shall-overcome/4050-30359/" data-ref-id="4050-30359">Guardians of the Galaxy: Earth Shall Overcome</a> (#26-29)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/guardians-of-the-galaxy-tomorrows-heroes-omnibus/4050-116248/">Guardians of the Galaxy: Tomorrow''s Heroes Omnibus</a> (#26-29)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-5-volume-5/4000-502867/" data-ref-id="4000-502867">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 5</a> (#31-41)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-6-volume-6/4000-670117/" data-ref-id="4000-670117">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 6</a> (#42-57)</li><li><a href="/moon-knight-epic-collection-bad-moon-rising/4050-77333/" data-ref-id="4050-77333">Moon Knight Epic Collection: Bad Moon Rising</a> (#47-50)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/moon-knight-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-824088/" data-ref-id="4000-824088">Moon Knight Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#47-50)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ms-marvel-epic-collection-this-woman-this-warrior/4050-116378/">Ms. Marvel Epic Collection: This Woman, This Warrior</a> (#57)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-ms-marvel-a-hero-is-born/4050-117049/">Captain Marvel: Ms. Marvel: A Hero Is Born</a> (#57)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-defenders-7-volume-7/4000-814972/" data-ref-id="4000-814972">Marvel Masterworks: Defenders Volume 7</a> (#58-75)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/defenders-epic-collection-the-sixfingered-hand-sag/4050-93423/" data-ref-id="4050-93423">Defenders Epic Collection: The Six-Fingered Hand Saga</a> (#92-109)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hellstrom-evil-origins/4050-129473/">Hellstrom: Evil Origins</a> (#92 &amp; 120-121)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-epic-collection-monsters-and-men/4050-131207/">Captain America Epic Collection: Monsters and Men</a> (#106)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/defenders-epic-collection-ashes-ashes/4050-103812/" data-ref-id="4050-103812">Defenders Epic Collection: Ashes, Ashes...</a> (#110-125)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/squadron-supreme-classic-omnibus/4050-90892/" data-ref-id="4050-90892">Squadron Supreme Classic Omnibus</a> (#112-114)</li><li><a href="/the-new-defenders-1-volume-one/4000-312125/" data-ref-id="4000-312125">The New Defenders Volume One</a> (#122-131)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/defenders-epic-collection-the-new-defenders/4050-112801/">Defenders Epic Collection: The New Defenders</a> (#126-137)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/defenders-epic-collection-the-end-of-all-songs/4050-123717/">Defenders Epic Collection: The End of All Songs</a> (#138-152)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#152) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issue <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-la-cosa-1/4000-285468/" data-ref-id="4000-285468">#20</a> has been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1972', '152', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2618111-defenders001.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2572', 'Hero for Hire', 'Out of Hell - A Hero!', '31', '<p>Introducing Luke Cage, Hero for Hire! This volume follows the first adventures of Luke Cage, whom was wrongly convicted of a crime and, under the alias of Luke Cage, fights for the little people as a Hero for Hire! The series was continued as <a href="/power-man/4050-2700/" data-ref-id="4050-2700"> Power Man</a> with issue #17.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/luke-cage-epic-collection-retribution/4050-133628/">Luke Cage Epic Collection: Retribution</a></li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-luke-cage-hero-for-hire/4050-83964/" data-ref-id="4050-83964">Marvel Masterworks: Luke Cage, Hero For Hire</a></li><li><a href="/luke-cage-omnibus/4050-148451/" data-ref-id="4050-148451">Luke Cage Omnibus</a></li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/los-nuevos-vengadores-luke-cage/4050-103867/">Los Nuevos Vengadores: Luke Cage</a> (#1) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1972', '16', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6606937-4179961455-STL093571', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2574', 'Jungle Action', 'The Trail of Sudden Death', '31', '<p>It started as a series for the "Tarzan-like" hero known as <a href="/tharn/4005-37003/" data-ref-id="4005-37003"> Tharn</a>, whom was the star of the <a href="/jungle-action/4050-20835/" data-ref-id="4050-20835"> first Jungle Action</a> series, but became a series starring the Black Panther with issue 5. The series lasted until issue 24 and was continued one month later in Black Panther''s very own <a href="/black-panther/4050-2896/" data-ref-id="4050-2896"> ongoing series</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-panther-epic-collection-panthers-rage/4050-94409/" data-ref-id="4050-94409">Black Panther Epic Collection: Panther''s Rage</a> (#6-24)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvels-black-panther-prelude/4050-107660/" data-ref-id="4050-107660">Marvel''s Black Panther Prelude</a> (#6-7)</li></ul>', '1972', '24', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/3668184-%24%28kgrhqf%2C%21pce9enm3fpbbpz7szmpmq~~60_3.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2575', 'Marvel Premiere', 'And Men Shall Call Him... Warlock', '31', '<p>Marvel Premiere is a series that introduced some major Marvel Characters, it starred the first appearances of <a href="../../iron-fist/29-1492/" rel="nofollow ">Iron Fist</a>, <a href="../../colleen-wing/29-1494/" rel="nofollow ">Colleen Wing</a>, <a href="../../3-d-man/29-43653/" rel="nofollow ">3-D Man</a>, <a href="../../legion-of-monsters/65-46227/" rel="nofollow ">the Legion of Monsters</a> and <a href="../../stature/29-40516/" rel="nofollow ">Stature</a> to name a few.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/annihilation-classic/4050-30933/" data-ref-id="4050-30933">Annihilation Classic</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-epic-collection-a-separate-reality/4050-95006/" data-ref-id="4050-95006">Doctor Strange Epic Collection: A Separate Reality</a> (#3-14)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-what-is-it-that-disturbs-you-stephe/4050-95213/" data-ref-id="4050-95213">Doctor Strange: What Is It That Disturbs You, Stephen?</a> (#7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvels-doctor-strange-prelude/4050-94646/" data-ref-id="4050-94646">Marvel''s Doctor Strange Prelude</a> (#14)</li><li><a href="/iron-fist-epic-collection-the-fury-of-iron-fist/4050-83138/" data-ref-id="4050-83138">Iron Fist Epic Collection: The Fury of Iron Fist</a> (#15-25)</li><li><a href="/marvel-universe-by-john-byrne-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-694138/" data-ref-id="4000-694138">Marvel Universe by John Byrne Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#25)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-lives-again-omnibus/4050-131205/">Marvel Horror Lives Again! Omnibus</a> (#27)</li><li><a href="/werewold-by-night-omnibus/4050-85148/" data-ref-id="4050-85148">Werewolf By Night Omnibus</a> (#28)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/decades-marvel-in-the-70s-legion-of-monsters/4050-118241/">Decades: Marvel In The ''70s - Legion of Monsters</a> (#28)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ghost-rider-3-volume-3/4000-891875/" data-ref-id="4000-891875">Marvel Masterworks: Ghost Rider Volume 3</a> (#28)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-the-living-vampire-omnibus/4050-128226/">Morbius the Living Vampire Omnibus</a> (#28)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-epic-collection-the-end-of-a-living-vampir/4050-136029/">Morbius Epic Collection: The End Of A Living Vampire</a> (#28)</li><li><a href="/the-invaders-classic-the-complete-collection/4050-74817/" data-ref-id="4050-74817">The Invaders Classic: The Complete Collection</a> (#29-30)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/solomon-kane-the-original-marvel-years-omnibus/4050-129249/">Solomon Kane: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus</a> (#33-34)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-mighty-thor-14-volume-14/4000-495526/" data-ref-id="4000-495526">Marvel Masterworks: The Mighty Thor Vol. 14</a> (#36)</li><li><a href="/weirdworld/4050-81184/" data-ref-id="4050-81184">Weirdworld</a> (#38)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tigra-the-complete-collection/4050-123417/">Tigra: The Complete Collection</a> (#42)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-daredevil-14-volume-14/4000-733878/" data-ref-id="4000-733878">Marvel Masterworks: Daredevil Volume 14</a> (#43)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-invincible-iron-man-13-volu/4000-839822/" data-ref-id="4000-839822">Marvel Masterworks: The Invincible Iron Man Vol. 13</a> (#44)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/man-wolf-the-complete-collection/4050-121739/">Man-Wolf: The Complete Collection</a> (#45-46)</li><li><a href="/antman-scott-lang/4050-82479/" data-ref-id="4050-82479">Ant-Man: Scott Lang</a> (#47-48)</li><li><a href="/marvel-universe-by-john-byrne-omnibus-1-hc/4000-523259/" data-ref-id="4000-523259">Marvel Universe by John Byrne Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#47-48)</li><li><a href="/marvels-antman-prelude/4050-82504/" data-ref-id="4050-82504">Marvel''s Ant-Man Prelude</a> (#47-48)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ant-mangiant-man-3-volume-3/4000-673021/" data-ref-id="4000-673021">Marvel Masterworks: Ant-Man/Giant-Man Volume 3</a> (#47-48)</li><li><a href="/avengers-falcon/4050-72196/" data-ref-id="4050-72196">Avengers: Falcon</a> (#49)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-avengers-18-volume-18/4000-665917/" data-ref-id="4000-665917">Marvel Masterworks: Avengers Volume 18</a> (#49)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-captain-america-13-volume-13/4000-873645/" data-ref-id="4000-873645">Marvel Masterworks: Captain America Vol. 13</a> (#49)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-black-panther-2-volume-2/4000-556473/" data-ref-id="4000-556473">Marvel Masterworks: Black Panther Volume 2</a> (#51-53)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-panther-epic-collection-revenge-of-the-black/4050-117199/">Black Panther Epic Collection: Revenge of the Black Panther</a> (#51-53)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dominic-fortune-it-can-happen-here-and-now/4050-31437/">Dominic Fortune It Can Happen Here And Now</a> (#56)</li><li><a href="/starlord-tears-for-heaven/4050-72794/" data-ref-id="4050-72794">Star-Lord: Tears For Heaven</a> (#61)</li><li><a href="/guardians-of-the-galaxy-solo-classic-omnibus/4050-85759/" data-ref-id="4050-85759">Guardians of the Galaxy Solo Classic Omnibus</a> (#61)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ant-man-1-band-1/4000-510273/">Ant-Man - Band 1</a> (#47-48) (German)</li></ul><p>Issue <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/visionarios-marvel-stan-lee/4050-95780/" data-ref-id="4050-95780">#3</a> has been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1972', '61', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2618086-marvelpremiere01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2576', 'Marvel Team-Up', 'Have Yourself a Sandman Little Christmas!', '31', '<p>A series that connected the Marvel Universe for years to come. It features mainly Spider-Man teaming up with other heroes. This series had a <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-team-up-annual/4050-2863/">Marvel Team-Up Annual</a> series as well.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/spider-man-saga-of-the-sandman/4050-27204/" data-ref-id="4050-27204">Spider-Man: Saga of the Sandman</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-the-living-vampire-omnibus/4050-128226/">Morbius the Living Vampire Omnibus</a> (#3-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-preludes-and-nightmares/4050-133630/">Morbius: Preludes and Nightmares</a> (#3-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-epic-collection-the-living-vampire/4050-133733/">Morbius Epic Collection: The Living Vampire</a> (#3-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-epic-collection-its-always-darkest-before-th/4050-120262/">X-Men Epic Collection: It''s Always Darkest Before the Dawn</a> (#4 &amp; 23)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tigra-the-complete-collection/4050-123417/">Tigra: The Complete Collection</a> (#8 &amp; 67)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-maniron-man-marvel-team-up/4050-114422/">Spider-Man/Iron Man: Marvel Team-Up</a> (#9-11, 48-51, 72, 110 &amp; 145)</li><li><a href="/werewold-by-night-omnibus/4050-85148/" data-ref-id="4050-85148">Werewolf By Night Omnibus</a> (#12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/werewolf-by-night-the-complete-collection-1-volume/4000-626305/" data-ref-id="4000-626305">Werewolf By Night: The Complete Collection Volume 1</a> (#12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-captain-america/4050-129192/">Marvel-Verse: Captain America</a> (#13)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spidermandoctor-strange-the-way-to-dusty-death/4050-102278/" data-ref-id="4050-102278">Spider-Man/Doctor Strange: The Way To Dusty Death</a> (#21, 50-51, 76-77 &amp; 80-81)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-omnibus/4050-121088/">Marvel Horror Omnibus</a> (#24)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-brother-voodoo-1-volume-1/4000-851632/" data-ref-id="4000-851632">Marvel Masterworks: Brother Voodoo Volume 1</a> (#24)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-marvel-team-up-4-volume-4/4000-696947/" data-ref-id="4000-696947">Marvel Masterworks: Marvel Team-Up Volume 4</a> (#31-40)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-son-of-satan-classic/4050-95033/" data-ref-id="4050-95033">The Son of Satan Classic</a> (#32)</li><li><a href="/monster-of-frankenstein/4050-84984/" data-ref-id="4050-84984">Monster of Frankenstein</a> (#36-37)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/man-wolf-the-complete-collection/4050-121739/">Man-Wolf: The Complete Collection</a> (#36-37)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-marvel-team-up-5-volume-5/4000-785731/" data-ref-id="4000-785731">Marvel Masterworks: Marvel Team-Up Volume 5</a> (#41-52)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/killraven-epic-collection-warrior-of-the-worlds/4050-139434/">Killraven Epic Collection: Warrior of the Worlds</a> (#45)</li><li><a href="/deathlok-the-demolisher-the-complete-collection/4050-77316/" data-ref-id="4050-77316">Deathlok The Demolisher: The Complete Collection</a> (#46)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-marvel-two-in-one-2-volume-2/4000-621669/" data-ref-id="4000-621669">Marvel Masterworks: Marvel Two-In-One vol. 2</a> (#47)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-two-in-one-epic-collection-cry-monster/4050-112694/">Marvel Two-In-One Epic Collection: Cry Monster</a> (#47)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/xmen-epic-collection-second-genesis/4050-100394/" data-ref-id="4050-100394">X-Men Epic Collection: Second Genesis</a> (#53 &amp; 69-70)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-by-john-byrne-omnibus/4050-121104/">Spider-Man By John Byrne Omnibus</a> (#53-55, 59-70 &amp; 75)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-thanos-wars-infinity-origin/4050-118000/">The Thanos Wars: Infinity Origin</a> (#55)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-widow-marvel-team-up/4050-125684/">Black Widow: Marvel Team-Up</a> (#57, 82-85, 98 &amp; 140-141)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ms-marvel-epic-collection-this-woman-this-warrior/4050-116378/">Ms. Marvel Epic Collection: This Woman, This Warrior</a> (#61-62)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-ms-marvel-a-hero-is-born/4050-117049/">Captain Marvel: Ms. Marvel: A Hero Is Born</a> (#61-62 &amp; 76-77)</li><li><a href="/iron-fist-epic-collection-the-fury-of-iron-fist/4050-83138/" data-ref-id="4050-83138">Iron Fist Epic Collection: The Fury of Iron Fist</a> (#63-64)</li><li><a href="/marvel-universe-by-john-byrne-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-694138/" data-ref-id="4000-694138">Marvel Universe by John Byrne Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#63-64 &amp; 100 (Story B))</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-britain-legacy-of-a-legend/4050-95813/" data-ref-id="4050-95813">Captain Britain: Legacy of A Legend</a> (#65-66)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-lords-of-fear/4050-107359/" data-ref-id="4050-107359">Doctor Strange: Lords of Fear</a> (#68)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ms-marvel-epic-collection-the-woman-who-fell-to-ea/4050-118662/">Ms. Marvel Epic Collection: The Woman Who Fell To Earth</a> (#76-77)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-lives-again-omnibus/4050-131205/">Marvel Horror Lives Again! Omnibus</a> (#80-81)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/guardians-of-the-galaxy-tomorrows-heroes-omnibus/4050-116248/">Guardians of the Galaxy: Tomorrow''s Heroes Omnibus</a> (#86)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-epic-collection-proteus/4050-129905/">X-Men Epic Collection: Proteus</a> (#89)</li><li><a href="/spider-man-the-mutant-agenda/4050-54343/" data-ref-id="4050-54343">Spider-Man: The Mutant Agenda</a> (#90)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mockingbird-bobbi-morse-agent-of-shield/4050-92762/" data-ref-id="4050-92762">Mockingbird: Bobbi Morse, Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.</a> (#95)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/howard-the-duck-the-complete-collection-4-vol-4/4000-622940/" data-ref-id="4000-622940">Howard the Duck: The Complete Collection Vol. 4</a> (#96)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/fantastic-fourspider-man-classic/4050-41406/">Fantastic Four/Spider-Man Classic</a> (#100 &amp; 132-133)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/defenders-epic-collection-the-sixfingered-hand-sag/4050-93423/" data-ref-id="4050-93423">Defenders Epic Collection: The Six-Fingered Hand Saga</a> (#101)</li><li><a href="/antman-scott-lang/4050-82479/" data-ref-id="4050-82479">Ant-Man: Scott Lang</a> (#103)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/taskmaster-anything-you-can-do/4050-125196/">Taskmaster: Anything You Can Do...</a> (#103 &amp; 146)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-adventures-thorspider-man/4050-40732/">Marvel Adventures: Thor/Spider-Man</a> (#115-116)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-kravens-last-hunt-deluxe-edition/4050-112703/">Spider-Man: Kraven''s Last Hunt Deluxe Edition</a> (#128)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-wanda-and-vision/4050-132768/">Marvel-Verse: Wanda and Vision</a> (#129-130)</li><li><a href="/the-amazing-spider-man-the-complete-alien-costume-/4000-461312/" data-ref-id="4000-461312">The Amazing Spider-Man: The Complete Alien Costume Saga Book 1</a> (#141-145)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-black-widow/4050-126296/">Marvel-Verse: Black Widow</a> (#141)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-monica-rambeau/4050-116814/">Captain Marvel: Monica Rambeau</a> (#142-143)</li><li><a href="/the-amazing-spider-man-the-complete-alien-costume-/4000-486880/" data-ref-id="4000-486880">The Amazing Spider-Man: The Complete Alien Costume Saga Book 2</a> (#146-150)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-gold-capitan-america-6-la-era-de-la-bomba-l/4000-631321/">Marvel Gold. Capitán América - La era de la "Bomba Loca"</a> (#52) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-6-spiderman-integral-f/4000-612211/" data-ref-id="4000-612211">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes: Spiderman: Integral Frank Miller </a>(#100) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-el-universo-marvel-segun-fr/4050-105405/">Colección Frank Miller. El Universo Marvel según Frank Miller</a> (#100) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issues <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spiderman-marvel-teamup/4050-97538/" data-ref-id="4050-97538">#1-52</a>, <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-la-cosa-3/4000-285470/" data-ref-id="4000-285470">#47</a> &amp; <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spiderman-marvel-team-up/4050-43280/" data-ref-id="4050-43280">#53-150</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1972', '150', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4033788-mtu1vf8m054.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2577', 'Marvel Triple Action', 'When Strikes the Silver Surfer! - Enter... Dr. Doom!', '31', '<b><i>Marvel Triple Action</i> </b>was a reprint title from the 1970''s, reprinting older <i>Avengers</i> issues (after the first four issues were devoted to  <i>Fantastic Four</i> reprints).  For us kids who were growing up at the time, older comics were nearly impossible to get (for those of us in  the boondocks, anyway), and <i>MTA</i> provided us with some fantastic Avengers stories that we otherwise wouldn''t have been able to afford. By the time I was reading it, the book was reprinting stories from the era when the Avengers consisted of Captain America, Hawkeye, the Scarlet Witch, and Quicksilver - a weak lineup, it seemed to me, but the stories were fantastic. Don Heck''s art lended itself to dynamic figures, manic action, and fantastic machinery; Roy Thomas was fresh and creative and had a definite vision of super-heroic stories that was a perfect complement to what his mentor Stan Lee had been doing.<br/><br/>  As time wore on, later issues of the <i>Avengers</i> comic were reprinted. I got to read about the introduction of such characters as Ultron - whom I had always been intrigued with since Fantastic Four #150 - and his creation The Vision, a favorite superhero of mine and some schoolmates. Like <i>Marvel Tales</i> with the Spider-man stories and <i>Marvel''s Greatest Comics</i> with <i>Fantastic Four</i> issues, <i>MTA</i> provided kids of the 1970''s with beautiful, full-color reprints of classic Silver Age stories that we''d previously only heard about, and all for the same cover price as our regular comics. Even in this day of deluxe Marvel Masterworks and DC Archives, nothing beat the thrill of being able to go to the local comics dealer and pick up classic stories, month after month. Of course, it would help if I could be twelve years old again.', '1972', '47', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/10881-2577-11997-1-marvel-triple-action.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2580', 'Shanna the She-Devil', 'And A Jungle Queen Is Born!', '31', '<p>Shanna the She-Devil''s very first appearance and ongoing series. It was part of Marvel''s plan to break open the market for more female readers, with other series like <a href="/night-nurse/4050-20623/" data-ref-id="4050-20623"> Night Nurse</a>. The series however failed to catch on and lasted only 5 issues. Her story continued into <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ka-zar/4050-2692/">Ka-Zar Vol.1</a> issues 1 and 2 and in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/daredevil-109-dying-for-dollars/4000-14260/">Daredevil Vol.1 issue 109</a> and further issues after that. <br />Shanna would later become a mayor player in the <a href="/ka-zar-the-savage/4050-3087/" data-ref-id="4050-3087">Ka-Zar The Savage</a> series and become Ka-Zar''s wife.</p><p>Collected in <a href="/marvel-masterworks-ka-zar-2-volume-2/4000-663576/" data-ref-id="4000-663576">Marvel Masterworks: Ka-Zar Volume 2</a>.</p>', '1972', '5', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4033767-shanna1nm9m054.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2583', 'Warlock', 'Day of the Prophet', '31', '<p>Continues from <a href="/marvel-premiere/4050-2575/" data-ref-id="4050-2575">Marvel Premier</a> issue 2. <a href="//www.comicvine.com/adam-warlock/4005-6805/" data-ref-id="4005-6805">Adam Warlock</a> stars in his first own ongoing series. The series lasted until issue 8, after which it was on a hiatus for 2 years. After that, the series resumed with issue 9 (hence that issue 9 says it''s a "premier issue") and lasted until issue 15. Issue #9 is the first issue after the reviving of the series and was the continued story from <a href="../../strange-tales/49-2643/" rel="nofollow ">Strange Tales</a> #181.</p><p>Although a short series, it has been critically acclaimed for the ground breaking work <a href="//www.comicvine.com/jim-starlin/4040-7922/" data-ref-id="4040-7922">Jim Starlin</a> did in these comics.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-warlock-1-volume-one/4000-394410/" data-ref-id="4000-394410">Marvel Masterworks: Warlock Vol. 1</a> (#1-8)</li><li><a href="/essential-warlock-1-volume-1/4000-352254/" data-ref-id="4000-352254">Essential Warlock</a> (#1-15) *Black and white*</li><li><a href="/avengers-avengers-vs-thanos/4050-57667/" data-ref-id="4050-57667">Avengers vs Thanos</a> (#9-11)</li><li><a href="/guardians-of-the-galaxy-solo-classic-omnibus/4050-85759/" data-ref-id="4050-85759">Guardians of the Galaxy Solo Classic Omnibus</a> (#9-11)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-warlock-2-volume-two/4000-233678/" data-ref-id="4000-233678">Marvel Masterworks: Warlock Vol. 2</a> (#9-15)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/warlock-by-jim-starlin-1-tpb/4000-444317/" data-ref-id="4000-444317">Warlock By Jim Starlin: The Complete Collection vol. 1</a> (#9-15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gamora-guardian-of-the-galaxy/4050-94272/" data-ref-id="4050-94272">Gamora: Guardian of the Galaxy</a> (#9-11 &amp; 15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-thanos-wars-infinity-origin/4050-118000/">The Thanos Wars: Infinity Origin</a> (#9-15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-tales-thanos/4050-118253/">Marvel Tales: Thanos</a> (#10)</li><li><a href="/thanos-vs-hulk/4050-82251/" data-ref-id="4050-82251">Thanos vs. Hulk</a> (#12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/drax-guardian-of-the-galaxy/4050-93657/" data-ref-id="4050-93657">Drax: Guardian of the Galaxy</a> (#15)</li></ul><h4>Reprints</h4><ul><li><a href="/fantasy-masterpieces/4050-3003/" data-ref-id="4050-3003">Fantasy Masterpieces Vol 2</a> (1979)</li><li><a href="/warlock/4050-3156/" data-ref-id="4050-3156">Warlock</a> (1982)</li></ul>', '1972', '15', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2618088-power_of_warlock01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2584', 'Werewolf by Night', 'Eye of the Beholder!', '31', '<p>After enjoying a successful three issue stint in <a href="/marvel-spotlight/4050-2516/" data-ref-id="4050-2516"> Marvel Spotlight </a>(Vol. 1), Marvel awarded the Werewolf his own series, <b>Werewolf By Night</b>, in 1972. The series depicted the trials of Jack Russell who inherited the curse of the <a href="/werewolf-by-night/4005-4984/" data-ref-id="4005-4984"> Werewolf</a> on his eighteenth birthday. He frequently confronted menaces who wanted the man-beast for one nefarious purpose or another. His supporting cast included his devoted sister Lissa, who feared her approaching eighteenth birthday and possibly succumbing to the curse herself; Jack''s step-father Philip whom the siblings suspected murdered their mother, and Buck Cowan, the reporter who became Jack''s best friend and confidante. Other characters introduced in the series include the <a href="/the-hangman/4005-68262/" data-ref-id="4005-68262"> Hangman</a>, <a href="/topaz/4005-16079/" data-ref-id="4005-16079"> Topaz</a> (currently a member of the Witches), and most significantly, <a href="/moon-knight/4005-1493/" data-ref-id="4005-1493"> Moon Knight</a>.</p><p>The series was at its artistic peak in its first two years with decent writing by <a href="/gerry-conway/4040-40871/" data-ref-id="4040-40871"> Gerry Conway</a>, <a href="/len-wein/4040-41457/" data-ref-id="4040-41457"> Len Wein</a> and <a href="/marv-wolfman/4040-41478/" data-ref-id="4040-41478"> Marv Wolfman</a> and excellent art by <a href="/mike-ploog/4040-26572/" data-ref-id="4040-26572"> Mike Ploog</a>, <a href="/tom-sutton/4040-4016/" data-ref-id="4040-4016"> Tom Sutton</a> and <a href="/gil-kane/4040-1764/" data-ref-id="4040-1764"> Gil Kane</a>, developing a style that was referred to in the letters pages as "California Gothic". Then the book took a severe drop in quality, with inconsistent stories by <a href="/doug-moench/4040-42016/" data-ref-id="4040-42016"> Doug Moench</a> and pedestrian art by <a href="/don-perlin/4040-1539/" data-ref-id="4040-1539"> Don Perlin</a>. In 1976, the Marvel monster boom of the mid-70s went bust and the series was nearly canceled, but a leveling off in sales kept it in publication, albeit demoted to bi-monthly status. Feeling restricted by the fact that a werewolf can appear for only three nights out of a month, Moench and Perlin made changes to the Werewolf character. They put Jack in full control of the Werewolf, giving him the abilities to think, speak and transform at will. It appeared they were grooming him for a career as a super-hero as they completely phased-out the California Gothic style. The success of the experiment proved inconclusive, as the series was canceled with the 43rd issue, leaving a developing subplot with the abduction of Jack''s friend Buck Cowan unresolved.</p><p>The Werewolf also starred in the companion series <a href="/giant-size-werewolf/4050-2689/" data-ref-id="4050-2689"> <b>GIANT-SIZE WEREWOLF</b></a>.</p><p>A second volume of <a href="/werewolf-by-night/4050-18541/" data-ref-id="4050-18541"> <b>WEREWOLF BY NIGHT</b></a> was published is 1998, lasing six issues.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/werewold-by-night-omnibus/4050-85148/" data-ref-id="4050-85148">Werewolf By Night Omnibus</a> (#1-43)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/werewolf-by-night-the-complete-collection-1-volume/4000-626305/" data-ref-id="4000-626305">Werewolf By Night: The Complete Collection Volume 1</a> (#1-15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengersdoctor-strange-rise-of-the-darkhold/4050-114044/">Avengers/Doctor Strange: Rise of the Darkhold</a> (#1, 3 &amp; 15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-tomb-of-dracula-the-complete-collection-2-volu/4000-687022/" data-ref-id="4000-687022">The Tomb of Dracula: The Complete Collection Volume 2</a> (#15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/werewolf-by-night-in-the-blood/4050-125395/">Werewolf by Night: In the Blood</a> (#15)</li><li><a href="/werewolf-by-night-the-complete-collection-2-volume/4000-656721/" data-ref-id="4000-656721">Werewolf By Night: The Complete Collection Volume 2</a> (#16-30)</li><li><a href="/moon-knight-epic-collection-bad-moon-rising/4050-77333/" data-ref-id="4050-77333">Moon Knight Epic Collection: Bad Moon Rising</a> (#32-33)</li><li><a href="/moon-knight-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-824088/" data-ref-id="4000-824088">Moon Knight Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#32-33)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-omnibus/4050-121088/">Marvel Horror Omnibus</a> (#39-41)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-brother-voodoo-1-volume-1/4000-851632/" data-ref-id="4000-851632">Marvel Masterworks: Brother Voodoo Volume 1</a> (#39-41)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/100-max-hombe-lobo/4050-41720/" data-ref-id="4050-41720">100% MAX: Hombe Lobo</a> (#15) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-65-caballero-luna-1-cu/4000-612301/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Caballero Luna 1: Cuenta atrás hacia la oscuridad</a> (#32-33) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1972', '43', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/11278-2584-12500-1-werewolf-by-night.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2631', 'Crazy', 'Beware The Forbush-Man My Son!', '31', NULL, '1973', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/55747-2631-77796-1-crazy.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2632', 'Crypt of Shadows', 'Midnight On Black Mountain', '31', '<p>What nameless evil lurks in...the Crypt of Shadows!! A Marvel Comics horror series, with new and reprinted short stories full of horrifying events. It lasted for 21 issues.</p>', '1973', '21', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/59031-2632-92026-1-crypt-of-shadows.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2636', 'Ghost Rider', 'A Woman Possessed!', '31', '<p><a href="/ghost-rider-blaze/4005-6108/" data-ref-id="4005-6108">Ghost Rider</a> (Johnny Blaze) received his own ongoing series after his debut in <a href="/marvel-spotlight/4050-2516/" data-ref-id="4050-2516">Marvel Spotlight</a>. This volume bearing the title Ghost Rider lasted for ten years and 81 issues.</p><h3>Writers</h3><ul><li><a href="/gary-friedrich/4040-43812/" data-ref-id="4040-43812">Gary Friedrich</a> #1-4, 6, 10(reprint of <a href="/marvel-spotlight-5-origin-of-the-ghost-rider/4000-12422/" data-ref-id="4000-12422">Marvel Spotlight #5</a>)</li><li><a href="/marv-wolfman/4040-41478/" data-ref-id="4040-41478">Marv Wolfman</a> #5, 20</li><li><a href="/doug-moench/4040-42016/" data-ref-id="4040-42016">Doug Moench</a> #5</li><li><a href="/tony-isabella/4040-42209/" data-ref-id="4040-42209">Tony Isabella</a> #6-9, 11-15, 17-19</li><li><a href="/frank-robbins/4040-34476/" data-ref-id="4040-34476">Frank Robbins</a> #12</li><li><a href="/bill-mantlo/4040-42478/" data-ref-id="4040-42478">Bill Mantlo</a> #16</li><li><a href="/gerry-conway/4040-40871/" data-ref-id="4040-40871">Gerry Conway</a> #21-23</li><li><a href="/don-glut/4040-57469/" data-ref-id="4040-57469">Don Glut</a> #22</li><li><a href="/jim-shooter/4040-40450/" data-ref-id="4040-40450">Jim Shooter</a> #23-27</li><li><a href="/roger-mckenzie/4040-44822/" data-ref-id="4040-44822">Roger McKenzie</a> #28-34</li><li><a href="/don-perlin/4040-1539/" data-ref-id="4040-1539">Don Perlin</a> #32-33</li><li><a href="/jim-starlin/4040-7922/" data-ref-id="4040-7922">Jim Starlin</a> #35</li><li><a href="/michael-fleisher/4040-44657/" data-ref-id="4040-44657">Michael Fleisher</a> #36-66</li><li><a href="/jm-dematteis/4040-41043/" data-ref-id="4040-41043">J.M. DeMatteis</a> #67, 71, 74-81</li><li><a href="/roger-stern/4040-41502/" data-ref-id="4040-41502">Roger Stern</a> #68-70, 72-73</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-son-of-satan-classic/4050-95033/" data-ref-id="4050-95033">The Son of Satan Classic</a> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="/essential-ghost-rider-1-volume-1/4000-153492/" data-ref-id="4000-153492">Essential Ghost Rider #1 - Volume 1</a> (#1-20)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ghost-rider-1-volume-1/4000-721798/" data-ref-id="4000-721798">Marvel Masterworks: Ghost Rider Volume 1</a> (#1-5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hellstrom-evil-origins/4050-129473/">Hellstrom: Evil Origins</a> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ghost-rider-2-volume-2/4000-821522/" data-ref-id="4000-821522">Marvel Masterworks: Ghost Rider Volume 2</a> (#6-20)</li><li><a href="/marvel-universe-by-john-byrne-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-694138/" data-ref-id="4000-694138">Marvel Universe by John Byrne Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#20)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/essential-ghost-rider-2-volume-2/4000-153726/" data-ref-id="4000-153726">Essential Ghost Rider #2 - Volume 2</a> (#21-50)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-ghost-rider-3-volume-3/4000-891875/" data-ref-id="4000-891875">Marvel Masterworks: Ghost Rider Volume 3</a> (#21-35)</li><li><a href="/ghost-racers/4050-87545/" data-ref-id="4050-87545">Ghost Racers</a> (#35)</li><li><a href="/essential-ghost-rider-3-volume-3/4000-186481/" data-ref-id="4000-186481">Essential Ghost Rider #3 - Volume 3</a> (#51-65)</li><li><a href="/essential-ghost-rider-4-volume-4/4000-239679/" data-ref-id="4000-239679">Essential Ghost Rider #4 - Volume 4</a> (#66-81)</li></ul>', '1973', '81', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12128-2636-13577-1-ghost-rider.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2639', 'Marvel Double Feature', NULL, '31', '<p>Marvel Double Feature was a reprint title, originally reprinting issues of Tales of Suspense and giving Captain America lead billing on the cover. The final two issues dropped Iron Man in favour of reprinting a story from Captain America that featured Black Panther.</p>', '1973', '21', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12394-2639-13889-1-marvel-double-featur.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2640', 'Marvel Spectacular', 'The Power of Pluto!', '31', '<p>A reprint series of earlier adventures of Thor.</p>', '1973', '19', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12056-2640-13484-1-marvel-spectacular.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2642', 'SHIELD', 'When the Unliving Strike!', '31', '<p>This short-run volume features <a href="/nick-fury/4005-3202/" data-ref-id="4005-3202"> Nick Fury</a> and his <a href="/shield/4060-3775/" data-ref-id="4060-3775"> S.H.I.E.L.D.</a> agents in stories reprinted from <a href="/strange-tales/4050-18066/" data-ref-id="4050-18066">Strange Tales</a>. </p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Volume named per the indicia.</p>', '1973', '5', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/11630-2642-12935-1-shield-nick-fury-an.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2643', 'Strange Tales', 'Brother Voodoo', '31', '<p>This series is a continuation of the <a href="/strange-tales/4050-18066/" data-ref-id="4050-18066">Strange Tales</a> series that ended in 1968 with issue 168. That series'' name was transformed into <a href="/doctor-strange/4050-2403/" data-ref-id="4050-2403">Doctor Strange</a> with issue 169 while the Nick Fury stories moved to a new title, <a href="/nick-fury-agent-of-shield/4050-2410/" data-ref-id="4050-2410">Nick Fury, Agent of SHIELD</a>.</p><p>Strangely enough, a few years later, this series came to light with a new issue 169. This comic-series is mostly known for introducing Brother Voodoo and Golem to the Marvel Universe, as well as the beginning of Jim Starlin''s run on Warlock. After Strange Tales 181, Warlock''s series continues in number 9 of <a href="../../warlock/49-2583/" rel="nofollow ">Warlock''s own</a> (revived) series.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/warlock-by-jim-starlin-1-tpb/4000-444317/" data-ref-id="4000-444317">Warlock By Jim Starlin: The Complete Collection vol. 1</a> (#178-181)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvels-guardians-of-the-galaxy-prelude-1-tpb/4000-458964/" data-ref-id="4000-458964">Marvel''s Guardians of the Galaxy Prelude Volume 1</a> (#181)</li></ul>', '1973', '20', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3754591-169.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2668', 'The Superman Family', 'Death Bites with Fangs of Stone / The Gift-Wrapped Doom', '10', '<p><em><b>The Superman Family</b></em> was a DC Comics comic book series which ran from 1974 to 1982 featuring primarily stories starring the supporting characters in the Superman comics. The term is often used to refer to the extended cast of characters (especially super-powered ones) of comics books associated with Superman.</p><p>The title was an amalgamation of the titles <em><a href="/supermans-girl-friend-lois-lane/4050-19245/" data-ref-id="4050-19245">Superman''s Girl Friend, Lois Lane</a></em> and <em><a href="/supermans-pal-jimmy-olsen/4050-19172/" data-ref-id="4050-19172">Superman''s Pal Jimmy Olsen</a></em> and the first series of <em><a href="/supergirl/4050-2555/" data-ref-id="4050-2555">Supergirl</a></em>, therefore immediately becoming DC''s flagship title with the highest sales for the remainder. The first issue, #164, took its numbering from the Jimmy Olsen title, which had reached issue <a href="/superman-s-pal-jimmy-olsen-163-a-world-that-came-b/4000-134734/" data-ref-id="4000-134734">#163</a> and thus had the most issues published (the Lois Lane series ended at issue <a href="/superman-s-girl-friend-lois-lane-137-the-stolen-su/4000-125593/" data-ref-id="4000-125593">#137</a>, while the newly-launched <em>Supergirl</em> volume 1 series had only made it to <a href="/supergirl-10-death-of-a-prez/4000-14554/" data-ref-id="4000-14554">#10</a>). The three leads rotated new stories in each issue with <a href="/reprinted-material/4015-56278/" data-ref-id="4015-56278">reprints</a> as a backup feature for other the characters (Issues #164-181). <em>The Superman Family</em> started as a 100-page format from issues #164-169. The quantity of pages dropped to 64-pages with issue #170 and dropped to 48-pages with issue #178. In 1976 (<a href="/the-superman-family-182-death-on-ice/4000-17226/" data-ref-id="4000-17226">#182</a>), <em>The Superman Family</em> became the first DC Comics to feature the 80-page Dollar Comics format. The new 80-page format featured all new stories for all the characters. Later the page quantity dropped to 64-pages starting with issue <a href="/the-superman-family-191-the-incredible-shrinking-t/4000-18799/" data-ref-id="4000-18799">#191</a> and finally to 48-pages starting with issue <a href="/the-superman-family-205-magic-over-miami-catch-a-f/4000-20931/" data-ref-id="4000-20931">#205</a>. The series briefly featured a "no ads" and a wraparound cover format from issues #191-196. The series was published on a bi-monthly schedule until 1981, when the series was published on a monthly schedule starting with issue <a href="/the-superman-family-207-look-homeward-argonian-the/4000-21203/" data-ref-id="4000-21203">#207</a>.</p><p>Other featured series in addition to:</p><p>* Lois Lane (166,169,172,175,178,181-222)</p><p>* Supergirl (165,168,171,174,177,180,182-222)</p><p>* Jimmy Olsen (164,167,170,173,176,179,182-222)</p><p>* "Superboy" (182,191-198) — The adventures of the Earth-One Superman as a teenage super-hero. This series continued from <em><a href="/adventure-comics/4050-3105/" data-ref-id="4050-3105">Adventure Comics #458</a></em> and led to the feature leaving the title for its own in 1980, <em><a href="/new-adventures-of-superboy/4050-3035/" data-ref-id="4050-3035">The New Adventures of Superboy</a></em>.</p><p>* "<em>The Private Life of Clark Kent</em>" (195-197, 199-215) — The adventures of Clark Kent in which he used his powers and skills without becoming Superman. This feature had moved over from <em><a href="/superman/4050-773/" data-ref-id="4050-773">Superman</a></em> after <a href="/superman-328-the-attack-of-the-kryptonoid-clark-ke/4000-18875/" data-ref-id="4000-18875">#328</a>.</p><p>* "<em>Mr. and Mrs. Superman</em>" (195-196, 198-222) — The adventures of the <a href="/kal-l/4005-62833/" data-ref-id="4005-62833">Earth-Two Superman</a> and his wife, <a href="/lois-lane/4005-1808/" data-ref-id="4005-1808">Lois</a>. This feature had moved from Superman after <a href="/superman-329-i-have-met-the-enemy-and-it-is-me-sec/4000-18945/" data-ref-id="4000-18945">#329</a>. #200 of this series also had a story that dealt with a married Lois and Clark, but as part of an issue-long <a href="/imaginary-stories/4015-55849/" data-ref-id="4015-55849">Imaginary Story</a> set on Earth-1 at the turn of the millennium.</p><p>* "Krypto" (182-192) — The adventures of Superman''s dog.</p><p>* "<a href="/nightwing-flamebird/4060-56092/" data-ref-id="4060-56092">Nightwing and Flamebird</a>" (182-194) — The adventures of the second Nightwing and Flamebird team of heroes (<a href="/van-zee/4005-31096/" data-ref-id="4005-31096">Van-Zee</a> and <a href="/ak-var/4005-65220/" data-ref-id="4005-65220">Ak-Var</a>) in the <a href="/kandor/4020-41290/" data-ref-id="4020-41290">Bottled City of Kandor</a>.</p><p>* "<em>The Misadventures of Superbaby</em>" (216) — A one-shot story featuring Superbaby.</p><p>DC published several other "Family" titles concurrent with <em>The Superman Family</em>: <em><a href="/batman-family/4050-2727/" data-ref-id="4050-2727">Batman Family</a></em> (1975-78), <em><a href="/super-team-family/4050-2741/" data-ref-id="4050-2741">Super-Team Family</a></em> (1975-1978) and <em><a href="/tarzan-family/4050-2743/" data-ref-id="4050-2743">Tarzan Family</a></em> (1975-76). As a rule, DC''s "Family" titles contained mostly reprints, and featured a higher page count (and higher price) than DC''s normal books. (In 2004, <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel Comics</a> paid homage to DC''s "Family" titles with <em><a href="/spider-man-family/4050-18459/" data-ref-id="4050-18459">Spider-Man Family</a></em>.)</p><p>In 1982, with issue #222, <em>The Superman Family</em> series was cancelled to make room for the <em><a href="/supergirl-vol-2/4050-3113/" data-ref-id="4050-3113">Daring New Adventures of Supergirl</a></em>, which briefly featured a Lois Lane back-up series. The <a href="/doom-patrol/4060-5701/" data-ref-id="4060-5701">Doom Patrol</a> appeared alongside Supergirl in issues of both series.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadman-omnibus/4050-132454/">Deadman Omnibus</a> (#183)</li></ul>', '1974', '59', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12621-2668-14164-1-superman-family-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2675', 'The Deadly Hands of Kung Fu', 'The Testing of Shang-Chi', '31', '<p>A black and white magazine from Marvel Comics. Coming from the success of the Martial-Arts craze in the early 1970''s in America. It housed the first appearance of such Marvel superheroes such as Jack of Hearts and the White Tiger to name a few.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadly-hands-of-kung-fu-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-557364/" data-ref-id="4000-557364">The Deadly Hands of Kung Fu Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#1-18)</li><li><a href="/deadly-hands-of-kung-fu-out-of-the-past/4050-77630/" data-ref-id="4050-77630">Deadly Hands of Kung Fu: Out Of The Past</a> (#1 and 32-33)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-deadly-hands-of-kung-fu-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-600566/" data-ref-id="4000-600566">The Deadly Hands of Kung Fu Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#19-33)</li></ul>', '1974', '33', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12649-2675-14192-1-deadly-hands-of-kung.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2676', 'Doctor Strange', 'Through an Orb Darkly', '31', '<p>The second ongoing series starring Doctor Strange. After the Doctor''s adventures in <a href="/strange-tales/4050-18066/" data-ref-id="4050-18066"> Strange Tales Vol.1</a>, his continued adventures in<a href="/doctor-strange/4050-2403/" data-ref-id="4050-2403"> Doctor Strange Vol.1 </a>and his spot in issues 3 - 14 of <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-premiere/4050-2575/">Marvel Premiere</a>, here Steven Strange is once more ready to battle the spiritual threads that threaten Earth!</p><p>The series lasted for 81 issues after which it continued as <a href="/strange-tales/4050-3863/" data-ref-id="4050-3863">Strange Tales Vol.3</a>.</p><h4>Additional Volumes</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange/4050-2403/" data-ref-id="4050-2403">Doctor Strange Volume 1</a></li><li>Doctor Strange Volume 2</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange/4050-85094/" data-ref-id="4050-85094">Doctor Strange Volume 3</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange/4050-111415/" data-ref-id="4050-111415">Doctor Strange Volume 4</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange/4050-148962/" data-ref-id="4050-148962">Doctor Strange Volume 5</a></li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li>Marvel Masterworks Vol. 5 (#1-9)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-epic-collection-a-separate-reality/4050-95006/" data-ref-id="4050-95006">Doctor Strange Epic Collection: A Separate Reality</a> (#1-5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-epic-collection-alone-against-etern/4050-133481/">Doctor Strange Epic Collection: Alone Against Eternity</a> (#6-28)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-tomb-of-dracula-the-complete-collection-4-volu/4000-797288/" data-ref-id="4000-797288">The Tomb of Dracula: The Complete Collection Volume 4</a> (#14)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-doctor-strange-7-volume-7/4000-557368/" data-ref-id="4000-557368">Marvel Masterworks: Doctor Strange Volume 7</a> (#23-37)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-what-is-it-that-disturbs-you-stephe/4050-95213/" data-ref-id="4050-95213">Doctor Strange: What Is It That Disturbs You, Stephen?</a> (#34)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-doctor-strange-8-volume-8/4000-594966/" data-ref-id="4000-594966">Marvel Masterworks: Doctor Strange Volume 8</a> (#38-45)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-universe-by-chris-claremont-omnibus/4050-103251/" data-ref-id="4050-103251">Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont Omnibus</a> (#38-45)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-brother-voodoo-1-volume-1/4000-851632/" data-ref-id="4000-851632">Marvel Masterworks: Brother Voodoo Volume 1</a> (#41)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-doctor-strange-9-volume-9/4000-723125/" data-ref-id="4000-723125">Marvel Masterworks: Doctor Strange Volume 9</a> (#47-57)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-horror-omnibus/4050-121088/">Marvel Horror Omnibus</a> (#48)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-doctor-strange/4050-138455/">Marvel-Verse: Doctor Strange</a> (#55)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/doctor-strange-doctor-doom-triumph-and-torment/4050-89079/" data-ref-id="4050-89079">Doctor Strange &amp; Doctor Doom: Triumph &amp; Torment</a> (#57)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengersdoctor-strange-rise-of-the-darkhold/4050-114044/">Avengers/Doctor Strange: Rise of the Darkhold</a> (#59-62, 67 &amp; 81)</li><li><a href="/doctor-strange-dont-pay-the-ferryman/4050-85095/" data-ref-id="4050-85095">Doctor Strange: Don''t Pay the Ferryman</a> (#75-81)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-agony-and-ecstasy/4050-119528/">Cloak and Dagger: Agony and Ecstasy</a> (#78)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-omnibus/4050-130070/">Cloak and Dagger Omnibus</a> (#78)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-75-doctor-extrano-de-r/4000-612313/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Doctor Extraño de Roger Stern</a> (#46-73) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#74) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issues <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-dr-extrano/4050-41949/" data-ref-id="4050-41949">#15-76</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1974', '81', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12773-2676-14334-1-doctor-strange.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2677', 'Giant-Size Avengers', 'Nuklo--The Invader That Time Forgot', '31', '<p>The Giant-Size Avengers companion to the monthly Avengers series. It featured al new stories.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-epic-collection-the-avengersdefenders-war/4050-109747/">Avengers Epic Collection: The Avengers/Defenders War</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-avengers-14-volume-14/4000-460712/" data-ref-id="4000-460712">Marvel Masterworks: Avengers Vol. 14</a> (#2-4)</li><li><a href="/avengers-celestial-madonna/4050-29381/" data-ref-id="4050-29381">Avengers: Celestial Madonna</a> (#2-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-the-complete-celestial-madonna-saga/4050-100682/" data-ref-id="4050-100682">Avengers: The Complete Celestial Madonna Saga</a> (#2-4)</li><li><a href="/avengers-the-vibranium-collection/4050-81281/" data-ref-id="4050-81281">Avengers: The Vibranium Collection</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvels-guardians-of-the-galaxy-prelude-2-volume-2/4000-590798/" data-ref-id="4000-590798">Marvel''s Guardians of the Galaxy Prelude Volume 2</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-wanda-and-vision/4050-132768/">Marvel-Verse: Wanda and Vision</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/vision-and-the-scarlet-witch-the-saga-of-wanda-and/4050-133210/">Vision &amp; The Scarlet Witch: The Saga of Wanda and Vision</a> (#4)</li></ul>', '1974', '5', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2861979-giantsizeavengers01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2683', 'Giant-Size Fantastic Four', 'Cataclysm!', '31', '<p>Continues from <a href="/giant-size-super-stars/4050-21983/" data-ref-id="4050-21983">Giant-Size Super-Stars</a> #1. With the second issue, the series was re-titled GIANT-SIZE FANTASTIC FOUR. The series (under both titles) lasted six issues. Issue 4 features the first appearance of popular X-Factor character Madrox the Multiple Man.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-epic-collection-its-always-darkest-before-th/4050-120262/">X-Men Epic Collection: It''s Always Darkest Before the Dawn</a> (#4)</li></ul>', '1974', '5', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4101122-%24t2ec16rhjfoe9nh6nwf5bp5eyjosr%21~~60_57.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2684', 'Giant-Size Man-Thing', '"How Will We Keep Warm When the Last Flame Dies?" & "Ice-Monster Cometh!" & "I Was the Invisible Man!" & "Goom! The Thing from Planet X!"', '31', '<p>Giant-Size specials accompanying the first Man-Thing solo series from the early 1970''s.</p><p>Collected in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/man-thing-by-steve-gerber-the-complete-collection-/4000-555528/" data-ref-id="4000-555528">Man-Thing by Steve Gerber: The Complete Collection Vol. 2</a>.</p>', '1974', '5', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12950-2684-14522-1-giant-size-man-thing.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2686', 'Giant-Size Spider-Man', 'Ship of Fiends!', '31', '<p>Series of specials.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-tomb-of-dracula-the-complete-collection-2-volu/4000-687022/" data-ref-id="4000-687022">The Tomb of Dracula: The Complete Collection Volume 2</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/shang-chi-master-of-kung-fu-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-533502/" data-ref-id="4000-533502">Shang-Chi Master of Kung-Fu Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="/master-of-kung-fu-epic-collection-weapon-of-the-so/4050-109201/" data-ref-id="4050-109201">Master of Kung Fu Epic Collection: Weapon of the Soul</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-punisher-back-to-the-war-omnibus/4050-104072/" data-ref-id="4050-104072">The Punisher: Back To the War Omnibus</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-marvel-team-up-4-volume-4/4000-696947/" data-ref-id="4000-696947">Marvel Masterworks: Marvel Team-Up Volume 4</a> (#4-5)</li></ul>', '1974', '6', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/12855-2686-14421-1-giant-size-spider-ma.jpg', '0');
