en: Inferno Omnibus</a> (#146-148)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/acts-of-vengeance-spider-man-and-the-x-men/4050-136147/">Acts of Vengeance: Spider-Man &amp; The X-Men</a> (#158-160)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spiderman-vs-the-vulture/4050-101492/" data-ref-id="4050-101492">Spider-Man vs. The Vulture</a> (#186-188)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-son-of-the-goblin/4050-27280/">Spider-Man: Son of the Goblin</a> (#189 &amp; 200)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-vs-venom-omnibus/4050-113261/">Spider-Man Vs. Venom Omnibus</a> (#201-203)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-amazing-spider-man-epic-collection-maximum-car/4050-124287/">The Amazing Spider-Man Epic Collection: Maximum Carnage</a> (#201-203)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/amazing-spider-man-epic-collection-lifetheft/4050-142111/">Amazing Spider-Man Epic Collection: Lifetheft</a> (#211)</li><li><a href="/daredevil-typhoids-kiss/4050-83808/" data-ref-id="4050-83808">Daredevil: Typhoid''s Kiss</a> (#213-214)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-clone-saga-omnibus-1-vol-1/4000-552429/" data-ref-id="4000-552429">Spider-Man Clone Saga Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#217-224)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-clone-saga-omnibus-2-vol-2/4000-634544/" data-ref-id="4000-634544">Spider-Man Clone Saga Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#225-229)</li><li><a href="/spider-man-ben-reilly-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-696366/" data-ref-id="4000-696366">Spider-Man: Ben Reilly Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#230-233)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/carnage-classic/4050-91743/" data-ref-id="4050-91743">Carnage Classic</a> (#233)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-the-many-hosts-of-carnage/4050-121255/">Spider-Man: The Many Hosts of Carnage</a> (#233)</li><li><a href="/spider-man-ben-reilly-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-803675/" data-ref-id="4000-803675">Spider-Man: Ben Reilly Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#234-241)</li><li><a href="/the-amazing-spider-man-identity-crisis/4050-49119/" data-ref-id="4050-49119">The Amazing Spider-Man: Identity Crisis</a> (#257-258)</li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/spiderman-the-gathering-of-five/4050-70142/" data-ref-id="4050-70142">Spider-Man: The Gathering of Five</a> (#262-263)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-6-spiderman-integral-f/4000-612211/" data-ref-id="4000-612211">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Spiderman: Integral Frank Miller </a>(#27-28) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-el-universo-marvel-segun-fr/4050-105405/">Colección Frank Miller. El Universo Marvel según Frank Miller</a> (#27-28) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-52-peter-parker-el-esp/4000-612260/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Peter Parker, El Espectacular Spiderman: Noches de Nueva York</a> (#64-89) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-74-peter-parker-el-esp/4000-612311/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Peter Parker, El Espectacular Spiderman: Punto de ruptura</a> (#90-110) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/best-of-marvel-essentials-spiderman-la-muerte-de-j/4050-41941/" data-ref-id="4050-41941">Best of Marvel Essentials: Spiderman: La Muerte De Jean DeWolff</a> (#107-110)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-57-el-asombroso-spider/4000-612265/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - El Asombroso Spiderman: La era del traje negro</a> (#111) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#111) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-80-peter-parker-el-esp/4000-612318/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Peter Parker, El Espectacular Spiderman: La Caza de la Araña</a> (#112-130 &amp; #134-136) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-spider-man-6-vida-en-el-pabellon-de-/4000-614363/">Coleccionable Spider-Man - Vida en el pabellón de perros rabiosos</a> (#113) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/100-marvel-hc-spiderman-la-ultima-caceria-de-krave/4050-104357/" data-ref-id="4050-104357">100% Marvel HC. Spiderman: La última cacería de Kraven</a> (#131-132) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issues <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/peter-parker-spiderman/4050-42855/" data-ref-id="4050-42855">#1-63</a> have translated into Spanish.</p>', '1976', '180', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2432028-spectacularspider_man001.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2873', 'Super Heroes Album', NULL, '2378', '<p>Title changed from <a href="/super-heroes/4050-28253/" data-ref-id="4050-28253"> Super Heroes</a> to Super Heroes Album starting with issue #3.</p>', '1976', '17', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/42426-2873-48346-1-super-heroes-album.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2884', 'Black Lightning', 'Black Lightning', '10', '<figure data-align="right" data-size="small" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/14/148518/2959667-black%20lightnng%20ad.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2959667" data-ratio="1.4752136752137" data-width="585" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 585px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:147.5%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/14/148518/2959667-black%20lightnng%20ad.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2959667"><img alt="No Caption Provided" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/14/148518/2959667-black%20lightnng%20ad.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/14/148518/2959667-black%20lightnng%20ad.jpg 585w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/14/148518/2959667-black%20lightnng%20ad.jpg 433w" sizes="(max-width: 433px) 100vw, 433px" data-width="433"></a></figure><p>Black Lighting was the creation of writer Tony Isabella and artist Trevor Von Eeden. Originally DC planned to have their first ever black headlining character be "The Black Bomber", a black hero who was secretly a white racist. Thankfully, the project fell through when the editor left and writer Tony Isabella was able to introduce his Black Lightning character that he had been working on and the project was handed over to him.</p><p>Isabella handed over to book to Denny O''Neil after the 10th issue, but the book was canceled after #11. Black Lightning next went on to become a back-up feature in <em>Detective Comics</em>.</p><p>Note: This series was implemented as part of the <a href="/dc-explosion-and-implosion/4015-56163/" data-ref-id="4015-56163">DC Explosion,</a> but was subsequently cancelled in what became known as the DC Implosion.</p><p>Collected in <a href="/black-lightning-1-volume-1/4000-523220/" data-ref-id="4000-523220">Black Lightning Volume 1</a>.</p>', '1977', '11', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15528-2884-17309-1-black-lightning.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2886', 'DC Special Series', '5-Star Super-Hero Spectacular', '10', '<p>Launched as part of the <a href="/dc-explosion-and-implosion/4015-56163/" data-ref-id="4015-56163">DC Explosion</a>, <i>DC Special Series</i> was anthology that focused on a different character every month. It would survive the following Implosion, lasting until the 1981 #27 - <i>Batman vs. The Incredible Hulk</i> - a <a href="/crossover/4015-55803/" data-ref-id="4015-55803">crossover</a> between <a href="/dc-comics/4010-10/" data-ref-id="4010-10">DC</a> &amp; <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/justice-league-of-america-the-bronze-age-omnibus-3/4000-867809/" data-ref-id="4000-867809">Justice League of America: The Bronze Age Omnibus Volume 3</a> (#6)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadman-omnibus/4050-132454/">Deadman Omnibus</a> (#8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-gods-by-gerry-conway/4050-126349/">New Gods by Gerry Conway</a> (#10)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-arkham-ras-al-ghul/4050-117730/">Batman Arkham: Ra''s Al Ghul</a> (#15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-tales-of-the-demon/4050-125639/">Batman: Tales of the Demon</a> (#15)</li><li><a href="/batman-a-celebration-of-75-years/4050-75707/" data-ref-id="4050-75707">Batman: A Celebration of 75 Years</a> (#21)</li></ul>', '1977', '27', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15261-2886-17013-1-dc-special-series.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2896', 'Black Panther', 'King Solomon''s Frog!', '31', '<p>After the Black Panther''s stint in <a href="/jungle-action/4050-2574/" data-ref-id="4050-2574"> Jungle Action</a>, the African hero stars in his very own magazine, drawn and written by the legendary Jack Kirby!</p><h4>Collected Edition</h4><ul><li><a href="/black-panther-by-jack-kirby-volume-one/4000-294017/" data-ref-id="4000-294017"> Black Panther by Jack Kirby Vol. 1</a> (#1-7)</li><li><a href="/essential-black-panther/4050-49774/" data-ref-id="4050-49774">Essential Black Panther</a> (#1-10)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-black-panther-2-volume-2/4000-556473/" data-ref-id="4000-556473">Marvel Masterworks: Black Panther Volume 2</a> (#1-15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-panther-epic-collection-revenge-of-the-black/4050-117199/">Black Panther Epic Collection: Revenge of the Black Panther</a> (#1-15)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kirby-returns/4050-120559/">Kirby Returns!</a> (#1-3)</li><li><a href="/black-panther-by-jack-kirby-volume-two/4000-294018/" data-ref-id="4000-294018">Black Panther by Jack Kirby Vol. 2</a> (#8-13)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-black-panther/4050-124689/">Marvel-Verse: Black Panther</a> (#14-15)</li></ul>', '1977', '15', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15334-2896-17091-1-black-panther.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2901', 'Godzilla', 'The Coming!', '31', '<p>Marvel Comics got the rights to publish comics of the famed Godzilla monster. Resulting in this series, where the famous monster is set firmly into the Marvel Universe and interacts with the Avengers, among others.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/essential-godzilla/4050-36892/" data-ref-id="4050-36892">Essential Godzilla</a> (#1-24)</li></ul>', '1977', '24', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15869-2901-17681-1-godzilla.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2905', 'Iron Man Annual', 'What Price Victory?; Disaster!; When Fall The Mighty!; The Power of Iron Man!', '31', '<p>This series accompanies <a href="/iron-man/4050-2407/" data-ref-id="4050-2407">Iron Man vol. 1</a> and <a href="/iron-man/4050-6504/" data-ref-id="4050-6504">Iron Man vol. 3</a>. Published for fifteen issues until 1994. It resumed in 1998 with unique titles;</p><ul><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/iron-man-captain-america-annual-98/4050-30391/" data-ref-id="4050-30391">Iron Man / Captain America ''98</a></li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/iron-man-annual-99/4050-60457/" data-ref-id="4050-60457">Iron Man 1999</a></li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/iron-man-annual-2000/4050-60459/" data-ref-id="4050-60459">Iron Man 2000</a></li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/iron-man-annual-2001/4050-60460/" data-ref-id="4050-60460">Iron Man 2001</a></li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/man-thing-by-steve-gerber-the-complete-collection-/4000-845175/" data-ref-id="4000-845175">Man-Thing by Steve Gerber: The Complete Collection Vol. 3</a> (#3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-champions-1-volume-1/4000-516959/" data-ref-id="4000-516959">Marvel Masterworks: The Champions Volume 1</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/champions-classic-the-complete-collection/4050-111662/">Champions Classic: The Complete Collection</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-black-panther/4050-124689/">Marvel-Verse: Black Panther</a> (#5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/iron-man-epic-collection-duel-of-iron/4050-89265/" data-ref-id="4050-89265">Iron Man Epic Collection: Duel of Iron</a> (#6-7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/eternals-the-dreaming-celestial-saga/4050-133206/">Eternals: The Dreaming Celestial Saga</a> (#6)</li><li><a href="../../west-coast-avengers-assemble-west-coast-avengers-assemble/37-216424/" rel="nofollow ">West Coast Avengers: Assemble</a> (#7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-west-coast-epic-collection-how-the-west-w/4050-113854/">Avengers West Coast Epic Collection: How The West Was Won</a> (#7)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-epic-collection-stark-wars/4050-79615/" data-ref-id="4050-79615">Iron Man Epic Collection: Stark Wars</a> (#9)</li><li><a href="/iron-man-epic-collection-doom/4050-108102/" data-ref-id="4050-108102">Iron Man Epic Collection: Doom</a> (#10-11)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/iron-man-epic-collection-war-machine/4050-126294/">Iron Man Epic Collection: War Machine</a> (#12-13)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-assault-on-armor-city/4050-126603/">Avengers: Assault On Armor City</a> (#13 (Main Story))</li></ul>', '1970', '15', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2186050-01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2909', 'Marvel Comics Super Special', NULL, '31', '<p>In 1977 <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a> began publishing a full-color magazine series devoted to concepts thought to be deserving of special treatment, such as <a href="/kiss/4060-45153/" data-ref-id="4060-45153"> Kiss</a>'' first comics appearance as headliners, new stories of Conan, <a href="/starlord/4005-10957/" data-ref-id="4005-10957"> Star-Lord</a> and <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/weirdworld/4020-61290/" data-ref-id="4020-61290">Weirdworld</a>, and occasional movie adaptations. With issue #14 however, the magazine became an irregularly published vehicle for comics versions of new films. The series lasted 41 issues.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-savage-sword-of-conan-the-original-marvel-year/4000-726224/" data-ref-id="4000-726224">Savage Sword of Conan: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-savage-sword-of-conan-the-original-marvel-year/4000-775032/" data-ref-id="4000-775032">Savage Sword of Conan: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus Volume 3</a> (#9)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/muppet-babies-omnibus/4050-104803/" data-ref-id="4050-104803">Muppet Babies Omnibus</a> (#32)</li></ul>', '1977', '41', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15258-2909-17010-1-marvel-comics-super-.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2910', 'Ms. Marvel', 'This Woman, This Warrior!', '31', '<p>Ms. Marvel''s first ongoing series. It follows the adventures of <a href="/carol-danvers/4005-21561/" data-ref-id="4005-21561">Carol Danvers</a> after she gained superpowers and became a superhero. With issue 20, she changed costumes into the one that was most famous during the 2000''s. The series was cancelled with issue 23 in the middle of a story-line. Years later however, <a href="/marvel-super-heroes/4050-4404/" data-ref-id="4050-4404"> Marvel Super-Heroes</a> issue 10 and 11 printed the (already finished) stories intended for issues 24 and 25 and its covers. This included the first appearance (supposedly) of the X-Man <a href="/rogue/4005-1446/" data-ref-id="4005-1446">Rogue</a>.</p><figure data-ref-id="1300-4429427" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/11121/111219164/4429427-mms25.jpg" data-size="small" data-align="right" data-ratio="1.6641025641026" data-width="780" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 780px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:166.4%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/11121/111219164/4429427-mms25.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4429427"><img alt="Ms. Marvel 25" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/11121/111219164/4429427-mms25.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/11121/111219164/4429427-mms25.jpg 780w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11121/111219164/4429427-mms25.jpg 576w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/11121/111219164/4429427-mms25.jpg 384w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" data-width="384"></a><figcaption>Ms. Marvel 25</figcaption></figure><figure data-align="left" data-img-src="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/10/109227/2861926-msmarvelvol124.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2861926" data-size="small" data-ratio="1.494623655914" data-width="372" data-embed-type="image" style="width: 372px"><a class="fluid-height" style="padding-bottom:149.5%" href="https://static.comicvine.com/uploads/original/10/109227/2861926-msmarvelvol124.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-2861926"><img alt=" Ms. Marvel 24" src="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/10/109227/2861926-msmarvelvol124.jpg" srcset="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/10/109227/2861926-msmarvelvol124.jpg 372w, https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_small/10/109227/2861926-msmarvelvol124.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" data-width="320"></a><figcaption> Ms. Marvel 24</figcaption></figure><h2>Collected Editions</h2><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Marvel Masterworks</th><th scope="col">Epic Collection</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-masterworks-ms-marvel-1-volume-1/4000-468301/" data-ref-id="4000-468301">Vol. 1</a></td><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ms-marvel-epic-collection-this-woman-this-warrior/4050-116378/">This Woman, This Warrior</a></td><td>1-14</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-ms-marvel-2-volume-2/4000-539244/" data-ref-id="4000-539244">Vol. 2</a></td><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ms-marvel-epic-collection-the-woman-who-fell-to-ea/4050-118662/">The Woman Who Fell to Earth</a></td><td>15-23</td></tr></tbody></table><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Omnibuses</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="/essential-ms-marvel/4050-26106/" data-ref-id="4050-26106">Essential Ms. Marvel</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-ms-marvel-a-hero-is-born/4050-117049/">Ms. Marvel: A Hero Is Born</a></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Also:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvels-captain-marvel-prelude/4050-116977/">Marvel''s Captain Marvel Prelude</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-starforce/4050-119136/">Captain Marvel: Starforce</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-the-many-lives-of-carol-danvers/4050-129471/">Captain Marvel: The Many Lives of Carol Danvers</a> (#1 &amp; 19)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/guardians-of-the-galaxy-tomorrows-heroes-omnibus/4050-116248/">Guardians of the Galaxy: Tomorrow''s Heroes Omnibus</a> (#23)</li></ul>', '1977', '23', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15354-2910-17111-1-ms-marvel.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2911', 'Rampaging Hulk', 'The Krylorian Conspiracy', '31', '<p><b>THE RAMPAGING HULK</b> was a black-and-white comic magazine Marvel produced with the intent that the stories presented within would bridge the gap between the sixth and final issue the the Hulk''s first series, and his later serial in <b>TALES TO ASTONISH</b>. However, so many inconsistencies were apparent in the stories that they were later written off as a fictional entertainment produced by the alien Bereet.</p><p>With issue #10, the magazine was re-titled, "<b>HULK!</b>", and presented color tales somewhat closer in scope to the then-popular "Incredible Hulk" TV series.</p><p>Continues into <a href="/hulk/4050-2954/" data-ref-id="4050-2954"> Hulk!</a> #10</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li>Reprinted in <a href="/essential-rampaging-hulk-1-volume-one/4000-473268/" data-ref-id="4000-473268">Essential Rampaging Hulk #1 - Volume One</a></li></ul>', '1977', '9', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15359-2911-17116-1-rampaging-hulk.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2914', 'Star Wars', 'Star Wars', '31', '<p>A long time ago...</p><p>The original Star Wars comic book series, published by Marvel Comics from 1977-1986. The series started as an official adaption, but build on the legacy after the original film''s ending.</p><h4>Star Wars Annuals</h4><ul><li><a href="/star-wars-annual-1-the-long-hunt/4000-19083/" data-ref-id="4000-19083">Star Wars Annual #1</a></li><li><a href="/star-wars-annual-2-shadeshine/4000-21789/" data-ref-id="4000-21789">Star Wars Annual #2</a></li><li><a href="/star-wars-annual-3-the-apprentice/4000-22721/" data-ref-id="4000-22721">Star Wars Annual #3</a></li></ul><h4>Trade Paperback Collections</h4><ul><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-doomworld/4000-307855/" data-ref-id="4000-307855">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 1</a> (#1-20)</li><li><a href="/journey-to-star-wars-the-force-awakens-shattered-e/4050-86107/" data-ref-id="4050-86107">Journey to Star Wars: The Force Awakens - Shattered Empire</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-legends-epic-collection-the-original-mar/4000-555541/" data-ref-id="4000-555541">Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years Volume 1</a> (#1-23)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-the-original-trilogy-the-movie-adaptatio/4050-124292/">Star Wars: The Original Trilogy: The Movie Adaptations</a> (#1-6 &amp; 39-44)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-legends-forever-crimson/4050-124457/">Star Wars Legends: Forever Crimson</a> (#16, 27, 29, 50 &amp; 108)</li><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-dark-encounters/4000-307856/" data-ref-id="4000-307856">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 2</a> (#21-38)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-legends-epic-collection-the-original-mar/4000-608258/" data-ref-id="4000-608258">Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years Volume 2</a> (#24-38)</li><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-resurrection-of-evil/4000-307857/" data-ref-id="4000-307857">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 3</a> (#39-53)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-legends-epic-collection-the-original-mar/4000-677297/" data-ref-id="4000-677297">Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years Volume 3</a> (#39-55)</li><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-screams-in-the-void/4000-307858/" data-ref-id="4000-307858">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 4</a> (#54-67)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-legends-epic-collection-the-original-mar/4000-715320/" data-ref-id="4000-715320">Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years Volume 4</a> (#56-73)</li><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-fools-bounty/4000-307859/" data-ref-id="4000-307859">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 5</a> (#68-81)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-legends-epic-collection-the-original-mar/4000-878330/" data-ref-id="4000-878330">Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years Volume 5</a> (#74-88)</li><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-wookie-world/4000-307860/" data-ref-id="4000-307860">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 6</a> (#82-95)</li><li><a href="/classic-star-wars-a-long-time-ago-far-far-away/4000-307861/" data-ref-id="4000-307861">Classic Star Wars: A Long Time Ago... volume 7</a> (#96-107)</li></ul><h4>Omnibus Trade Paperback Collections</h4><ul><li><a href="/star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-volume-1/4000-249857/" data-ref-id="4000-249857">Star Wars Omnibus: A Long Time Ago volume 1</a> (#1-27)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-volume-2/4000-266311/" data-ref-id="4000-266311">Star Wars Omnibus: A Long Time Ago volume 2</a> (#28-49)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-/4000-315906/" data-ref-id="4000-315906">Star Wars Omnibus: A Long Time Ago volume 3</a> (#50-67)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-/4000-315907/" data-ref-id="4000-315907">Star Wars Omnibus: A Long Time Ago volume 4</a> (#68-85)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-omnibus-a-long-time-ago-/4000-315908/" data-ref-id="4000-315908">Star Wars Omnibus: A Long Time Ago volume 5</a> (#86-107)</li></ul><h4>Hardcover Collections</h4><ul><li><a href="/star-wars-episode-iv-a-new-hope/4050-81835/" data-ref-id="4050-81835">Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope</a> (#1-6)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-the-original-marvel-years-1-volume-1/4000-476260/" data-ref-id="4000-476260">Star Wars: The Original Marvel Years Volume 1</a> (#1-44, and Annual #1)</li><li><a href="/star-wars-episode-v-the-empire-strikes-back/4050-83841/" data-ref-id="4050-83841">Star Wars: Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back</a> (#39-44)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/star-wars-the-original-marvel-years-2-volume-2/4000-490891/" data-ref-id="4000-490891">Star Wars: The Original Marvel Years Volume 2</a> (#45-78, and Annual #2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-the-original-marvel-years-3-volume-3/4000-502136/" data-ref-id="4000-502136">Star Wars: The Original Marvel Years Volume 3</a> (#79-107, Annual #3, <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-return-of-the-jedi/4050-3243/" data-ref-id="4050-3243">Star Wars: Return of the Jedi #1-4</a>, and bonus material)</li></ul>', '1977', '108', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15811-2914-17616-1-star-wars.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2918', 'What If?', 'What if Spider-Man joined the Fantastic Four?', '31', '<p><em>What If?</em> is a series that shows what would have happened if things had turned out differently during many of the famous Marvel stories. Of note is issues #4 and #9 of this volume are considered canon.</p><p>Continued in <a href="/what-if/4050-4249/" data-ref-id="4050-4249">What If...?</a> Vol. 2 (1989)</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/what-if-classic-1-volume-1/4000-175521/" data-ref-id="4000-175521">What If? Classic #1</a> (#1-6)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-the-complete-collection-1-vol-1/4000-697649/" data-ref-id="4000-697649">What If? Classic: The Complete Collection Vol. 1</a> (#1-12)</li><li><a href="/what-if-the-original-marvel-series-omnibus-1-volum/4000-883326/" data-ref-id="4000-883326">What If?: The Original Marvel Series Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#1-15 &amp; 17-22)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-the-legacy-of-captain-america/4050-40166/">Captain America: The Legacy of Captain America</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-2-volume-2/4000-175572/" data-ref-id="4000-175572">What If? Classic #2</a> (#7-12)</li><li><a href="/agents-of-atlas-the-complete-collection-1-vol-1/4000-668768/" data-ref-id="4000-668768">Agents of Atlas: The Complete Collection Vol. 1</a> (#9)</li><li><a href="/kingsize-kirby/4050-83141/" data-ref-id="4050-83141">King-Size Kirby</a> (#11)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-the-complete-collection-2-vol-2/4000-725270/" data-ref-id="4000-725270">What If? Classic: The Complete Collection Vol. 2</a> (#13-15 &amp; 17-23)</li><li><a href="/conan-the-barbarian-the-original-marvel-years-omni/4000-803673/" data-ref-id="4000-803673">Conan the Barbarian: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus Volume 4</a> (#13)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-3-volume-3/4000-175593/" data-ref-id="4000-175593">What If? Classic #3</a> (#14-15, #17-20)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/shang-chi-master-of-kung-fu-omnibus-3-volume-3/4000-583726/" data-ref-id="4000-583726">Shang-Chi Master of Kung-Fu Omnibus Volume 3</a> (#16)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-doctor-strange-8-volume-8/4000-594966/" data-ref-id="4000-594966">Marvel Masterworks: Doctor Strange Volume 8</a> (#18)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-4-volume-4/4000-175729/" data-ref-id="4000-175729">What If? Classic #4</a> (#21-26)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hulk-heart-of-the-atom/4050-50267/" data-ref-id="4050-50267">Hulk: Heart of the Atom</a> (#23)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-the-complete-collection-3-vol-3/4000-735592/" data-ref-id="4000-735592">What If? Classic: The Complete Collection Vol. 3</a> (#24-35)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-5-volume-5/4000-185211/" data-ref-id="4000-185211">What If? Classic #5</a> (#27-32)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-6-volume-6/4000-192526/" data-ref-id="4000-192526">What If? Classic #6</a> (#33-38)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-the-complete-collection-4-vol-4/4000-755773/" data-ref-id="4000-755773">What If? Classic: The Complete Collection Vol. 4</a> (#36-47)</li><li><a href="/conan-the-barbarian-the-original-marvel-years-omni/4000-832905/" data-ref-id="4000-832905">Conan the Barbarian: The Original Marvel Years Omnibus Volume 5</a> (#39)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-fantastic-four-22-volume-22/4000-791981/" data-ref-id="4000-791981">Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Volume 22</a> (#36)</li><li><a href="/what-if-classic-7-volume-7/4000-261667/" data-ref-id="4000-261667">What If? Classic #7</a> (#40-42, #44-47, and material from #43)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-vs-hulk/4050-104825/" data-ref-id="4050-104825">Thor vs. Hulk</a> (#45)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/capitan-america-patriota/4050-103983/">Capitán América: Patriota</a> (#4) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kingsize-kirby/4050-104017/" data-ref-id="4050-104017">King-Size Kirby</a> (#11) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/best-of-marvel-essentials-daredevil-de-frank-mille/4000-285306/" data-ref-id="4000-285306">Best of Marvel Essentials: Daredevil de Frank Millar: Cazadores</a> (#28) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-daredevil-de-frank-miller-y/4050-103297/" data-ref-id="4050-103297">Colección Frank Miller. Daredevil de Frank Miller y Klaus Janson</a> (#28 &amp; #35) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-59-los-4-fantasticos-d/4000-612267/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Los 4 Fantásticos de John Byrne 1</a> (#36) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-57-el-asombroso-spider/4000-612265/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - El Asombroso Spiderman: La era del traje negro</a> (#46) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1977', '47', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/15442-2918-17208-1-what-if-.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2943', 'DC Comics Presents', 'Chase to the End of Time!', '10', '<p>Since the late 1960s Batman has been teaming up with various characters in <em><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-brave-and-the-bold/4050-1683/" data-ref-id="4050-1683">The Brave and the Bold</a></em>. It wasn''t until 1978 that DC Comic''s flagship character Superman was given his own team up book.<em> DC Comics Presents</em> ran for 97 issues with 4 annuals featuring Superman in team up adventures with characters from across the DC Universe. For a brief time it also featured a <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/back-up-story/4015-57009/" data-ref-id="4015-57009">backup</a> series called "<em>Whatever Happened To</em>" which would highlight a Golden Age character that hasn''t been seen for many years. Though this title was abruptly ended with the <a href="/reboot/4015-56620/" data-ref-id="4015-56620">rebooting</a> of Superman, the concept of the Superman team-ups continued briefly in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/action-comics/4050-18005/" data-ref-id="4050-18005"><em>Action Comics</em></a> from issues 584-600.</p><h4>Related Issues</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dc-comics-presents-annual/4050-3114/">DC Comics Presents Annual</a> (#1-4)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/showcase-presents-dc-comics-presents-superman-team/4000-315276/" data-ref-id="4000-315276">Showcase Presents: DC Comics Presents - Superman Team-Ups vol. 1</a> (#1-26)</li><li><a href="/adventures-of-superman-jose-luis-garcia-lopez-1-vo/4000-395904/" data-ref-id="4000-395904">Adventures of Superman: José Luis García-López Volume 1</a> (#1-4, 17)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/supermans-greatest-team-ups/4050-135226/">Superman''s Greatest Team-Ups</a> (#5, 9-10, 12, 14, 19, 28, 30, 35, 38-39, 45, 50, 58, 63, 67, 71 &amp; 97)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/swamp-thing-the-bronze-age-2-volume-two/4000-732690/" data-ref-id="4000-732690">Swamp Thing: The Bronze Age Volume Two</a> (#8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mister-miracle-by-steve-englehart-and-steve-gerber/4050-125642/">Mister Miracle by Steve Englehart and Steve Gerber</a> (#12)</li><li><a href="/black-lightning-2-volume-two/4000-656676/" data-ref-id="4000-656676">Black Lightning Volume 2</a> (#16)</li><li><a href="/justice-league-of-america-the-bronze-age-omnibus-3/4000-867809/" data-ref-id="4000-867809">Justice League of America: The Bronze Age Omnibus Volume 3</a> (#17)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/new-teen-titans-1-volume-one/4000-465827/" data-ref-id="4000-465827">New Teen Titans Volume One</a> (#26)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/showcase-presents-dc-comics-presents-superman-team/4000-419963/" data-ref-id="4000-419963">Showcase Presents: DC Comics Presents - Superman Team-Ups vol. 2</a> (#27-50 &amp; <a href="/dc-comics-presents-annual-1-crisis-on-three-earths/4000-21776/" data-ref-id="4000-21776">Annual #1</a>)</li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/superman-vs-mongul/4050-70058/" data-ref-id="4050-70058">Superman vs. Mongul</a> (#27-28, 36 and 43)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/robin-the-bronze-age-omnibus/4050-127130/">Robin: The Bronze Age Omnibus</a> (#31 &amp; 58)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/superman-vs-shazam/4050-134487/">Superman vs. Shazam!</a> (#33-34 &amp; 49)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-joker-the-bronze-age-omnibus/4050-120647/">The Joker: The Bronze Age Omnibus</a> (#41 &amp; 72)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-doom-patrol-the-bronze-age-omnibus/4050-122961/">The Doom Patrol: The Bronze Age Omnibus</a> (#52)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/adventures-of-superman-by-george-perez/4050-126873/">Adventures of Superman by George Perez</a> (#61)</li><li><a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths-companion-deluxe-edition/4000-691351/" data-ref-id="4000-691351">Crisis On Infinite Earths Companion Deluxe Edition Volume 1</a> (#78)</li><li><a href="/batman-and-the-outsiders-3-volume-3/4000-705406/" data-ref-id="4000-705406">Batman and the Outsiders Volume 3</a> (#83)</li><li><a href="/jack-kirby-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-400381/" data-ref-id="4000-400381">Jack Kirby Omnibus vol. 2</a> (#84)</li><li><a href="/dc-universe-the-stories-of-alan-moore-1-the-storie/4000-119422/" data-ref-id="4000-119422">DC Universe: The Stories of Alan Moore </a>and<a href="/across-the-universe-the-dc-universe-stories-of-ala/4000-136829/" data-ref-id="4000-136829"> Across the Universe: The DC uinverse Stories of Alan Moore</a> (#85)</li><li><a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths-companion-deluxe-edition/4000-708088/" data-ref-id="4000-708088">Crisis On Infinite Earths Companion Deluxe Edition Volume 2</a> (#86)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadman-omnibus/4050-132454/">Deadman Omnibus</a> (#94)</li></ul>', '1978', '97', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/16713-2943-18623-1-dc-comics-presents.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2954', 'Hulk!', NULL, '31', '<p>Continues from <a href="/rampaging-hulk/4050-2911/" data-ref-id="4050-2911"> Rampaging Hulk</a> #9.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li>Reprinted in <a href="/essential-rampaging-hulk-1-volume-one/4000-473268/" data-ref-id="4000-473268">Essential Rampaging Hulk #1 - Volume One</a> (#10-15)</li><li><p>Reprinted in <a href="/essential-rampaging-hulk-2-volume-two/4000-473276/" data-ref-id="4000-473276">Essential Rampaging Hulk #2 - Volume Two</a> (#16-27)</p></li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-65-caballero-luna-1-cu/4000-612301/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Caballero Luna 1: Cuenta atrás hacia la oscuridad</a> (#11-15, #17-18 &amp; #20) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1978', '18', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/16818-2954-18735-1-hulk.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2956', 'Machine Man', 'Machine Man', '31', '<p>Spinning out of the comic-book adaptions of <a href="../../2001-a-space-odyssey/49-2854/" rel="nofollow "> 2001: A Space Odyssey</a>. After Marvel lost the license to publish the series, they brought their own creation, Machine Man, to the Marvel Universe and gave him his own series.</p><p>The first (and longest) series is known for it''s classic Jack Kirby art. The series lasted untill issue 9, but was revived some months later with issue 10 and a new creative team. The series is famous for introducing villain Jack O'' Lantern, as well as the second appearance of Alpha Flight.</p><p>After this series ended with issue 19, Machine Man returned with a <a href="../49-3350/" rel="nofollow "> Machine Man mini-series</a> in 1984 and returned with an ongoing series called <a href="../../x-51/49-11868/" rel="nofollow "> X-51</a>, starring the Machine Man.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kirby-returns/4050-120559/">Kirby Returns!</a> (#1-6)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/alpha-flight-by-john-byrne-omnibus/4050-98560/" data-ref-id="4050-98560">Alpha Flight By John Byrne Omnibus</a> (#18)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/machine-man-by-kirby-ditko-the-complete-collection/4050-92563/" data-ref-id="4050-92563">Machine Man by Kirby &amp; Ditko: The Complete Collection</a></li></ul>', '1978', '19', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/16532-2956-18419-1-machine-man.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2957', 'Nova', 'Heavy Mettle', '31', '<p>Richard Rider is back for all-new adventures as Nova, the Human Rocket! While Nova is not hanging out with the New Warriors, he has his hands full in his own life. The series lasted for a total of 18 issues.</p><p> </p>', '1994', '18', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/77/328692-2957-18970-2-man-called-nova-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2959', 'Power Man and Iron Fist', 'Freedom!', '31', '<p>The long running team-up comic starring Luke Cage and Iron Fist as they fight the thugs from the mean streets of America. It is continued from <a href="/power-man/4050-2700/" data-ref-id="4050-2700"> Power Man</a> #49 and lasted until issue 125.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/power-man-and-iron-fist-epic-collection-heroes-for/4050-83705/" data-ref-id="4050-83705">Power Man and Iron Fist Epic Collection: Heroes For Hire</a> (#50-70)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/power-man-and-iron-fist-epic-collection-revenge/4050-94655/" data-ref-id="4050-94655">Power Man And Iron Fist Epic Collection: Revenge!</a> (#71-72 &amp; 74-89)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/power-man-and-iron-fist-epic-collection-doombringe/4050-122992/">Power Man and Iron Fist Epic Collection: Doombringer</a> (#90-107)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#121) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1978', '76', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/16539-2959-18426-1-power-man-and-iron-f.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2960', 'Spider-Woman', '... A Future Uncertain', '31', '<p><strong>To know her...is to fear her!</strong></p><p>After her debut in <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-spotlight-32-dark-destiny/4000-17194/">Marvel Spotlight issue 32</a>, the mysterious and eerie Spider-Woman stars in her very own ongoing series. The first ongoing series of Spider-woman started in 1978 and lasted until 1983 with a total of 50 issues.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-spider-woman-1-volume-1/4000-505913/" data-ref-id="4000-505913">Marvel Masterworks: Spider-Woman Volume 1</a> (#1-8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-spider-verse-spider-women/4050-130410/">Spider-Man: Spider-Verse - Spider-Women</a> (#1 &amp; 20)</li></ul>', '1978', '50', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3755103-01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2966', 'Gli Eterni', 'Il Ritorno degli Dei', '184', '<br/>', '1978', '29', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/16470-2966-18350-1-eterni-gli.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('2989', 'The Best of DC', 'Superman', '10', '<p><em>The Best of DC</em> Blue Ribbon Digest is just that: <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/reprinted-material/4015-56278/" data-ref-id="4015-56278">reprinting</a> the best storylines from <a href="//www.comicvine.com/batman/4005-1699/" data-ref-id="4005-1699">Batman</a>, <a href="//www.comicvine.com/superman/4005-1807/" data-ref-id="4005-1807">Superman</a>, <a href="//www.comicvine.com/worlds-finest-comics/4050-18006/" data-ref-id="4050-18006">World''s Finest Comics</a>, <a href="/superboy/4050-19154/" data-ref-id="4050-19154">Superboy</a>, <a href="//www.comicvine.com/green-lantern/4015-41148/" data-ref-id="4015-41148">Green Lantern</a>, The Flash <a href="//www.comicvine.com/barry-allen/4005-22804/" data-ref-id="4005-22804">Barry Allen</a> and featuring the Secret Origin of Super-Villains, the <a href="/justice-society-of-america/4060-27589/" data-ref-id="4060-27589">Justice Society of America</a>, <a href="//www.comicvine.com/legion-of-super-heroes/4060-19241/" data-ref-id="4060-19241">Legion of Super-Heroes</a>, <a href="//www.comicvine.com/teen-titans/4060-19081/" data-ref-id="4060-19081">Teen Titans</a> and other characters.</p><p>The digests, similar to <a href="//www.comicvine.com/archie-comics/4010-101/" data-ref-id="4010-101">Archie Comics</a> digests, were published at a time before graphic novels and trade paperbacks, when publisherIds like <a href="//www.comicvine.com/dc-comics/4010-10/" data-ref-id="4010-10">DC Comics</a> and <a href="//www.comicvine.com/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a> reprinted material in comic book pages. DC''s 100 Page Comics featured 10 - 12 pages of original stories and the rest were reprint material. Case in point <em><a href="/the-best-of-dc-9-batman/4000-20935/" data-ref-id="4000-20935">The Best of DC #9</a></em>, collecting the <em><a href="/detective-comics/4050-18058/" data-ref-id="4050-18058">Detective Comics</a></em> "<em><a href="//www.comicvine.com/bat-murderer/4045-57688/" data-ref-id="4045-57688">Bat Murderer</a></em>" storyline. Each segment is roughly 12-pages long. Combining that with a 1969 reprint from <em><a href="//www.comicvine.com/batman/4050-796/" data-ref-id="4050-796">Batman</a></em>, and a layout of the <a href="/wayne-foundation-building/4020-58159/" data-ref-id="4020-58159">Wayne Foundation Building</a>, what you have is a 100 page digest for under a dollar!</p><p>After 71 issues, the series ended in 1986.</p>', '1979', '71', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/17662-2989-19747-1-best-of-dc-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3001', 'Amazing Adventures', 'X-Men - A Man Called X', '31', '<p><strong> Amazing Adventures Volume 3</strong></p><p>A series reprinting the first few X-Men tales.</p>', '1979', '14', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/1985253-01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3002', 'Battlestar Galactica', 'Battlestar Galactica', '31', NULL, '1979', '23', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4085418-bg1nm92m084.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3003', 'Fantasy Masterpieces', 'The Origin of the Silver Surfer!', '31', '<p>Fantasy Masterpieces Volume 2 are reprints of <a data-ref-id="4050-2411" href="/the-silver-surfer/4050-2411/" slug="the-silver-surfer"> Silver Surfer Volume 1</a> #1-14. The first eleven issues are not complete reprints. Issues #1-7 are missing four pages each and issues #8-11 are missing two. Issues #12-14 are complete. These reprints are presented by <a data-ref-id="4040-40467" href="/stan-lee/4040-40467/" slug="stan-lee"> Stan Lee</a> and <a data-ref-id="4040-3800" href="/john-buscema/4040-3800/" slug="john-buscema"> John Buscema</a>. <br/><br/>Beginning at issue #8, the volume reprints <a data-ref-id="4005-6805" href="/adam-warlock/4005-6805/" slug="adam-warlock"> Adam Warlock</a> stories from <a data-ref-id="4050-18066" href="/strange-tales/4050-18066/" slug="strange-tales"> Strange Tales</a> and <a data-ref-id="4050-2583" href="/warlock/4050-2583/" slug="warlock"> Warlock</a>.<br/><br/>Complete reproductions can be found in the <a data-ref-id="4050-3851" href="/marvel-masterworks/4050-3851/" slug="marvel-masterworks"> Marvel Masterworks</a> hardcovers or in the <a data-ref-id="4050-26431" href="/essential-silver-surfer/4050-26431/" slug="essential-silver-surfer"> Essential Silver Surfer</a> TPB.<br/></p>', '1979', '14', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/50784-3003-66593-1-fantasy-masterpieces.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3004', 'Fun and Games Magazine', NULL, '31', '<p>Marvel''s very own puzzle magazine. "All you need is a pencil".  It featured Marvel heroes in puzzles.  The only original character introduced was Cross Wordo.</p>', '1979', '13', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/50798-3004-66607-1-fun-and-games-magazi.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3007', 'Marvel Spotlight', 'The Saturn Storm!', '31', '<p>The short lived second incarnation of the Marvel Spotlight series. Issue #8 features one of the last (if not THE last) appearances of <a href="/captain-marvel/4005-1472/" data-ref-id="4005-1472">Captain Marvel</a> before his death in <a href="/marvel-graphic-novel/4050-3144/" data-ref-id="4050-3144">Marvel Graphic Novel</a> #1: <a href="/marvel-graphic-novel-the-death-of-captain-marvel/4000-21782/" data-ref-id="4000-21782">The Death of Captain Marvel</a>. Issue #12 was supposed to put the spotlight back on Captain Marvel but the series was instead cancelled.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/guardians-of-the-galaxy-solo-classic-omnibus/4050-85759/" data-ref-id="4050-85759">Guardians of the Galaxy Solo Classic Omnibus</a> (#1-2 &amp; 6-7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/drax-guardian-of-the-galaxy/4050-93657/" data-ref-id="4050-93657">Drax: Guardian of the Galaxy</a> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-captain-marvel-6-volume-6/4000-529659/" data-ref-id="4000-529659">Marvel Masterworks: Captain Marvel Vol. 6</a> (#1-4 &amp; 8)</li><li><a href="/captain-marvel-the-death-of-captain-marvel/4050-34102/" data-ref-id="4050-34102">Captain Marvel: The Death of Captain Marvel</a> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/decades-marvel-in-the-70s-legion-of-monsters/4050-118241/">Decades: Marvel In The ''70s - Legion of Monsters</a> (#2 &amp; 5)</li><li><a href="/annihilation-classic/4050-30933/" data-ref-id="4050-30933">Annihilation Classic</a> (#6)</li><li><a href="/starlord-tears-for-heaven/4050-72794/" data-ref-id="4050-72794">Star-Lord: Tears For Heaven</a> (#6-7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-universe-power-unimaginable/4050-25914/">Captain Universe: Power Unimaginable</a> (#9-11)</li></ul>', '1979', '11', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/17571-3007-19647-1-marvel-spotlight.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3008', 'Micronauts', 'Homeworld', '31', '<p data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"><b>The Micronauts Volume 1</b></p><p data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0">The Micronauts series was created by Marvel Comics in a deal with Mego Toys to produce a series of adventures based off their Micronauts toy line. The Mego toys were in fact mostly reproductions of an earlier long running series of Japanese toys called Microman.</p><p data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0">The comic''s inaugural creators were Bill Mantlo and Michael Golden, and they presented The Micronauts as a team of adventurers, exploring a subatomic universe called the Microverse. The series ends with issue #59 and was later revamped as <a href="../../micronauts-the-new-voyages/49-3353/" rel="nofollow "> Micronauts: The New Voyages</a>.</p>', '1979', '59', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4351486-mn1nm92m013.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3009', 'Micronauts Annual', NULL, '31', '<p>Annuals to the Micronauts series.</p>', '1979', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/17891-3009-19995-1-micronauts-annual.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3010', 'Rom', 'Arrival!', '31', '<p>The first (and only) volume of Rom. Although Rom was a Marvel character, and fully integrated into the Marvel Universe, the Hasbro toy company owned the rights to the character (since it was a comic published after a toy they made). The series ended with issue 75, after which Marvel lost the rights to publish Rom. Rom has a devoted fan-base who tries to convince Marvel to buy the rights back to publish a new Rom series. A sequel to this series, the mini-series <a href="../../spaceknights/49-25951/" rel="nofollow ">Spaceknights</a>, was published in 2000.</p>', '1979', '75', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/17893-3010-19997-1-rom.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3011', 'Shogun Warriors', 'Raydeen!', '31', '<p>Inspired by the toy-line of Shogun Warriors licensed by Mattel. Marvel brought these warriors into the Marvel Universe and even had them joined up with the Fantastic Four..</p>', '1979', '20', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/66844-3011-99841-1-shogun-warriors.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3012', 'The Spectacular Spider-Man Annual', 'And Men Shall Call Him Octopus!', '31', '<p>Annual series to the <a href="/the-spectacular-spider-man/4050-2870/" data-ref-id="4050-2870">Spectacular Spider-man</a> series. It lasted from 1979 until 1994.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-amazing-spider-man-19-volum/4000-601796/" data-ref-id="4000-601796">Marvel Masterworks: The Amazing Spider-Man Vol. 19</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-spectacular-spider-man-3-vo/4000-772344/" data-ref-id="4000-772344">Marvel Masterworks: The Spectacular Spider-Man Volume 3</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-spectacular-spider-man-4-vo/4000-907536/" data-ref-id="4000-907536">Marvel Masterworks: The Spectacular Spider-Man Volume 4</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="/the-amazing-spider-man-the-complete-alien-costume-/4000-486880/" data-ref-id="4000-486880">The Amazing Spider-Man: The Complete Alien Costume Saga Book 2</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-the-original-clone-saga/4050-41275/">Spider-Man: The Original Clone Saga</a> (#8)</li><li><a href="/amazing-spiderman-epic-collection-round-robin/4050-80960/" data-ref-id="4050-80960">Amazing Spider-Man Epic Collection: Round Robin</a> (#11)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-vibranium-vendetta/4050-126605/">Spider-Man: Vibranium Vendetta</a> (#11 (Main Story))</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/spider-man-the-new-warriors-the-hero-killers/4050-46628/" data-ref-id="4050-46628">Spider-Man &amp; the New Warriors: The Hero Killers</a> (#12)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-74-peter-parker-el-esp/4000-612311/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Peter Parker, El Espectacular Spiderman: Punto de ruptura</a> (#4-5) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-80-peter-parker-el-esp/4000-612318/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Peter Parker, El Espectacular Spiderman: La Caza de la Araña</a> (#6) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-58-el-asombroso-spider/4000-612266/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - El Asombroso Spiderman: La identidad del Duende</a> (#7) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1979', '14', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2430746-spectacularspider_manannual01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3032', 'DC Special Blue Ribbon Digest', 'Legion of Super-Heores', '10', NULL, '1980', '24', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18061-3032-20211-1-dc-special-blue-ribb.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3033', 'The Legion of Super-Heroes', 'Psycho War', '10', '<p>Starring: <a href="/legion-of-super-heroes/4060-19241/" data-ref-id="4060-19241">The Legion of Super-Heroes</a>.</p><p>Continued from: <em><a href="/superboy-and-the-legion-of-super-heroes/4050-2894/" data-ref-id="4050-2894">Superboy and the Legion of Super-Heroes</a></em> (231-258).</p><p>Continued in: <em><a href="/tales-of-the-legion-of-super-heroes/4050-20776/" data-ref-id="4050-20776">Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes</a></em> (314-354).</p><p>Annuals: <a href="/legion-of-super-heroes-annual/4050-3116/" data-ref-id="4050-3116"><em>Legion of Super-Heroes Annual</em></a> (1-3).</p><p>After a decade of playing second fiddle to Superboy in "<em>Superboy and the Legion of Super-Heroes</em>", the Legion finally made a grab for the title''s marquee when the boy of steel left the 30th Century. In this seminal issue, penned by Gerry Conway and drawn by Joe Staton, Superboy was confronted with a vision of the death of his adoptive parents when he battled with the misguided Rejis Thomak. As he set off for Smallville, Saturn Girl used her telepathic powers to insure that Superboy would stay in the past and therefore never have to confront a similar vision about his parents'' fate when he returned to the future.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/legion-of-super-heroes-before-the-darkness-1-volum/4000-827114/" data-ref-id="4000-827114">Legion of Super-Heroes: Before the Darkness Volume One</a> (#260-271)</li><li><a href="/legion-of-super-heroes-the-curse-the-deluxe-editio/4050-76859/" data-ref-id="4050-76859">Legion of Super-Heroes: The Curse - The Deluxe Edition</a> (#297-313)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dc-through-the-80s-the-experiments/4050-137001/">DC Through the 80''s: The Experiments</a> (#298)</li></ul>', '1980', '55', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/17941-3033-20075-1-legion-of-super-hero.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3036', 'The New Teen Titans', 'The NEW Teen Titans', '10', '<h4>Marv Wolfman''s run in order:</h4><ol><li><strong>The New Teen Titans</strong> Vol. 1 (#1-40)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/tales-of-the-teen-titans/4050-3324/" data-ref-id="4050-3324">Tales of the Teen Titans</a> (#41-58)</li><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans/4050-3316/" data-ref-id="4050-3316">The New Teen Titans</a> Vol. 2 (#1-49)</li><li><a href="/the-new-titans/4050-4014/" data-ref-id="4050-4014">The New Titans</a> (#50-130)</li></ol><p>The spin-off was about to surpass the original. The Teen Titans had been a part of DC Comics lore since their debut in the pages of "<a href="/the-brave-and-the-bold/4050-1683/" data-ref-id="4050-1683"><em>The Brave and the Bold</em></a>" in 1964. Originally grouping <a href="/sidekick/4015-45156/" data-ref-id="4015-45156">sidekicks</a> Robin, Kid Flash and Aqualad, the team expanded to include Wonder Girl and then gained <a href="/teen-titans/4050-2279/" data-ref-id="4050-2279">its own ongoing series</a> in 1966, adding other team members along the way. Over the course of the years, the teens popularity began to wane, and after a hiatus and a brief return, the comic was cancelled altogether in 1978 at issue #53. But in that title''s end, writer Marv Wolfman saw the opportunity of a new beginning.</p><p>Joining with artist George Perez, a detailed craftsman known for his ability to seemingly effortlessly render large casts of characters, Wolfman relaunched the famous team of sidekicks in "The New Teen Titans." With a mix of familiar heroes like Robin, Wonder Girl, Kid Flash, the Doom Patrol''s Beast Boy (now called Changeling), and a few intriguing new faces including the beautiful princess Starfire, the mysterious empath Raven and the half - machine hero Cyborg, "The New Teen Titans" attracted scores of new readers, in no small part due to the quality of the work put into the title.</p><p>Wolfman seamlessly blended action and characterization, creating a cast of varied yet easily identifiable team mates, and the New Teen Titans soon climbed to new heights of popularity, scaling right past their mentors in the Justice League to become one of DC''s best selling titles of the day. Readers found themselves not only picking up the comic to witness the Titans square off against new foes like the demon Trigon and the criminal organization H.I.V.E., they also did so to check in on the relationships of the cast, including the budding romance between Robin and Starfire. With a level of sophistication rarely seen in its era, "<em>The New Teen Titans</em>" ran for 91 standard issues and spun out into a second series that amassed another 130 issues.</p><p>Starting members: <a href="/dick-grayson/4005-1691/" data-ref-id="4005-1691">Robin</a>, <a href="/donna-troy/4005-4913/" data-ref-id="4005-4913">Wonder Girl</a>, <a href="/wally-west/4005-23879/" data-ref-id="4005-23879">Kid Flash</a>, <a href="/cyborg/4005-2388/" data-ref-id="4005-2388">Cyborg</a>, <a href="/starfire/4005-2389/" data-ref-id="4005-2389">Starfire</a> (II), <a href="/beast-boy/4005-3586/" data-ref-id="4005-3586">Beast Boy</a> and <a href="/raven/4005-3584/" data-ref-id="4005-3584">Raven</a>.</p><h4>Related Issues</h4><ul><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-annual/4050-3118/" data-ref-id="4050-3118">The New Teen Titans Annual</a> (#1-2)</li></ul><h2>Collected Editions</h2><h3>Actual collections:</h3><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Volumes</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/new-teen-titans-1-volume-one/4000-465827/" data-ref-id="4000-465827">One</a></td><td>1-8</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/new-teen-titans-2-volume-two/4000-484884/" data-ref-id="4000-484884">Two</a></td><td>9-16</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-3-volume-three/4000-500274/" data-ref-id="4000-500274">Three</a></td><td>17-20</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-4-volume-four/4000-511493/" data-ref-id="4000-511493">Four</a></td><td>21-27</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-5-volume-five/4000-541171/" data-ref-id="4000-541171">Five</a></td><td>28-34</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-6-volume-six/4000-580725/" data-ref-id="4000-580725">Six</a></td><td>35-40</td></tr></tbody></table><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Omnibuses</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-299469/" data-ref-id="4000-299469">One</a></td><td>1-20</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-335836/" data-ref-id="4000-335836">Two</a></td><td>21-40</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Both collections continue further and cover the entire Marv Wolfman''s run.</p><h3>Old collections:</h3><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Archives</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-archives-1-volume-1/4000-273552/" data-ref-id="4000-273552">One</a></td><td>1-8</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-archives-2-volume-2/4000-273554/" data-ref-id="4000-273554">Two</a></td><td>9-16</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-archives-3-volume-3/4000-273555/" data-ref-id="4000-273555">Three</a></td><td>17-20</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-archives-4-volume-4/4000-273556/" data-ref-id="4000-273556">Four</a></td><td>21-27</td></tr></tbody></table><ul><li><a href="/new-teen-titans-terra-incognito/4050-43796/" data-ref-id="4050-43796">Terra Incognito</a> (#28-34)</li><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-the-judas-contract/4050-37465/" data-ref-id="4050-37465">The Judas Contract</a> (#39-44)</li></ul><p><strong>Also in:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="/captain-carrot-and-the-final-ark/4050-43746/" data-ref-id="4050-43746">Captain Carrot and the Final Ark</a> (#16)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-and-the-outsiders-1-volume-1/4000-581519/" data-ref-id="4000-581519">Batman and the Outsiders Vol. 1</a> (#37)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tales-of-the-batman-marv-wolfman-1-volume-1/4000-743303/" data-ref-id="4000-743303">Tales of the Batman: Marv Wolfman Vol. 1</a> (#37)</li><li><a href="/new-teen-titans-who-is-donna-troy-tpb/4000-301048/" data-ref-id="4000-301048">The New Teen Titans: Who is Donna Troy?</a> (#38)</li></ul>', '1980', '40', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/2031889-1937032_dc_comics_new_teen_titans_1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3049', 'Epic Illustrated', 'The Answer; Homespun; Aware; For the next 60 seconds; Metamorphosis Odyssey, Chapter I: Aknaton; Lullabye of Bedlam; Elfspire; History of Human Absurdity Part 1; The Victor; Shakti; Convert; Heads; Metamorphosis Odyssey, Chapter II: Za!; Metamorphosis Ody', '31', '<p>Epic was a Marvel Comics magazine that featured groundbreaking artwork and stories that focused on a market for more mature readers. According to the Marvel Bullpen Bulletins from October 1979, the comic was originally supposed to be named "Odyssey", but was renamed after Marvel found out a comic with that name was already being published by another publisherId. It was then renamed Epic instead. The series would become a huge success and was even followed by it''s own Epic imprint some months later. Many of the individual stories contained within have since been published in trade format among many different publisherIds.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><em><a href="/dreadstar/4050-51175/" data-ref-id="4050-51175">Dreadstar</a> </em>Vol 1:<em> <a href="/dreadstar-1-the-metamorphosis-odyssey/4000-350328/" data-ref-id="4000-350328">Metamorphosis Odyssey</a> </em>(#1-9. <a href="/slg-publishing/4010-383/" data-ref-id="4010-383">SLG</a>, 2000) Vol. 2:<em><a href="/dreadstar-2-the-price/4000-350517/" data-ref-id="4000-350517"> The Price</a> </em>(#15. <a href="/slg-publishing/4010-383/" data-ref-id="4010-383">SLG</a> 2000)</li><li><a href="/shiny-beasts/4050-34709/" data-ref-id="4050-34709"><em>Shiny Beasts </em></a>(#2, #4-6, #8, #19, #25, #28-29, #34. <a href="/king-hell/4010-469/" data-ref-id="4010-469">King Hell</a>, 2007)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/weirdworld-the-dragonmaster-of-klarn/4050-120142/">Weirdworld: The Dragonmaster of Klarn</a> (#9 &amp; 11-13)</li><li><a href="/dr-watchstop-adventures-in-time-and-space/4050-49321/" data-ref-id="4050-49321"><em>Dr. Watchstop: Adventures in Time and Space</em></a> (#10,#14,#17,#21,#29, #33-34. <a href="/eclipse/4010-285/" data-ref-id="4010-285">Eclipse</a>, 1989)</li><li><em>At Home With Ricky Geary</em> (#16, #18, #26, #30. <a href="/fantagraphics/4010-309/" data-ref-id="4010-309">Fantagraphics</a>, 1985)</li><li><a href="/generation-zero/4050-78531/" data-ref-id="4050-78531"><em>Generation Zero</em></a> (#17-24. <a href="/dc-comics/4010-10/" data-ref-id="4010-10">DC Comics</a>, 1991)</li><li><em><a href="/fantastic-four-by-john-byrne-omnibus/4050-43976/" data-ref-id="4050-43976">Fantastic Four by John Byrne Omnibus</a>: <a href="/fantastic-four-by-john-byrne-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-435863/" data-ref-id="4000-435863">Volume 2</a></em> (#26-34. <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a>, 2013)</li><li><em>Cobalt-60</em> (#27-31. <a href="/starblaze-graphics/4010-3411/" data-ref-id="4010-3411">Starblaze</a>, 1988)</li><li><a href="/marvel-graphic-novel-2-elric-the-dreaming-city/4000-21788/" data-ref-id="4000-21788">Marvel Graphic Novel #2 - Elric: The Dreaming City</a> (#3-4. <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a>, 1982)</li><li><a href="/the-michael-moorcock-library-3-elric-the-dreaming-/4000-539300/" data-ref-id="4000-539300">The Michael Moorcock Library #3 - Elric: The Dreaming City</a> (#3-4. <a href="/titan-comics/4010-4212/" data-ref-id="4010-4212">Titan Comics</a>, 2016)</li><li><a href="/elric-the-weird-of-the-white-wolf/4050-3708/" data-ref-id="4050-3708">Elric: The Weird of the White Wolf #2-3</a> (#14, <a href="/first/4010-324/" data-ref-id="4010-324">First</a>, 1986)</li><li><a href="/elric-the-weird-of-the-white-wolf/4050-38442/" data-ref-id="4050-38442">Elric: The Weird of the White Wolf</a> (#14, <a href="/first/4010-324/" data-ref-id="4010-324">First</a>, 1990)</li><li><a href="/the-michael-moorcock-library-4-elric-the-weird-of-/4000-566778/" data-ref-id="4000-566778">The Michael Moorcock Library #4 - Elric: The Weird of the White Wolf</a> (#14. <a href="/titan-comics/4010-4212/" data-ref-id="4010-4212">Titan Comics</a>, 2016)</li></ul>', '1980', '34', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18088-3049-20239-1-epic-illustrated.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3052', 'Moon Knight', 'The Macabre Moon Knight', '31', '<p>Moon Knight''s first on-going series. It sets up much of his rogues gallery and delves deeper into Marc Spector and his different personas.</p><p>Continues in the <a href="/moon-knight-fist-of-khonshu/4050-3492/" data-ref-id="4050-3492">Moon Knight: Fist of Khonshu</a> mini-series.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/moon-knight-epic-collection-bad-moon-rising/4050-77333/" data-ref-id="4050-77333">Moon Knight Epic Collection: Bad Moon Rising</a> (#1-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/moon-knight-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-824088/" data-ref-id="4000-824088">Moon Knight Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#1-20)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/moon-knight-reincarnations/4050-101627/" data-ref-id="4050-101627">Moon Knight: Reincarnations</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="/moon-knight-epic-collection-shadows-of-the-moon/4050-85440/" data-ref-id="4050-85440">Moon Knight Epic Collection: Shadows of the Moon</a> (#5-23)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-brother-voodoo-1-volume-1/4000-851632/" data-ref-id="4000-851632">Marvel Masterworks: Brother Voodoo Volume 1</a> (#21)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/moon-knight-epic-collection-final-rest/4050-116075/">Moon Knight Epic Collection: Final Rest</a> (#24-38)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/moon-knight-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-941422/" data-ref-id="4000-941422">Moon Knight Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#21-38)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-65-caballero-luna-1-cu/4000-612301/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Caballero Luna 1: Cuenta atrás hacia la oscuridad</a> (#1-15) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-71-caballero-luna-2-ec/4000-612308/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Caballero Luna 2: Eclipse</a> (#16-38) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issue''s <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-caballero-luna/4050-41948/" data-ref-id="4050-41948">#1-8</a> &amp; <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/100-marvel-tierra-de-sombras-caballero-luna/4050-93162/" data-ref-id="4050-93162">#13</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1980', '38', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/56044/1798878-moon_knight__1980_1st_series__1.jpeg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3053', 'The Savage She-Hulk', 'The She-Hulk Lives', '31', '<p>The series that introduced She-Hulk! It started out as just a female version of the angry-mad Hulk. In later series, She-Hulk got a grip on her mind.</p><h4>Writers</h4><ul><li><a href="/stan-lee/4040-40467/" data-ref-id="4040-40467">Stan Lee</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="/david-anthony-kraft/4040-42922/" data-ref-id="4040-42922">David Anthony Kraft</a> (#2-25)</li></ul><h4>Related Issues:</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/savage-she-hulk-no-1-facsimile-edition/4050-150837/">Savage She-Hulk No. 1 Facsimile Edition</a> (reprints #1)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/essential-savage-she-hulk/4050-56871/" data-ref-id="4050-56871">The Essential Savage She-Hulk</a></li><li><a href="/the-savage-she-hulk-omnibus/4050-148450/" data-ref-id="4050-148450">The Savage She-Hulk Omnibus</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-savage-she-hulk-1-volume-1/4000-612044/" data-ref-id="4000-612044">Marvel Masterworks: The Savage She-Hulk Volume 1</a> (#1-14)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-she-hulk/4050-137620/">Marvel-Verse: She-Hulk</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-the-living-vampire-omnibus/4050-128226/">Morbius the Living Vampire Omnibus</a> (#9-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/morbius-epic-collection-the-end-of-a-living-vampir/4050-136029/">Morbius Epic Collection: The End Of A Living Vampire</a> (#9-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/man-wolf-the-complete-collection/4050-121739/">Man-Wolf: The Complete Collection</a> (#13-14)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-savage-she-hulk-2-volume-2/4000-708135/" data-ref-id="4000-708135">Marvel Masterworks: The Savage She-Hulk Volume 2</a> (#15-25)</li></ul>', '1980', '25', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18037-3053-20177-1-savage-she-hulk-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3070', 'All-Star Squadron', 'The World on Fire!', '10', '<p>"Come with us now to Earth-Two, and the awesome origin of the <a href="/all-star-squadron/4060-41753/" data-ref-id="4060-41753">All-Star Squadron</a>!"</p><p><a href="/roy-thomas/4040-42067/" data-ref-id="4040-42067">Roy Thomas</a>, <a href="/rich-buckler/4040-14053/" data-ref-id="4040-14053">Rich Buckler</a>, <a href="/jerry-ordway/4040-2908/" data-ref-id="4040-2908">Jerry Ordway</a> (credited here as <em>Jeremiah Ordway</em>!) along with editor <a href="/len-wein/4040-41457/" data-ref-id="4040-41457">Len Wein</a>, letterer <a href="/john-costanza/4040-9421/" data-ref-id="4040-9421">John Costanza</a> and colorist <a href="/carl-gafford/4040-7825/" data-ref-id="4040-7825">Carl Gafford</a> begin the wartime adventures of the Golden-Age heroes of the DC Universe. Writer <strong>Roy Thomas</strong> is no stranger to <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/world-war-ii/4015-56025/" data-ref-id="4015-56025">World War II</a>, or wartime comic book super-heroes having come off Marvel''s WWII super-team, <a href="/invaders/4060-25865/" data-ref-id="4060-25865">The Invaders</a>.</p><p>The world of <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/earth-2/4015-56462/" data-ref-id="4015-56462">Earth-2</a> was at war. In a dimension not unlike that of the Justice League on Earth-1, the greatest heroes of the 1940s had banded together to form the Justice Society of America, but even that wasn''t enough to battle the Axis powers plaguing their society. So, at the behest of President Franklin D. Roosevelt, a new, larger team was created to help unite the war torn country. The massive All-Star Squadron was formed, setting up their headquarters in the <a href="/perisphere-and-trylon/4020-56251/" data-ref-id="4020-56251">Perisphere</a> at the heart of New York''s World''s Fair.</p><p>The creative team of writer Roy Thomas and artist Rich Buckler on "All-Star Squadron" offered readers a nostalgic glimpse back in time, albeit through the slightly distorted lens of Earth-2''s history. In this popular series that ran for 67 issues, readers were treated not only to the adventures of the more familiar Justice Society, but also to every other mystery man of the time and dozens of minor heroes from DC''s Golden Age, including the speedster Johnny Quick, the patriotic Liberty Belle, power houses Robotman and Commander Steel, and the 1940s versions of Batman and Robin.</p><p>With Thomas''comprehensive knowledge of the heroes and history of World War II era Americana, the All-Star Squadron was a certifiable hit, even if the Earth-2 shattering events of DC''s tumultuous "<a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths/4050-3441/" data-ref-id="4050-3441"><em>Crisis on Infinite Earths</em></a>" <a href="/mini-series/4015-56281/" data-ref-id="4015-56281">maxi-series</a> of the mid-1980s took a toll on the book''s continuity.</p><p>Click here for the annuals of the <a href="/all-star-squadron-annual/4050-3106/" data-ref-id="4050-3106">All-Star Squadron</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths-companion-deluxe-edition/4000-691351/" data-ref-id="4000-691351">Crisis On Infinite Earths Companion Deluxe Edition Volume 1</a> (#50-60)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/justice-league-of-america-crisis-6-band-6-1981-198/4000-667900/">Justice League of America: Crisis - Band 6: 1981-1982</a> (#14-15) (German)</li></ul>', '1981', '67', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/19233-3070-21477-1-all-star-squadron.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3077', 'Tales of the Green Lantern Corps', 'Challenge!', '10', '<p>Three issue mini-series.</p>', '1981', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18996-3077-21224-1-tales-of-the-green-l.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3082', 'Bizarre Adventures', 'I Got the Yo-Yo... You Got the String', '31', '<p>Continues from <a href="/marvel-preview/4050-2774/" data-ref-id="4050-2774">Marvel Preview</a> #24</p><p>With issue #25, Marvel''s black-and-white showcase magazine <b>MARVEL PREVIEW</b> was re-titled <b>BIZARRE ADVENTURES</b>. Content remained more or less the same, with themes changing every issue. The series continued to feature stories starring new and established Marvel Universe characters (some left over from other canceled series), new stand-alone stories, and adaptions of prose fiction. The final issue, #34, was published in a color comic book format, rather than as a black-and-white magazine.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-widow-epic-collection-the-coldest-war/4050-130989/">Black Widow Epic Collection: The Coldest War</a> (#25)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-el-universo-marvel-segun-fr/4050-105405/">Colección Frank Miller. El Universo Marvel según Frank Miller</a> (#28 &amp; #31) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1981', '10', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18881-3082-21102-1-bizarre-adventures.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3083', 'Dazzler', 'So Bright This Star', '31', '<p>Published from the early to mid 80''s, ''Dazzler'' was an attempt on Marvel Comics'' part to draw a female audience by putting a title on the stands that was half superhero action and part soap opera. Or, at least, that''s what the series was like for most of its first two years. Towards the end of its second year it took a turn towards being more soap opera than superhero book. In the series'' final 5 issues it made a return to superheroics, with Dazzler''s well-known blue costume making it''s first appearance in issue 38.</p><p>Issue 1 of Dazzler was the first ever "Direct Market Only" comic, giving the book a large hype at the time, since a lot of readers whom bought their comics at newsstands, did not manage to get a copy. There was also a graphic novel published named <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-graphic-novel-12-dazzler-the-movie/4000-108265/">Marvel Graphic Novel issue 12: Dazzler the Movie</a>, set between issues 34 and 35 of this series. Years later, a special <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dazzler/4050-33347/">Dazzler</a> one-shot was published, which was an aftermath of the Necrosha-X crossover as well as a special homage to this original series.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-dazzler-1-volume-1/4000-742426/" data-ref-id="4000-742426">Marvel Masterworks: Dazzler Volume 1</a> (#1-13)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-dazzler-2-volume-2/4000-839820/" data-ref-id="4000-839820">Marvel Masterworks: Dazzler Volume 2</a> (#14-25)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#40) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1981', '42', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/4026826-d1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3087', 'Ka-Zar the Savage', 'A New Dawn...A New World!', '31', '<p>Ka-Zar''s second and most critically acclaimed own ongoing comic-book series. This time, the title is officialy named "Ka-Zar the Savage" instead of just Ka-Zar. The series started out in 1981, not 4 years after the first ongoing <a href="../../ka-zar/49-2692/" rel="nofollow "> Ka-Zar</a> series ended, and lasted for 34 issues.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/kazar-savage-dawn/4050-98060/" data-ref-id="4050-98060">Ka-Zar: Savage Dawn</a> (#1-5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ka-zar-the-savage-omnibus/4050-136161/">Ka-Zar the Savage Omnibus</a> (#1-34)</li></ul>', '1981', '34', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18955-3087-21180-1-ka-zar-the-savage.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3088', 'Marvel Super-Heroes', NULL, '2812', '<p>In 1979 <a href="/marvel-uk/4010-2812/" data-ref-id="4010-2812">Marvel UK''s</a> then-longest running weekly title, <a href="/marvel-comic/4050-47378/" data-ref-id="4050-47378">Marvel Comic</a> (originally titled <a href="/the-mighty-world-of-marvel/4050-33875/" data-ref-id="4050-33875">Mighty World of Marvel</a>) came to an end with #352, cover dated 25th July, and was merged into Spider-Man Comic (the second longest running Marvel UK title), while at the same time being relaunched as the monthly title Marvel Super-Heroes, which continued Marvel Comics numbering. In May 1983''s #397, Marvel Super-Heroes was cancelled and merged into The Daredevils.</p><p>Issue''s <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/best-of-marvel-capitan-britania/4050-41906/" data-ref-id="4050-41906">#387-388</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1979', '45', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/77/1564078-uk_msh_353.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3092', 'The Uncanny X-Men', 'Mind Out of Time!', '31', '<p>This is a continuation of <a href="/stan-lee/4040-40467/" data-ref-id="4040-40467">Stan Lee''s</a> and <a href="/jack-kirby/4040-5614/" data-ref-id="4040-5614">Jack Kirby''s</a> original <a href="/x-men/4050-2133/" data-ref-id="4050-2133">The X-Men</a> (Vol. 1). Beginning with issue #114 the descriptive "Uncanny" was added to the cover treatment but it wasn''t until issue #142 that the volume''s official name, via the indicia, was permanently changed to <i>Uncanny X-Men.</i></p><p>The title has had many creative influences over the years, but <a href="/chris-claremont/4040-40468/" data-ref-id="4040-40468"> Chris Claremont</a> was probably the force that drove the title through many of its historic changes, truly bringing it from "the world''s strangest teens" into their new status as a team of mutants fighting in a "world that fears and hates them." During his legendary 15 year run, he gave us characters and stories such as Phoenix/Dark Phoenix, the Hellfire Club, the New Mutants, X-Factor, the Mutant Massacre, Inferno and Jubilee and numerous other historic heroes and events. This epic run ended after editorial disputes in 1991.</p><p>For the Uncanny X-Men Post-<a href="/schism/4045-56404/" data-ref-id="4045-56404">Schism</a>, see <a href="/uncanny-x-men/4050-43785/" data-ref-id="4050-43785"> Uncanny X-Men (Vol. 2)</a>.</p><h4>Writers</h4><h4>Pencillers</h4><ul><li>John Romita, Jr #175–185, 187–197, 199–200, 202–203, 206–211, 287, 300–302, 304, 306–311 (TOT 43)</li><li>John Byrne #108–109, 111–143 (TOT 35)</li><li>Marc Silvestri #218, 220-222, 224-227, 229-230, 232-234, 236, 238-244, 246-247, 249-251, 253-255, 259-261, 273 (TOT 33)</li><li>Greg Land #500–503, 508–511, 515–521, 530–534, 540–544 (TOT 25)</li><li>Joe Madureira #312–313, 316–317, 325–326, 328–330, 332, 334–338, 340–343, 345–348, 350 (TOT 24)</li><li>Salvador Larroca #338, #387–392, #437–443, #487–491 (TOT 19)</li><li>Billy Tan #338, 387–392, 437–443, 487–491 (TOT 19)</li><li>Jim Lee #248, 256–258, 267–277 (TOT 15)</li><li>Alan Davis #213, 215, 444–447, 450–451, 455–459, 462–463 (TOT 15)</li><li>Whilce Portacio #281–286, 289–290, 526–529 (TOT 12)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li>Issues #142-143 are collected in <a href="/x-men-days-of-future-past/4050-34959/" data-ref-id="4050-34959"> X-Men: Days of the Future Past</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/uncanny-x-men-omnibus-3-volume-3/4000-516096/" data-ref-id="4000-516096">Uncanny X-Men Omnibus Volume 3</a> (#154-175)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-starjammers-by-dave-cockrum/4050-122501/">X-Men: Starjammers by Dave Cockrum</a> (#154-158 &amp; 161-167)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-vs-rogue/4050-136150/">Captain Marvel vs. Rogue</a> (#158, 171 &amp; 269)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-the-many-lives-of-carol-danvers/4050-129471/">Captain Marvel: The Many Lives of Carol Danvers</a> (#164)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-renewal/4050-99448/" data-ref-id="4050-99448">New Mutants Epic Collection: Renewal</a> (#167)</li><li>Issues #168-176 are collected in <a href="/uncanny-x-men-from-the-ashes/4050-30242/" data-ref-id="4050-30242"> From the Ashes</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-we-are-the-x-men/4050-35334/">X-Men: We Are the X-Men</a> (#171, 200, 213, 267 &amp; 287)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/decades-marvel-in-the-80s-awesome-evolutions/4050-118846/">Decades: Marvel In The ''80s: Awesome Evolutions</a> (#173)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-uncanny-x-men-10-volume-10/4000-580758/" data-ref-id="4000-580758">Marvel Masterworks: The Uncanny X-Men Volume 10</a> (#176-188)</li><li><a href="/uncanny-x-men-omnibus-4-volume-4/4000-828998/" data-ref-id="4000-828998">Uncanny X-Men Omnibus Volume 4</a> (#176-193)</li><li>Issues #189-198 are collected in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/xmen-epic-collection-the-gift/4050-87522/" data-ref-id="4050-87522">X-men Epic Collection: The Gift</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/xmen-origins-firestar/4050-101006/" data-ref-id="4050-101006">X-Men Origins: Firestar</a> (#193)</li><li><a href="/power-pack-classic-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-739614/" data-ref-id="4000-739614">Power Pack Classic Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#195 &amp; 205)</li><li>Issues #199-209 are collected in <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/x-men-ghosts/4050-62951/" data-ref-id="4050-62951">Ghosts</a></li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-uncanny-x-men-13-volume-13/4000-864577/" data-ref-id="4000-864577">Marvel Masterworks: The Uncanny X-Men Volume 13</a> (#201-209)</li><li>Issues #210-213 are collected in <a href="/x-men-mutant-massacre/4050-31061/" data-ref-id="4050-31061"> Mutant Massacre</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-mutant-massacre-omnibus/4050-115098/">X-Men: Mutant Massacre Omnibus</a> (#210-219)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-mutant-massacre/4050-120422/">X-Men Milestones: Mutant Massacre</a> (#210-214)</li><li>Issues #225-227 are collected in <a href="/fall-of-the-mutants/4045-41745/" data-ref-id="4045-41745"> Fall of the Mutants</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-fall-of-the-mutants/4050-120263/">X-Men Milestones: Fall of the Mutants</a> (#225-227)</li><li><a href="/xmen-inferno-prologue/4050-78660/" data-ref-id="4050-78660">X-Men: Inferno Prologue</a> (#228-238)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-x-tinction-agenda/4050-121589/">X-Men Milestones: X-Tinction Agenda</a> (#235-238 &amp; 270-272)</li><li>Issues #239-243 are collected in <a href="/inferno/4045-41408/" data-ref-id="4045-41408"> Inferno</a></li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/x-men-inferno-1-volume-1/4000-511530/" data-ref-id="4000-511530">X-Men: Inferno Volume 1</a> (#239-240)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-inferno/4050-120966/">X-Men Milestones: Inferno</a> (#239-243)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-inferno-omnibus/4050-134787/">X-Men: Inferno Omnibus</a> (#239-243)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-inferno-2-volume-2/4000-537447/" data-ref-id="4000-537447">X-Men: Inferno Volume 2</a> (#241-243)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-universe-by-rob-liefeld-omnibus/4050-121741/">Marvel Universe By Rob Liefeld Omnibus</a> (#245)</li><li>Issues #248 and 256-258 are collected in <a href="/x-men-visionaries-jim-lee/4050-41090/" data-ref-id="4050-41090"> X-Men Visionaries: Jim Lee</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-epic-collection-dissolution-and-rebirth/4050-120673/">X-Men Epic Collection: Dissolution &amp; Rebirth</a> (#248-267)</li><li><a href="/xmen-legion-shadow-king-rising/4050-107965/" data-ref-id="4050-107965">X-Men: Legion: Shadow King Rising</a> (#253-255 &amp; 278-280)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-xxl-by-jim-lee/4050-121908/">X-Men XXL by Jim Lee</a> (#256-258, 268-269 &amp; 274-277)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/acts-of-vengeance-spider-man-and-the-x-men/4050-136147/">Acts of Vengeance: Spider-Man &amp; The X-Men</a> (#256-258)</li><li>Issues #265-267 are collected in <a href="/gambit-classic/4050-27134/" data-ref-id="4050-27134"> Gambit Classic</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/xmen-origins-gambit/4050-94150/" data-ref-id="4050-94150">X-Men Origins: Gambit</a> (#266-267)</li><li>Issues #268-269 are collected in <a href="/x-men-visionaries-jim-lee/4050-41090/" data-ref-id="4050-41090"> X-Men Visionaries: Jim Lee</a></li><li>Issues #270-272 are collected in <a href="/x-tinction-agenda/4045-42177/" data-ref-id="4045-42177"> X-Tinction Agenda<