ref-id="4000-610299">Colección Extra Superhéroes #20</a> (#372-380) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-extra-superheroes-31/4000-610310/" data-ref-id="4000-610310">Colección Extra Superheroes #31</a> (#388-393) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-deluxe-patrullax/4050-73655/" data-ref-id="4050-73655">Marvel Deluxe. Patrulla-X: Nación X</a> (#515-522) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-deluxe-patrullax-advenimiento/4050-105291/">Marvel Deluxe. Patrulla-X: Advenimiento</a> (#523-525) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-deluxe-jovenes-vengadores-3-la-cruzada-de-l/4000-624553/">Marvel Deluxe: Jóvenes Vengadores - La cruzada de los niños</a> (#526) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-deluxe-patrullax-la-edad-heroica/4050-105290/" data-ref-id="4050-105290">Marvel Deluxe. Patrulla-X: La Edad Heroica</a> (#526-534) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-deluxe-patrullax-miedo-encarnado/4050-105289/">Marvel Deluxe. Patrulla-X: Miedo Encarnado</a> (#534.1-544) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issue''s <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-x-men/4050-42042/" data-ref-id="4050-42042">#228-280</a>, <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/patrulla-x/4050-45578/" data-ref-id="4050-45578">#322-499</a> &amp; <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/patrulla-x/4050-42852/" data-ref-id="4050-42852">#450-544</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1981', '405', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/18838-3092-21057-1-uncanny-x-men-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3105', 'Adventure Comics', 'Fang Gow of China', '10', '<p>Issues 12-31 are indexed in <a href="/new-adventure-comics/4050-18546/" data-ref-id="4050-18546">New Adventure Comics</a>. The series was relaunched decades after its conclusion, with <a href="/adventure-comics/4050-25643/" data-ref-id="4050-25643">Adventure Comics</a> a series featuring the age-old technique of dual-numbering so that although it began it''s own numbering of the series, it also displays the numbering on the cover as if the series were still ongoing from this series started back in ''35.</p><h3>Collected Editions</h3><ul><li><a href="/all-star-comics-archives-volume-1/4000-299160/" data-ref-id="4000-299160">JSA All Stars Archives Vol. 1</a> (#48-52)</li><li><a href="/the-adventures-of-superboy/4050-35819/" data-ref-id="4050-35819">The Adventures of Superboy Vol. 1</a> (#103-121, <a href="/more-fun-comics/4050-19320/" data-ref-id="4050-19320">More Fun Comics</a> #101-107)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/green-arrow-the-golden-age-omnibus-1-volume-1/4000-649704/" data-ref-id="4000-649704">Green Arrow: The Golden Age Omnibus Volume 1</a> (#103-117)</li><li><a href="/showcase-presents-green-arrow/4050-38845/" data-ref-id="4050-38845">Showcase Presents: Green Arrow </a>(#250-266, 268-269)</li><li><a href="/aquaman-archives/4050-23395/" data-ref-id="4050-23395">Aquaman Archives Vol. 1</a> (#260-280, 282)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/superman-tales-from-the-phantom-zone/4050-43665/">Superman: Tales from the Phantom Zone</a> (#283 &amp; 300)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-volume-two/4000-140324/" data-ref-id="4000-140324">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 2</a> (#306-317)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-volume-three/4000-46448/" data-ref-id="4000-46448">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 3</a> (#318-328)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-5-volume-5/4000-46450/" data-ref-id="4000-46450">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 4</a> (#329-339)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-5-volume-5/4000-46450/" data-ref-id="4000-46450">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 5</a> (#340-349)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-volume-six/4000-48146/" data-ref-id="4000-48146">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 6</a> (#350-358)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-volume-seven/4000-48147/" data-ref-id="4000-48147">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 7</a> (#359-367)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-volume-eight/4000-48148/" data-ref-id="4000-48148">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 8</a> (#368-376)</li><li><a href="/the-legion-of-super-heroes-archives-volume-nine/4000-48149/" data-ref-id="4000-48149">Legion of Super-Heroes Archives Vol. 9</a> (#377-380)</li><li><a href="/aquaman-death-of-a-prince/4050-41218/" data-ref-id="4050-41218">Aquaman: Death of a Prince</a> (#435-437, 441-466)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-gods-by-gerry-conway/4050-126349/">New Gods by Gerry Conway</a> (#459-460)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadman-omnibus/4050-132454/">Deadman Omnibus</a> (#459-466)</li></ul><h3>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h3><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/aquaman-anthologie/4050-116277/">Aquaman Anthologie</a> (#174, #260 #269, #444, #452 &amp; #475) (German)</li></ul>', '1938', '472', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/3125/220967-3105-116357-1-adventure-comics.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3106', 'All-Star Squadron Annual', 'The Three Faces of Evil!', '10', '<p>Annuals for the series <em><a href="/all-star-squadron/4050-3070/" data-ref-id="4050-3070">All-Star Squadron</a></em>.</p>', '1982', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/19504-3106-21775-1-all-star-squadron-an.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3109', 'Batman Annual', '1,001 Secrets Of Batman And Robin', '10', '<p>The first <a href="/batman/4050-796/" data-ref-id="4050-796">Batman</a> annual was released in 1961. Originally, despite the name annual, the series often released two comics per calendar year. The first 7 annuals were reprints of select stories from the late 50''s and early 60''s and contained no new stories. There is an 18 year gap between the release of Batman annual 7 and 8.</p><h4>Writers</h4><ul><li>Mike W. Barr #8-9</li><li>Doug Moench #10, 17-21</li><li>Alan Moore #11</li><li>Max Allan Collins #11</li><li>Mike Baron #12</li><li>Robert Greenberger #12</li><li>Christopher Priest #13</li><li>Kevin Dooley #13</li><li>Andrew Helfer #14</li><li>Alan Grant #15-16</li><li>John Wagner #16</li><li>Devin Grayson #22</li><li>Chuck Dixon #23</li><li>John Ostrander #24</li><li>Judd Winick #25</li><li>Jim Starlin #25</li><li>Peter Milligan #26</li><li>Fabian Nicieza #27</li><li>Derek Fridolfs #27</li><li>Dustin Nguyen #27</li><li>Mandy McMurray #27</li><li>David Hine #28</li><li>Paul Tobin #28</li><li>Kyle Higgins #28</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/batman-second-chances/4050-83297/" data-ref-id="4050-83297">Batman: Second Chances</a> (#11)</li><li><a href="/legends-of-the-dark-knight-norm-breyfogle-1-volume/4000-495783/" data-ref-id="4000-495783">Legends of the Dark Knight: Norm Breyfogle Volume 1</a> (#11-12)</li><li><a href="/batman-the-caped-crusader-1-volume-1/4000-679967/" data-ref-id="4000-679967">Batman: The Caped Crusader Volume 1</a> (#12)</li><li><a href="/batman-the-caped-crusader-2-volume-2/4000-700637/" data-ref-id="4000-700637">Batman: The Caped Crusader Volume 2</a> (#13)</li><li><a href="/batman-the-caped-crusader-3-volume-3/4000-719301/" data-ref-id="4000-719301">Batman: The Caped Crusader Volume 3</a> (#14)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-the-caped-crusader-4-volume-4/4000-763258/" data-ref-id="4000-763258">Batman: The Caped Crusader Volume 4</a> (#15)</li><li><a href="/tales-of-the-batman-jh-williams-iii/4050-75714/" data-ref-id="4050-75714">Tales of the Batman: J.H. Williams III</a> (#21)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-arkham-ras-al-ghul/4050-117730/">Batman Arkham: Ra''s Al Ghul</a> (#26)</li></ul>', '1961', '28', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/19859/846090-88302_20071006024323_large.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3113', 'Supergirl', 'A Very Strange and Special Girl!', '10', '<p>Starring: Kara Zor-El / Linda Lee as <a href="/supergirl/4005-2351/" data-ref-id="4005-2351"> Supergirl</a>.</p><p>Note: Indicias indicate issues #1-13 are titled The Daring New Adventures of Supergirl.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/daring-new-adventures-of-supergirl-1-volume-1/4000-539209/" data-ref-id="4000-539209">Daring New Adventures of Supergirl Volume 1</a> (#1-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-doom-patrol-the-bronze-age-omnibus/4050-122961/">The Doom Patrol: The Bronze Age Omnibus</a> (#7-9)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/daring-new-adventures-of-supergirl-2-volume-2/4000-608174/" data-ref-id="4000-608174">Daring New Adventures of Supergirl Volume 2</a> (#13-23)</li></ul>', '1982', '23', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20221-3113-22562-1-daring-new-adventure.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3114', 'DC Comics Presents Annual', 'Crisis on Three Earths!', '10', '<p>Series of annuals for the 1978 <em><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dc-comics-presents/4050-2943/" data-ref-id="4050-2943">DC Comics Presents</a></em> title.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dc-through-the-80s-the-end-of-eras/4050-132564/">DC Through the ''80s: The End of Eras</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/superman-vs-shazam/4050-134487/">Superman vs. Shazam!</a> (#3)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/shazam-anthologie/4050-118885/">Shazam! Anthologie</a> (#3) (German)</li></ul>', '1982', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/19505-3114-21776-1-dc-comics-presents-a.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3116', 'Legion of Super-Heroes Annual', 'Monster In A Little Girl''s Mind!', '10', '<p>Annual series from the 2nd volume of <a href="/legion-of-super-heroes/4050-3033/" data-ref-id="4050-3033">Legion of Super-Heroes</a></p><p>The annual series continues in <a href="/tales-of-the-legion-of-super-heroes-annual/4050-44355/" data-ref-id="4050-44355"><em>Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes Annual</em></a>.</p>', '1982', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/3664/342637-3116-21777-2-the-legion-of-super.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3118', 'The New Teen Titans Annual', 'Final Conflict!', '10', '<p>Annuals for the 1st volume of <em><a href="/the-new-teen-titans/4050-3036/" data-ref-id="4050-3036">The New Teen Titans</a></em>.</p><h4>Publishing History:</h4><ul><li><strong>The New Teen Titans Annual</strong> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="/tales-of-the-teen-titans-annual/4050-3325/" data-ref-id="4050-3325">Tales of the Teen Titans Annual</a> (#3-4)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/new-teen-titans-4-volume-four/4000-511493/" data-ref-id="4000-511493">New Teen Titans Volume Four</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-5-volume-five/4000-541171/" data-ref-id="4000-541171">New Teen Titans Volume Five</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/vigilante-by-marv-wolfman-1-volume-one/4000-591741/" data-ref-id="4000-591741">Vigilante by Marv Wolfman Volume One</a> (#2)</li></ul>', '1982', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/56044/1811321-new_teen_titans__1980__annual_1.jpeg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3125', 'Tales of the New Teen Titans', 'Cyborg', '10', '<p><b>Tales of the New Teen Titans</b></p><p><i>A four-issue miniseries starring</i> <a href="/cyborg/4005-2388/" data-ref-id="4005-2388">Cyborg</a>, <a href="/raven/4005-3584/" data-ref-id="4005-3584">Raven</a>, <a href="/beast-boy/4005-3586/" data-ref-id="4005-3586">Changeling</a>, <i>and</i> <a href="/starfire/4005-2389/" data-ref-id="4005-2389">Starfire</a></p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-new-teen-titans-archives-3-volume-3/4000-273555/" data-ref-id="4000-273555">The New Teen Titans Archives Vol. 3</a></li><li><a href="/new-teen-titans-3-volume-three/4000-500274/" data-ref-id="4000-500274">New Teen Titans Volume Three</a></li><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus/4050-43537/" data-ref-id="4050-43537">The New Teen Titans Omnibus</a> Vol. 2</li></ul>', '1982', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/19908-3125-22213-1-tales-of-the-new-tee.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3138', 'G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero', 'Operation: Lady Doomsday; ...Hot Potato!', '31', '<p><a href="//www.comicvine.com/gi-joe/4060-12206/" data-ref-id="4060-12206">G.I. Joe</a>, the legendary <a href="//www.comicvine.com/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a> series based on the cartoon and action figures-line. It featured many of the most popular G.I.Joe characters and even introduced <a href="/snake-eyes/4050-40244/" data-ref-id="4050-40244">Snake Eyes</a>.</p><p>The series lasted for 155 issues until Marvel lost the rights to publish the series in 1995.</p><p>The series had a concluding re-print special in 1995, simply called <a href="/gi-joe-special/4050-32923/" data-ref-id="4050-32923">G.I. Joe: Special</a>, making that the last G.I. Joe comic to be published by Marvel Comics.</p><p>In 2010, the G.I. Joe series was continued by <a href="//www.comicvine.com/idw-publishing/4010-1190/" data-ref-id="4010-1190">IDW Publishing</a> as <a href="/gi-joe-a-real-american-hero/4050-32910/" data-ref-id="4050-32910">G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero</a>, continuing the numbering and the storyline of this original series. IDW''s series ignored <a href="//www.comicvine.com/image/4010-513/" data-ref-id="4010-513">Image</a>''s <a href="/gi-joe-a-real-american-hero/4050-9112/" data-ref-id="4050-9112">G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero</a> and <a href="//www.comicvine.com/devils-due/4010-1863/" data-ref-id="4010-1863">Devil''s Due</a>''s <a href="/gi-joe-a-real-american-hero/4050-11071/" data-ref-id="4050-11071">G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero</a>.</p><p>Whether the G.I. Joe comics published by various publisherIds in between the cap from 1995 till 2010 are ''in continuity'' remains to be seen.</p><h4><strong>Writers</strong></h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/larry-hama/4040-12272/" data-ref-id="4040-12272">Larry Hama</a> #1-7, 10-19, 21-118, 120-142, 144-152, 155 <strong>(TOT 148)</strong></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/herb-trimpe/4040-3439/" data-ref-id="4040-3439">Herb Trimpe</a> #8, 119,</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/steven-grant/4040-41567/" data-ref-id="4040-41567">Steven Grant</a> #9</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/eric-fern/4040-56536/" data-ref-id="4040-56536">Eric Fein </a>#143</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/peter-quinones/4040-42502/" data-ref-id="4040-42502">Peter Quionones</a> #153,</li></ul><p><strong>Pencillers</strong></p><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/herb-trimpe/4040-3439/" data-ref-id="4040-3439">Herb Trimpe</a> #1, 3, 4, 6-8, 99, 119</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/don-perlin/4040-1539/" data-ref-id="4040-1539">Don Perlin</a> #2, 5</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mike-vosburg/4040-5595/" data-ref-id="4040-5595">Mike Vosburg</a> #9-19, 22, 23</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/geof-isherwood/4040-11627/" data-ref-id="4040-11627">Geoff Isherwood</a> #20, 97</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/larry-hama/4040-12272/" data-ref-id="4040-12272">Larry Hama</a> #21, 26,</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/russ-heath/4040-6102/" data-ref-id="4040-6102">Russ Heath</a> #24</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/frank-springer/4040-30117/" data-ref-id="4040-30117">Frank Springer</a> #25, 27, 29, 30, 32, 33, 37</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marie-severin/4040-3492/" data-ref-id="4040-3492">Marie Severin</a> #28</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/gi-joe-a-real-american-hero-31-all-fall-down/4000-76185/" data-ref-id="4000-76185">Rod Whigham</a> #31, 34-36, 38-58, 78, 116-118</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ron-wagner/4040-6586/" data-ref-id="4040-6586">Ron Wagner</a> #59, 63-68, 70-74, 76, 80, 83</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/todd-mcfarlane/4040-3380/" data-ref-id="4040-3380">Todd McFarlene</a> #60</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marshall-rogers/4040-14894/" data-ref-id="4040-14894">Marshall Rogers</a> #61, 75, 77, 79, 81, 82 (pgs. 1-6), 84, 86</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/arvell-jones/4040-26077/" data-ref-id="4040-26077">Avell Jones</a> #62</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tony-salmons/4040-12240/" data-ref-id="4040-12240">Tony Salmons</a> #69, 87, 88, 91</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/don-hudson/4040-7118/" data-ref-id="4040-7118">Don Hudson</a> #82 (pgs. 7-22)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/paul-ryan/4040-3253/" data-ref-id="4040-3253">Paul Ryan</a> #85</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mark-bright/4040-10294/" data-ref-id="4040-10294">Mark Bright</a> #89, 90, 92-96, 98, 100-106, 108</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/lee-weeks/4040-3252/" data-ref-id="4040-3252">Lee Weeks</a> #107</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/john-statema/4040-2907/" data-ref-id="4040-2907">John Statema</a> #109, 111-115</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/ron-garney/4040-7117/" data-ref-id="4040-7117">Ron Garney</a> #110</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/andrew-wildman/4040-12205/" data-ref-id="4040-12205">Andrew Wildman</a> #120-131, 133-138</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/rurik-tyler/4040-18557/" data-ref-id="4040-18557">Rurik Tyler</a> #132</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/chris-batista/4040-24182/" data-ref-id="4040-24182">Chris Batsta</a> #139, 140</li><li>Steve Lieber #141</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/william-rosado/4040-12203/" data-ref-id="4040-12203">Will Rosado</a> #141, 142, 144, 153</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/jesse-d-orozco/4040-107426/" data-ref-id="4040-107426">Jesse D. Orozco</a> #142, 143</li><li>Bob Sharen #143</li><li>Rick Parker #143</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/phil-gosier/4040-15310/" data-ref-id="4040-15