ref-id="4000-251517">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 7</a> (#61-70)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/g-i-joe-the-complete-collection-7-volume-7/4000-489926/" data-ref-id="4000-489926">G.I. Joe: The Complete Collection vol. 7</a> (#61-67)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-8/4000-251516/" data-ref-id="4000-251516">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 8</a> (#71-80)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-9/4000-251515/" data-ref-id="4000-251515">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 9</a> (#81-90)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-10/4000-251514/" data-ref-id="4000-251514">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 10</a> (#91-100)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-11/4000-270645/" data-ref-id="4000-270645">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 11</a> (#101-110)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-12/4000-284355/" data-ref-id="4000-284355">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 12</a> (#111-123)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-13/4000-318967/" data-ref-id="4000-318967">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 13</a> (#124-134)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-14/4000-325096/" data-ref-id="4000-325096">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 14</a> (#135-145)</li><li><a href="/gi-joe-transformers-volume-1/4000-376445/" data-ref-id="4000-376445">G.I. Joe/Transformers Volume 1</a> (#139-142)</li><li><a href="/classic-gi-joe-vol-15/4000-349635/" data-ref-id="4000-349635">Classic G.I. Joe vol. 15</a> (#146-155)</li></ul>', '1982', '155', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/110017/2665109-g.i._joe___a_real_american_hero_001___00___fc.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3139', 'Hercules', 'What Fools These Immortals Be!', '31', '<p>Hercules'' first solo series and, along with Wolverine, one of the first Marvel mini-series! The series proved so popular that a second mini-series named <a href="/hercules/4050-3344/" data-ref-id="4050-3344">Hercules Prince of Power Vol.2</a> was started a few months later.</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> this is not Earth 616''s Hercules, but rather Earth 829''s Hercules.</p><p>Collected in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/hercules-prince-of-power/4050-43093/">Hercules: Prince of Power</a>.</p>', '1982', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20115-3139-22444-1-hercules.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3143', 'Marvel Fanfare', 'Pin Up; Fast Descent Into Hell; Editori-Al; Snow', '31', '<p>In this series, mostly characters with no own comicbook-series starred in stories with high quality art by the top artists of the industry. It was printed on high quality paper as well. Although the series lasted for 10 years, it only had 60 issues published. Some 4 and a half years later, <a href="https://www.comicvine.com/marvel-fanfare/4050-25660/">Marvel Fanfare Vol.2 </a>was started.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-fanfare-strange-tales/4050-32702/">Marvel Fanfare: Strange Tales</a> (#1-7)</li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-the-fantastic-four-22-volume-22/4000-791981/" data-ref-id="4000-791981">Marvel Masterworks: The Fantastic Four Volume 22</a> (#2)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/black-widow-epic-collection-the-coldest-war/4050-130989/">Black Widow Epic Collection: The Coldest War</a> (#10-13)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/thor-the-warriors-three/4050-43096/">Thor: The Warriors Three</a> (#13 &amp; 34-37)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-universe-by-frank-miller-omnibus/4050-116073/">Marvel Universe by Frank Miller Omnibus</a> (#18)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-shadows-and-light/4050-98729/" data-ref-id="4050-98729">Cloak and Dagger: Shadows and Light</a> (#19)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-omnibus/4050-130070/">Cloak and Dagger Omnibus</a> (#19)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/iron-man-epic-collection-return-of-the-ghost/4050-117588/">Iron Man Epic Collection: Return of the Ghost</a> (#22-23 &amp; 44)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-universe-power-unimaginable/4050-25914/">Captain Universe: Power Unimaginable</a> (#25)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-america-scourge-of-the-underworld/4050-39209/">Captain America: Scourge of the Underworld</a> (#29)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-75-doctor-extrano-de-r/4000-612313/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Doctor Extraño de Roger Stern</a> (#6) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-22-viuda-negra-red-de-/4000-612227/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Viuda Negra: Red de intrigas</a> (#10-13) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-el-universo-marvel-segun-fr/4050-105405/">Colección Frank Miller. El Universo Marvel según Frank Miller</a> (#18) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-74-peter-parker-el-esp/4000-612311/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Peter Parker, El Espectacular Spiderman: Punto de ruptura</a> (#47) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>Issues <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-la-cosa-16/4000-285483/" data-ref-id="4000-285483">#15</a> &amp; <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/biblioteca-marvel-la-cosa-16/4000-285483/" data-ref-id="4000-285483">#20-21</a> have been translated into Spanish.</p>', '1982', '60', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/19728-3143-22013-1-marvel-fanfare.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3144', 'Marvel Graphic Novel', 'Dreadstar', '31', '<p>Marvel Graphic Novels (MGN) was a volume of graphic novel trade paperbacks in an over-sized magazine format that was published from 1982 to 1993, often filled with big stories and introductions of new characters and teams, such as the <a href="/new-mutants/4060-15971/" data-ref-id="4060-15971">New Mutants</a> or <a href="/futurians/4060-43541/" data-ref-id="4060-43541">Futurians</a>. Unfortunately they fell to the wayside in the early ''90s, when the prestige format came around.</p><p>Only the first 20 issues were cataloged as Marvel Graphic Novel #1, #2, #3, etc. After these 20 issues, Marvel continued the volume for another 18 graphic novels officially. <a href="/the-overstreet-comic-book-price-guide/4050-65397/" data-ref-id="4050-65397">The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide</a> began to label them #21-38 as part of the volume, but the titles in the indicia were shown unnumbered, as what the cover stated.</p><p>General listing for the graphic novels that were published after issue #38 from 1988-1993 (adding up to 76 published graphic novels in total):</p><ul><li>39 - <a href="/the-inhumans/4050-37821/" data-ref-id="4050-37821">The Inhumans</a></li><li>40 - <a href="/punisher-assassins-guild/4050-30703/" data-ref-id="4050-30703">The Punisher: Assassin''s Guild</a></li><li>41 - <a href="/who-framed-roger-rabbit/4050-33739/" data-ref-id="4050-33739">Who Framed Roger Rabbit?</a></li><li>42 - <a href="/conan-of-the-isles/4050-37820/" data-ref-id="4050-37820">Conan of the Isles: Red Shadows and Black Kraken!</a></li><li>43 - <a href="/the-dreamwalker/4050-33738/" data-ref-id="4050-33738">The Dreamwalker</a></li><li>44 - <a href="/ax/4050-33731/" data-ref-id="4050-33731">Ax</a></li><li>45 -<a href="/arena/4050-22563/" data-ref-id="4050-22563"> Arena</a></li><li>46 - <a href="/spider-man-parallel-lives/4050-27473/" data-ref-id="4050-27473">Spider-Man: Parallel Lives</a></li><li>47 - <a href="/kull-the-vale-of-shadow/4050-33733/" data-ref-id="4050-33733">Kull: The Vale of Shadow</a></li><li>48 -<a href="/a-sailors-story-book-2/4050-33726/" data-ref-id="4050-33726"> A Sailor''s Story: Book Two - Winds, Dreams, and Dragons</a></li><li>49 - <a href="/doctor-strange-doctor-doom-triumph-and-torment/4050-23227/" data-ref-id="4050-23227">Doctor Strange &amp; Doctor Doom: Triumph and Torment</a></li><li>50 -<a href="/wolverinenick-furythe-scorpio-connection/4050-25998/" data-ref-id="4050-25998"> Wolverine &amp; Nick Fury: The Scorpio Connection</a></li><li>51 -<a href="/the-punisher-intruder/4050-25459/" data-ref-id="4050-25459"> Punisher: Intruder</a></li><li>52 - <a href="/neuromancer/4050-33734/" data-ref-id="4050-33734">Neuromancer: The Graphic Novel</a></li><li>53 - <a href="/conan-the-barbarian-the-skull-of-set/4050-33760/" data-ref-id="4050-33760">Conan: The Skull of Set</a></li><li>54 -<a href="/roger-rabbit-the-resurrection-of-doom/4050-33737/" data-ref-id="4050-33737"> Roger Rabbit: The Resurrection of Doom</a></li><li>55 - <a href="/squadron-supreme-death-of-a-universe/4050-27684/" data-ref-id="4050-27684">Squadron Supreme: Death of a Universe</a></li><li>56 -<a href="/power-pack-cloak-and-dagger-shelter-from-the-storm/4050-33732/" data-ref-id="4050-33732"> Cloak &amp; Dagger and Power Pack: Shelter from the Storm</a></li><li>57 -<a href="/rick-mason-the-agent/4050-33735/" data-ref-id="4050-33735"> Rick Mason: The Agent</a></li><li>58 -<a href="/silver-surfer-the-enslavers/4050-27374/" data-ref-id="4050-27374"> Silver Surfer: The Enslavers</a></li><li>59 -<a href="/conan-the-barbarian-the-horn-of-azoth/4050-30316/" data-ref-id="4050-30316"> Conan the Barbarian: The Horn of Azoth</a></li><li>60 -<a href="/rio-rides-again/4050-33758/" data-ref-id="4050-33758"> Rio Rides Again</a></li><li>61 -<a href="/black-widow-coldest-war/4050-25458/" data-ref-id="4050-25458"> Black Widow: The Coldest War</a></li><li>62 -<a href="/ka-zar-guns-of-the-savage-land/4050-20442/" data-ref-id="4050-20442"> Ka-Zar: Guns of the Savage Land</a></li><li>63 - <a href="/spider-man-spirits-of-the-earth/4050-37819/" data-ref-id="4050-37819">Spider-Man: Spirits of the Earth</a></li><li>64 -<a href="/punisher-kingdom-gone/4050-30714/" data-ref-id="4050-30714"> Punisher: Kingdom Gone</a></li><li>65 - <a href="/wolverine-bloodlust/4050-23816/" data-ref-id="4050-23816">Wolverine: Bloodlust</a></li><li>66 -<a href="/excalibur-weird-war-3/4050-32120/" data-ref-id="4050-32120"> Excalibur: Weird War III</a></li><li>67 -<a href="/wolverine-bloody-choices/4050-32212/" data-ref-id="4050-32212"> Wolverine: Bloody Choices</a></li><li>68 - <a href="/avengers-deathtrap-the-vault/4050-20893/" data-ref-id="4050-20893">Avengers: Death Trap - The Vault</a></li><li>69 - <a href="/conan-the-rogue/4050-33759/" data-ref-id="4050-33759">Conan the Rogue</a></li><li>70 - <a href="/punisher-blood-on-the-moors/4050-27751/" data-ref-id="4050-27751">Punisher: Blood on the Moors</a></li><li>71 -<a href="/the-silver-surfer-homecoming/4050-26865/" data-ref-id="4050-26865"> Silver Surfer: Homecoming</a></li><li>72 - <a href="/spider-man-fear-itself/4050-33873/" data-ref-id="4050-33873">Spider-Man: Fear Itself</a></li><li>73 - <a href="/conan-the-ravagers-out-of-time/4050-35148/" data-ref-id="4050-35148">Conan: The Ravagers Out of Time</a></li><li>74 -<a href="/punisherblack-widow-spinning-doomsdays-web/4050-20443/" data-ref-id="4050-20443"> Punisher &amp; Black Widow: Spinning Doomsday''s Web</a></li><li>75 -<a href="/daredevil-black-widow-abattoir/4050-31673/" data-ref-id="4050-31673"> Daredevil &amp; Black Widow: Abattoir</a></li><li>76 - <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/night-raven-the-collected-stories/4050-20341/">Night Raven: The Collected Stories</a></li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-captain-marvel-6-volume-6/4000-529659/" data-ref-id="4000-529659">Marvel Masterworks: Captain Marvel Vol. 6</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/captain-marvel-by-jim-starlin-the-complete-collect/4050-95814/" data-ref-id="4050-95814">Captain Marvel By Jim Starlin: The Complete Collection</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="/captain-marvel-the-death-of-captain-marvel/4050-34102/" data-ref-id="4050-34102">Captain Marvel: The Death of Captain Marvel</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-thanos-wars-infinity-origin/4050-118000/">The Thanos Wars: Infinity Origin</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-renewal/4050-99448/" data-ref-id="4050-99448">New Mutants Epic Collection: Renewal</a> (#4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/uncanny-x-men-omnibus-3-volume-3/4000-516096/" data-ref-id="4000-516096">Uncanny X-Men Omnibus Volume 3</a> (#5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/killraven-epic-collection-warrior-of-the-worlds/4050-139434/">Killraven Epic Collection: Warrior of the Worlds</a> (#7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-killraven-1-volume-1/4000-685850/" data-ref-id="4000-685850">Marvel Masterworks: Killraven Volume 1</a> (#7)</li><li><a href="/swords-of-the-swashbucklers/4050-109126/" data-ref-id="4050-109126">Swords of the Swashbucklers</a> (#14)</li><li><a href="/marvel-universe-by-john-byrne-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-694138/" data-ref-id="4000-694138">Marvel Universe by John Byrne Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#18)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/sensational-she-hulk-by-john-byrne-omnibus/4050-127668/">Sensational She-Hulk by John Byrne Omnibus</a> (#18)</li><li><a href="/greenberg-the-vampire/4050-84969/" data-ref-id="4050-84969">Greenberg the Vampire</a> (#20)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/daredevilelektra-love-and-war-gallery-edition/4050-130071/">Daredevil/Elektra: Love and War Gallery Edition</a> (#24)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-west-coast-epic-collection-tales-to-aston/4050-130576/">Avengers West Coast Epic Collection: Tales To Astonish</a> (#27)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/fantastic-four-epic-collection-the-more-things-cha/4050-119753/">Fantastic Four Epic Collection: The More Things Change...</a> (#29)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/wolfpack-the-complete-collection/4050-112707/">Wolfpack: The Complete Collection</a> (#31)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/iron-man-epic-collection-return-of-the-ghost/4050-117588/">Iron Man Epic Collection: Return of the Ghost</a> (#33)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-predator-and-prey/4050-112941/">Cloak and Dagger: Predator and Prey</a> (#34)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-78-la-sensacional-hulk/4000-612316/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - La sensacional Hulka de John Byrne</a> (#18) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1982', '38', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/117763/2716684-marvelgraphicnovel01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3147', 'Marvel Super Hero Contest of Champions', 'A Gathering of Heroes', '31', '<p>History in the making! The first ever Marvel Comics Crossover mini-series! The heroes of earth are abducted and forced to fight each-other by the <a href="/grandmaster/4005-32735/" data-ref-id="4005-32735"> Grandmaster</a> and <a href="/death/4005-12620/" data-ref-id="4005-12620"> Death</a>. The series seemed to have laid the groundwork for the <a href="/marvel-super-heroes-secret-wars/4050-3352/" data-ref-id="4050-3352"> Marvel Super Heroes Secret Wars</a> mini-series that would start some years later since there is much resemblance to the two series (both featuring stories in which heroes are taken away from their homes and driven to fight one another by an entity). Years later, a second volume named <a href="/contest-of-champions-ii/4050-6353/" data-ref-id="4050-6353"> Contest of Champions II</a> was published.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/avengers-the-contest/4050-34101/" data-ref-id="4050-34101">Avengers: The Contest</a></li><li><a href="/marvel-super-hero-contest-of-champions/4050-85118/" data-ref-id="4050-85118">Marvel Super Hero Contest of Champions</a></li></ul>', '1982', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/19929-3147-22234-1-marvel-super-hero-co.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3148', 'Rom Annual', 'It Came From Beyond the Stars', '31', '<p>Annual''s to Marvel''s <a data-ref-id="4050-3010" href="/rom/4050-3010/" slug="rom">Rom</a> series.</p>', '1982', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20265-3148-22606-1-rom-annual.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3152', 'Team America', NULL, '31', '<p> .</p>', '1982', '12', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/47894-3152-57310-1-team-america.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3155', 'Vision and the Scarlet Witch', '"Trick Or Treat!"', '31', '<p>Four issue mini-series.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/avengers-vision-and-the-scarlet-witch/4050-32246/" data-ref-id="4050-32246">Avengers: Vision and the Scarlet Witch</a></li><li><a href="/marvel-masterworks-avengers-21-volume-21/4000-882696/" data-ref-id="4000-882696">Marvel Masterworks: Avengers Volume 21</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/vision-and-the-scarlet-witch-the-saga-of-wanda-and/4050-133210/">Vision &amp; The Scarlet Witch: The Saga of Wanda and Vision</a></li></ul>', '1982', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20271-3155-22612-1-vision-and-the-scarl.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3156', 'Warlock', NULL, '31', '<p>This volume reprints the classic Warlock tales by writer/artist Jim Starlin originally printed in Strange Tales #178-181, Warlock(vol.1) #9-15, Marvel Team-Up #55, Avengers Annual #7, and Marvel Two-in-One Annual #2</p>', '1982', '6', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20349-3156-22697-1-warlock.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3157', 'Wolverine', 'I''m Wolverine', '31', '<p>He is the best at what he does, and here he is in his first own mini-series!</p><p>By the creative minds of Chris Claremont and Frank Miller comes a four-issue miniseries, starring <a href="/wolverine/4005-1440/" data-ref-id="4005-1440">Wolverine</a> in his first solo series!</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-universe-by-frank-miller-omnibus/4050-116073/">Marvel Universe by Frank Miller Omnibus</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/uncanny-x-men-omnibus-3-volume-3/4000-516096/" data-ref-id="4000-516096">Uncanny X-Men Omnibus Volume 3</a></li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/wolverine-1-chris-claremont-frank-miller/4000-184081/" data-ref-id="4000-184081">Wolverine Volume 1</a> (#1-4), (Uncanny X-Men #172-173)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/best-of-marvel-essentials-lobezno-honor/4050-41923/" data-ref-id="4050-41923">Best of Marvel Essentials: Lobezno: Honor</a> (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccion-frank-miller-lobezno-honor/4050-103302/" data-ref-id="4050-103302">Colección Frank Miller. Lobezno: Honor</a> (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1982', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11161/111615891/9300027-3983472080-30841.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3194', 'Batman and the Outsiders', 'Preview', '10', '<p>Continued in: <a href="/outsiders-1985/4050-3455/" data-ref-id="4050-3455">Outsiders (Volume 1)</a>.</p><p>Batman had never been what anyone would call a natural team player. True, he had been Robin''s mentor since early in his career, but he''d often had trouble meshing with those he considered equals in the JLA. So, when his long time team mates in the Justice League refused to enter the country of Markovia to help Batman rescue Bruce Wayne''s longtime employee Lucius Fox, Batman abruptly quit the League and set out for the small European country on his own. Batman soon discovered Fox had been kidnapped by Baron Bedlam, a rebel who had already killed the king of Markovia. As he tries to find where Fox is located, Batman enlists the aid of his long time friend, Black Lightning in order to infiltrate a camp of rebel insurgents in the country. However, soon the samurai assassin Katana appeared and killed the rebel general and Batman''s plans took a different turn. Before long he encountered the mysterious energy projecting Halo, the gravity powered prince of Markovia now calling himself Geo-Force, and his old associate and master of the periodic table of the elements, Metamorpho, who all opposed the forces of Baron Bedlam, and a new plan formed in Batman''s mind. After successfully overthrowing Bedlam''s reign of terror, and saving Fox, Batman requested that the team return to Gotham with him and work under his leadership. Batman now had his own league of heroes, only his team would now operate outside the law.</p><p>Popular from its inception, Batman and the Outsiders (Outsiders) ran for a total of 46 issues, and spun off into a deluxe format Baxter title, The Outsiders in 1985. An interesting blend of old and new characters, the team''s roster continued to grow over the years, gaining members such as Looker, Windfall and the Atomic Knight and facing villains like Eclipso, Kobra and Maxie Zeus.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/showcase-presents-batman-and-the-outsiders/4050-34908/" data-ref-id="4050-34908">Showcase Presents: Batman and the Outsiders</a> (#1-19)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-and-the-outsiders-1-volume-1/4000-581519/" data-ref-id="4000-581519">Batman and the Outsiders Volume 1</a> (#1-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-6-volume-six/4000-580725/" data-ref-id="4000-580725">New Teen Titans Volume Six</a> (#5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tales-of-the-batman-marv-wolfman-1-volume-1/4000-743303/" data-ref-id="4000-743303">Tales of the Batman: Marv Wolfman Volume 1</a> (#5)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-and-the-outsiders-2-volume-2/4000-659974/" data-ref-id="4000-659974">Batman and the Outsiders Volume 2</a> (#13-23)</li><li><a href="/batman-and-the-outsiders-3-volume-3/4000-705406/" data-ref-id="4000-705406">Batman and the Outsiders Volume 3</a> (#24-32)</li></ul>', '1983', '33', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2755085-01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3199', 'The Omega Men', 'Beginning! A New Series of Interstellar Super-Heroic Adventure! The Omega Men!', '10', NULL, '1983', '38', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11134/111344039/6278231-the%20omega%20men_1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3217', 'Alpha Flight', 'Tundra!', '31', '<p>Spinning out of the pages of Uncanny X-men, this is the first comic volume of Canada''s own premiere superhero team. Witness the rebirth of the team of superheroes. It lasted from 1983 until 1994 for a total of 130 issues. Two special Annual issues were released: <a href="/alpha-flight-annual/4050-3623/" data-ref-id="4050-3623">Alpha Flight Annual</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/alpha-flight-classic-1-volume-one/4000-140343/" data-ref-id="4000-140343"> Alpha Flight Classic Volume One</a> (#1-8)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/alpha-flight-by-john-byrne-omnibus/4050-98560/" data-ref-id="4050-98560">Alpha Flight By John Byrne Omnibus</a> (#1-29)</li><li><a href="/alpha-flight-classic-volume-two/4000-293647/" data-ref-id="4000-293647"> Alpha Flight Classic Volume Two</a> (#9-19)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/alpha-flight-classic-3-volume-3/4000-550693/" data-ref-id="4000-550693">Alpha Flight Classic Volume Three</a> (#20-29)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/avengers-epic-collection-under-siege/4050-90398/" data-ref-id="4050-90398">Avengers Epic Collection: Under Siege</a> (#39)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/acts-of-vengeance-spider-man-and-the-x-men/4050-136147/">Acts of Vengeance: Spider-Man &amp; The X-Men</a> (#79-80)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-comics-the-world-outside-your-window/4050-119858/">Marvel Comics: The World Outside Your Window</a> (#106)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-infinity-war-omnibus/4050-118131/">The Infinity War Omnibus</a> (#110-112)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-infinity-crusade-omnibus/4050-133099/">The Infinity Crusade Omnibus</a> (#124-125 &amp; 127)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-56-alpha-flight-de-joh/4000-612264/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Alpha Flight de John Byrne</a> (#1-29) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-60-los-4-fantasticos-d/4000-612268/" data-ref-id="4000-612268">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Los 4 Fantásticos de John Byrne 2</a> (#4) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-51-el-increible-hulk-l/4000-612259/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - El Increíble Hulk: La Encrucijada</a> (#29) (Spanish)</li></ul><p>The series'' second volume started after a three year break: <a href="/alpha-flight/4050-11291/" data-ref-id="4050-11291">Alpha Flight</a> (1997).</p>', '1983', '130', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20946-3217-23361-1-alpha-flight.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3223', 'The Falcon', 'Winners and Losers', '31', '<p>Sam "Snap" Wilson soars into his own series. ''Falcon'' reveals Sam Wilson as a mutant, which is retconed out years later, leading to an encounter with a Sentinel.</p><p>Collected in <a href="/avengers-falcon/4050-72196/" data-ref-id="4050-72196">Avengers: Falcon</a>.</p>', '1983', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21188-3223-23624-1-falcon.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3225', 'Hawkeye', 'Listen to the Mockingbird', '31', '<p>The original mini-series starring <a href="/hawkeye/4005-1475/" data-ref-id="4005-1475"> Hawkeye</a> and introducing <a href="/mockingbird/4005-2497/" data-ref-id="4005-2497"> Mockingbird</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/avengers-hawkeye/4050-28608/" data-ref-id="4050-28608">Avengers: Hawkeye</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/mockingbird-bobbi-morse-agent-of-shield/4050-92762/" data-ref-id="4050-92762">Mockingbird: Bobbi Morse, Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-verse-hawkeye/4050-139914/">Marvel-Verse: Hawkeye</a> (#1)</li></ul>', '1983', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11128/111287063/7415565-hawkeye%20v1983%20%231%20-%20listen%20to%20the%20mockingbird%20%281983_9_1%29%20-%20page%201.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3227', 'The Kree-Skrull War Starring the Avengers', NULL, '31', '<p>Reprints the original <a data-ref-id="4050-2128" href="/the-avengers/4050-2128/" slug="the-avengers">Kree-Skrull War Avengers</a> (#89-97) Story Arc.</p>', '1983', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21036-3227-23458-1-kree-skrull-war-star.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3230', 'Magik (Storm and Illyana Limited Series)', 'Little Girl Lost', '31', '<p>Magik: Storm And Illyana tells the tale of <a href="/illyana-rasputin/4005-8303/" data-ref-id="4005-8303">Illyana Rasputin</a>, the younger sister of X-Man <a href="/colossus/4005-1460/" data-ref-id="4005-1460">Colossus</a>, her quest to escape from the demon sorcerer <a href="/belasco/4005-10947/" data-ref-id="4005-10947">Belasco</a> from the interdimensional pocket realm known as <a href="/limbo/4020-42990/" data-ref-id="4020-42990">Limbo</a>, and the manifestation of her mutant teleportation ability.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/x-men-magik-storm-and-illyana/4050-29783/" data-ref-id="4050-29783">X-Men: Magik: Storm and Illyana</a></li><li><a href="//www.comicvine.com/x-men-magik-storm-illyana/4050-66837/" data-ref-id="4050-66837">X-Men: Magik - Storm &amp; Illyana</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/uncanny-x-men-omnibus-3-volume-3/4000-516096/" data-ref-id="4000-516096">Uncanny X-Men Omnibus Volume 3</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-masterworks-the-uncanny-x-men-10-volume-10/4000-580758/" data-ref-id="4000-580758">Marvel Masterworks: The Uncanny X-Men Volume 10</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-renewal/4050-99448/" data-ref-id="4050-99448">New Mutants Epic Collection: Renewal</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-omnibus-1/4000-821559/" data-ref-id="4000-821559">New Mutants Omnibus Vol. 1</a></li></ul><p><b>Note:</b> Indicia titled as "Magik (Storm and Illyana Limited Series)"</p>', '1983', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21289-3230-23731-1-magik.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3232', 'The Mighty World of Marvel', NULL, '2812', '<p>Prior to 1972 US <a href="/marvel/4010-31/" data-ref-id="4010-31">Marvel</a> comics had been reprinted in the UK by a variety of licensees, including <a href="/alan-class-comics/4010-3207/" data-ref-id="4010-3207">Alan Class</a> and <a href="/odhams-press/4010-2495/" data-ref-id="4010-2495">Odhams</a>. In 1972 however, this reprinting was brought in-house with the formation of <a href="/marvel-uk/4010-2812/" data-ref-id="4010-2812">Marvel UK</a>, whose first title was <a href="/the-mighty-world-of-marvel/4050-33875/" data-ref-id="4050-33875">Mighty World of Marvel</a>. In 1979, after a couple of title changes, usually as a result of absorbing other, failing Marvel UK titles, it became the monthly title <a href="/marvel-super-heroes/4050-3088/" data-ref-id="4050-3088">Marvel Super-Heroes</a>, which finally ended in May 1983 with #397. In July 1983 Mighty World of Marvel was revived as a full colour monthly, picking up Marvel Super-Heroes'' final leading strip, the <a href="/chris-claremont/4040-40468/" data-ref-id="4040-40468">Claremont</a>-<a href="/john-byrne/4040-1770/" data-ref-id="4040-1770">Byrne</a> era <a href="/x-men/4060-3173/" data-ref-id="4060-3173">X-Men</a>, where it had left off, at the start of the later-to-be-classic <a href="/days-of-future-past/4045-44425/" data-ref-id="4045-44425">Days of Future Past</a> story-line, alongside the US mini-series <a href="/vision-and-the-scarlet-witch/4050-3155/" data-ref-id="4050-3155">Vision and Scarlet Witch</a>. With the latter concluding in #4, the fifth issue began reprinting Chris Claremont and <a href="/frank-miller/4040-7082/" data-ref-id="4040-7082">Frank Miller''s</a> <a href="/wolverine/4050-3157/" data-ref-id="4050-3157">Wolverine</a> mini-series. The seventh issue saw Mighty World of Marvel absorb <a href="/the-daredevils/4050-22944/" data-ref-id="4050-22944">The Daredevils</a>, causing the X-Men''s departure and bringing in <a href="/alan-moore/4040-40382/" data-ref-id="4040-40382">Alan Moore</a> and <a href="/alan-davis/4040-2348/" data-ref-id="4040-2348">Alan Davis''</a> <a href="/captain-britain/4005-7477/" data-ref-id="4005-7477">Captain Britain</a> and <a href="/night-raven/4005-47365/" data-ref-id="4005-47365">Night Raven</a> (the latter text stories, rather than a comic strip), both of which had previously graced the pages of Marvel Super-Heroes. Falling sales saw the title drop some of the colour pages a few issues later, and in #13 Moore completed his run on Captain Britain, with Alan Davis and <a href="/steve-craddock/4040-56862/" data-ref-id="4040-56862">Steve Craddock</a> taking over writing duties. Issue #16 saw the final instalment of Captain Britain before he departed to star in his <a href="/captain-britain/4050-19753/" data-ref-id="4050-19753">own title</a>. Though the next issue was the last, it saw the start of reprinting another US mini-series, <a href="/magik-storm-and-illyana/4050-3230/" data-ref-id="4050-3230">Magik</a>, which then transferred, along with the Night Raven text stories, to Marvel UK''s <a href="/savage-sword-of-conan/4050-47760/" data-ref-id="4050-47760">Savage Sword of Conan</a> monthly.</p><p>Issue''s #7-13 have been translated into <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/best-of-marvel-capitan-britania/4050-41906/" data-ref-id="4050-41906">Spanish</a>.</p>', '1983', '17', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/1582260-1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3234', 'The New Mutants', 'Initiation !', '31', '<p>After their first adventure in <a href="/marvel-graphic-novel-the-new-mutants-renewal/4000-21793/" data-ref-id="4000-21793">Marvel Graphic Novel #4</a>, the newest generation of mutants takes center stage in their first ongoing series! See Cannonball, Sunspot, Mirage, Wolfsbane, Magma, Cypher, Warlock, Karma and Magik in their quest for mastering their mutant-powers and growing up in a world that hates and fears them. The series lasted for 100 issues, after which it was continued in <a href="/x-force/4050-4604/" data-ref-id="4050-4604">X-Force</a>.</p><h4>Additional Volumes</h4><ul><li>New Mutants Vol. 1 (1983)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants/4050-18351/" data-ref-id="4050-18351">New Mutants Vol. 2</a> (2003)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants/4050-26327/" data-ref-id="4050-26327">New Mutants Vol. 3</a> (2009)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants/4050-122666/" data-ref-id="4050-122666">New Mutants Vol. 4</a> (2020)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-lethal-legion/4050-148780/" data-ref-id="4050-148780">New Mutants: Lethal Legion</a> (2023)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-volume-1/4000-153497/" data-ref-id="4000-153497">New Mutants Classic: Vol. 1</a> (#1-7)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-renewal/4050-99448/" data-ref-id="4050-99448">New Mutants Epic Collection: Renewal</a> (#1-12)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-omnibus-1/4000-821559/" data-ref-id="4000-821559">New Mutants Omnibus Vol. 1</a> (#1-34)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-volume-2/4000-153645/" data-ref-id="4000-153645">New Mutants Classic: Vol. 2</a> (#8-17)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-the-demon-bear-saga/4050-120134/">New Mutants Epic Collection: The Demon Bear Saga</a> (#13-31)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-/4000-154118/" data-ref-id="4000-154118">New Mutants Classic: Vol. 3</a> (#18-25)</li><li><a href="/the-new-mutants-x-force-demon-bear/4050-77336/" data-ref-id="4050-77336">The New Mutants/X-Force: Demon Bear</a> (#18-20)</li><li><a href="/the-new-mutants-demon-bear/4050-109455/" data-ref-id="4050-109455">The New Mutants: Demon Bear</a> (#18-20)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-shadows-and-light/4050-98729/" data-ref-id="4050-98729">Cloak and Dagger: Shadows and Light</a> (#23-25)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/cloak-and-dagger-omnibus/4050-130070/">Cloak and Dagger Omnibus</a> (#23-25)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-/4000-154135/" data-ref-id="4000-154135">New Mutants Classic: Vol. 4</a> (#26-34)</li><li><a href="/xmen-legion-shadow-king-rising/4050-107965/" data-ref-id="4050-107965">X-Men: Legion: Shadow King Rising</a> (#26-28 &amp; 44)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-/4000-202147/" data-ref-id="4000-202147">New Mutants Classic: Vol. 5</a> (#35-40)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-volume-six/4000-284854/" data-ref-id="4000-284854">New Mutants Classic: Vol 6</a> (#41-47)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/marvel-comics-the-world-outside-your-window/4050-119858/">Marvel Comics: The World Outside Your Window</a> (#45)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-mutant-massacre-omnibus/4050-115098/">X-Men: Mutant Massacre Omnibus</a> (#46)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-mutant-massacre/4050-120422/">X-Men Milestones: Mutant Massacre</a> (#46)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-classic-volume-seven/4000-341551/" data-ref-id="4000-341551">New Mutants Classic: Vol 7</a> (#48-54)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-forever/4050-39212/" data-ref-id="4050-39212">New Mutants: Forever</a> (#53-54)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-sudden-death/4050-138158/">New Mutants Epic Collection: Sudden Death</a> (#55-70)</li><li><a href="/fall-of-the-mutants/4045-41745/" data-ref-id="4045-41745">Fall of the Mutants</a> (#59-61)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-fall-of-the-mutants/4050-120263/">X-Men Milestones: Fall of the Mutants</a> (#59-61)</li><li><a href="/xmen-inferno-prologue/4050-78660/" data-ref-id="4050-78660">X-Men: Inferno Prologue</a> (#62-70)</li><li><a href="/x-men-inferno-inferno/4000-129123/" data-ref-id="4000-129123">Inferno</a> (#71-73)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/x-men-inferno-1-volume-1/4000-511530/" data-ref-id="4000-511530">X-Men: Inferno Volume 1</a> (#71-72)</li><li><a href="/new-mutants-epic-collection-curse-of-the-valkyries/4050-108957/" data-ref-id="4050-108957">New Mutants Epic Collection: Curse of the Valkyries</a> (#71-85)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-inferno/4050-120966/">X-Men Milestones: Inferno</a> (#71-73)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-inferno-omnibus/4050-134787/">X-Men: Inferno Omnibus</a> (#71-73)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-inferno-2-volume-2/4000-537447/" data-ref-id="4000-537447">X-Men: Inferno Volume 2</a> (#73)</li><li><a href="/marvel-universe-by-john-byrne-omnibus-2-volume-2/4000-694138/" data-ref-id="4000-694138">Marvel Universe by John Byrne Omnibus Volume 2</a> (#75)</li><li><a href="/cable-and-the-new-mutants/4050-21747/" data-ref-id="4050-21747">Cable &amp; the New Mutants</a> (#86-94)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-mutants-epic-collection-cable/4050-130998/">New Mutants Epic Collection: Cable</a> (#86-94)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/acts-of-vengeance-spider-man-and-the-x-men/4050-136147/">Acts of Vengeance: Spider-Man &amp; The X-Men</a> (#86)</li><li><a href="/x-tinction-agenda/4045-42177/" data-ref-id="4045-42177">X-Tinction Agenda</a> (#95-97)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/x-men-milestones-x-tinction-agenda/4050-121589/">X-Men Milestones: X-Tinction Agenda</a> (#95-97)</li><li><a href="/x-force-a-forced-to-be-reckoned-with-hc/4050-36822/" data-ref-id="4050-36822">A Force to Be Reckoned With</a> (#98-100)</li><li><a href="/deadpool-firsts/4050-87944/" data-ref-id="4050-87944">Deadpool Firsts</a> (#98)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadpool-beginnings-omnibus/4050-98397/" data-ref-id="4050-98397">Deadpool Beginnings Omnibus</a> (#98)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadpool-the-adamantium-collection/4050-99248/" data-ref-id="4050-99248">Deadpool: The Adamantium Collection</a> (#98)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/deadpool-hey-its-deadpool-marvel-select/4050-133096/">Deadpool: Hey, It''s Deadpool! Marvel Select</a> (#98)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#30 &amp; #36) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-54-secret-wars-ii-circ/4000-612262/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: Círculo cerrado</a> (#37) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1983', '100', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/84205/1937731-newmutants1.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3235', 'Nick Fury, Agent of SHIELD', 'Who is Scorpio?', '31', NULL, '1983', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21294-3235-23736-1-nick-fury-agent-of-.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3237', 'The Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe', 'A: Abomination to Avengers Quinjet', '31', '<p>The Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe is a fifteen issue series that serves as an encyclopedia for nearly every character, location, object, and alien race in the Marvel Universe. This first volume was published in 1983 and started it all (even inspiring DC Comics to create their own version, titled "Who''s Who").</p><p>Collected in <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-official-handbook-of-marvel-universe-omnibus/4050-122674/">The Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe Omnibus</a>.</p>', '1983', '15', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/77/102953-3237-107387-2-official-handbook-of.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3239', 'The Saga of Crystar, Crystal Warrior', 'The Sundered Throne', '31', '<p>The Saga of Crystar: Crystal Warrior - a Marvel owned character, specifically created to licence to a toy company. Crystar was taken up by Remco who produced a range of action figures and vehicles in 1982 (before the comic was officially launched).</p>', '1983', '11', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/62641-3239-95637-1-saga-of-crystar-cry.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3243', 'Star Wars: Return of the Jedi', 'In the Hands of Jabba the Hutt!', '31', '<p>The Official Comics Adaptation!</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/star-wars-episode-vi-return-of-the-jedi/4050-85966/" data-ref-id="4050-85966">Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi</a></li><li><a href="/star-wars-legends-epic-collection-the-original-mar/4000-878330/" data-ref-id="4000-878330">Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Original Marvel Years Volume 5</a></li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/star-wars-the-original-trilogy-the-movie-adaptatio/4050-124292/">Star Wars: The Original Trilogy: The Movie Adaptations</a></li></ul>', '1983', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/47778-3243-57171-1-star-wars-return-of.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3245', 'The Thing', 'Lifelines', '31', '<p>Thing''s first solo series. This series is somewhat of a continuation of <a href="/marvel-two-in-one/49-2696/">Marvel Two-In-One</a>, a series witch starred the Thing and teamed him up with many other Marvel heroes and anti-heroes. This series started right after Marvel Two-in-One ended. It stars the Thing on earth and from issue 10 and on he is seen on the planet of the Beyonder where he stayed after the events of the Secret Wars. Later the Thing returns to earth and started a wrestling career. The series lasted for 36 issues in total.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/taskmaster-anything-you-can-do/4050-125196/">Taskmaster: Anything You Can Do...</a> (#26)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-76-la-cosa-secret-wars/4000-612314/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - La Cosa: Secret Wars</a> (#1-23) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-60-los-4-fantasticos-d/4000-612268/" data-ref-id="4000-612268">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Los 4 Fantásticos de John Byrne 2</a> (#2 &amp; #10) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-62-los-4-fantasticos-d/4000-612270/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Los 4 Fantásticos de John Byrne 4</a> (#7) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-61-los-4-fantasticos-d/4000-612269/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Los 4 Fantásticos de John Byrne 3</a> (#19) (Spanish)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/coleccionable-marvel-heroes-53-secret-wars-ii-quie/4000-612261/">Coleccionable Marvel Héroes - Secret Wars II: ¿Quién es el Todopoderoso?</a> (#30) (Spanish)</li></ul>', '1983', '36', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/20897-3245-23305-1-thing-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3247', 'X-Men Classics Starring the X-Men', NULL, '31', '<p>Reprints of issues 57-63 with an overall introduction by John Byrne and new coloring. Each issue begins with a "story thus far" recap, and issue 2 has a newly-created first page. Each issue ends with a gallery of the original covers. Issue 1 has a bonus cover of Neal Adams''s original artwork submission for the cover of issue 56 (as well as the actual issue cover). The only other change is the final panel at the close of issue 3, which adds some artwork to the bottom of the original panel with the words "The End" instead of the preview for issue 64.</p>', '1983', '3', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21303-3247-23745-1-x-men-classics-starr.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3305', 'Batman and the Outsiders Annual', '...Land Where Our Fathers Died...!', '10', '<p>Annual for <a href="/batman-and-the-outsiders/4050-3194/" data-ref-id="4050-3194">Batman and the Outsiders</a>.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/batman-and-the-outsiders-2-volume-2/4000-659974/" data-ref-id="4000-659974">Batman and the Outsiders Volume 2</a> (#1)</li><li><a href="/batman-and-the-outsiders-3-volume-3/4000-705406/" data-ref-id="4000-705406">Batman and the Outsiders Volume 3</a> (#2)</li></ul>', '1984', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2755133-01.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3307', 'Blue Devil', 'How to Trap a Devil', '10', '<p>At the request of editor <a href="/dave-manak/4040-2411/" data-ref-id="4040-2411">Dave Manak</a>, <a href="/blue-devil/4005-4845/" data-ref-id="4005-4845">Blue Devil</a> was created by <a href="/gary-cohn/4040-45877/" data-ref-id="4040-45877">Gary Cohn</a> and <a href="/dan-mishkin/4040-44266/" data-ref-id="4040-44266">Dan Mishkin</a> for the express purpose of giving <a href="/steve-ditko/4040-4026/" data-ref-id="4040-4026">Steve Ditko</a> a project he could sink his teeth into. They tailor-made Blue Devil, using elements of characters that Ditko was famous for. When Ditko reviewed it, he responded that it was not his kind of stuff at all. So <a href="/paris-cullins/4040-7864/" data-ref-id="4040-7864">Paris Cullins</a> was brought in as artist, and the Blue Devil title was born.</p><p><strong>This title has one annual:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="/blue-devil-annual-1-the-day-all-hell-broke-loose/4000-176003/" data-ref-id="4000-176003">Blue Devil Annual #1</a>.</li></ul>', '1984', '31', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21828-3307-24356-1-blue-devil.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3308', 'Infinity, Inc.', 'Generations', '10', '<p><em>Infinity, Inc.</em> ran for 53 issues and told the adventures of the children / nephews and nieces of the original <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/justice-society-of-america/4060-27589/" data-ref-id="4060-27589">Justice Society of America</a> members.</p><p>On the other dimensional world of <a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/earth-2/4015-56462/" data-ref-id="4015-56462">Earth-2</a>, the heroes of the Justice Society of America were gathered together for a rare Christmas Eve meeting when a group of brash young costumed heroes burst through their doors demanding membership in the prestigious team. A collection of the sons and daughters of some of the Society''s members, the youths nevertheless failed to impress their mentors. Following their rejection by the majority of the Justice Society, the teens decided to band together and form Infinity Inc, a new generation of Earth-2''s crime fighters. The group even gained the support of Justice Society member Star Spangled Kid who sympathized with Infinity Inc''s situation so much that he joined their ranks.</p><p>Written by DC''s Golden Age guru Roy Thomas and drawn by Jerry Ordway, "Infinity Inc" was released in DC''s new deluxe format on bright Baxter paper. With the team facing threats like the Ultra-Humanite, Brainwave, Solomon Grundy and even manipulated versions of the Justice Society themselves, Infinity Inc proved so popular that the title prevailed even after Earth-2 was destroyed during 1985''s "<em><a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths/4050-3441/" data-ref-id="4050-3441">Crisis on Infinite Earths</a></em>."</p><p> </p><p>Annuals filed under <em><a href="/infinity-inc-annual/4050-3448/" data-ref-id="4050-3448">Infinity, Inc. Annual</a></em>.</p><p>Special filed under <em><a href="/infinity-inc-special/4050-23217/" data-ref-id="4050-23217">Infinity, Inc. Special</a></em>.</p><h4> </h4><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/infinity-inc-the-generations-saga-1-volume-one/4000-424814/" data-ref-id="4000-424814">Infinity, Inc.: The Generations Saga #1 - Volume One</a> (#1-4)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/dc-through-the-80s-the-experiments/4050-137001/">DC Through the 80''s: The Experiments</a> (#14)</li><li><a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths-companion-deluxe-edition/4000-708088/" data-ref-id="4000-708088">Crisis On Infinite Earths Companion Deluxe Edition Volume 2</a> (#18-25)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/justice-league-the-detroit-era-omnibus/4050-106681/" data-ref-id="4050-106681">Justice League: The Detroit Era Omnibus</a> (#19)</li><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-5-volume-5/4000-826309/" data-ref-id="4000-826309">The New Teen Titans Omnibus Volume 5</a> (#45)</li></ul><h4>Non-U.S. Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/justice-league-of-america-crisis-7-band-7-1983-198/4000-667901/">Justice League of America: Crisis #7 - Band 7: 1983-1985</a> (#19) (German)</li></ul>', '1984', '53', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21564-3308-24054-1-infinity-inc-.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3310', 'Legion of Super-Heroes', 'Here a Villain, There a Villain...', '10', '<p>Starring: <a href="/legion-of-super-heroes/4060-19241/" data-ref-id="4060-19241">The Legion of Super-Heroes</a>.</p><p>Runs in tandem with: <em><a href="/tales-of-the-legion-of-super-heroes/4050-20776/" data-ref-id="4050-20776">Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes</a></em> (reprinted issues 326-354).</p><p>Annuals: <a href="/legion-of-super-heroes-annual/4050-3451/" data-ref-id="4050-3451"><em>Legion of Super-Heroes Annual</em></a>.</p><p>The Legion of Super Heroes had been around since the late 1950''s but the legendary teens from the future had never starred in their own all - new first issue. The Legion had instead bounced around the pages of <a href="/adventure-comics/4050-3105/" data-ref-id="4050-3105"><em>Adventure Comics</em></a> and <a href="/superboy/4050-19154/" data-ref-id="4050-19154"><em>Superboy</em></a>, finally taking over the latter series'' title in 1973, a year in which they also starred in a four issue series featuring <a href="/reprinted-material/4015-56278/" data-ref-id="4015-56278">reprinted</a> Legion tales from <em>Adventure Comics</em>. However. the team had never been treated to the prestige and sales potential of a traditional debut issue. So as DC began to toy with the idea of relaunching some of their more popular titles using high quality Baxter paper, the Legion of Super Heroes was an obvious choice. Utilizing the talents of writer Paul Levitz and artist Keith Giffen, fan favourite creators ever since their fabled 1982 epic, "<a href="/great-darkness-saga/4045-40773/" data-ref-id="4045-40773"><em>The Great Darkness Saga</em></a>," the Legion was off and running with their own new title with a major new storyline. The debut issue and story arc introduced a newly united Legion of Super-Villains, a concept that had been building since the LSH was born and a battle royal between the two Legions ensued. The Baxter series ran for sixty three issues until its next relaunch and remains the high point of the Legion''s career in the eyes of many fans.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/superman-the-man-of-steel-2-vol-2/4000-826311/" data-ref-id="4000-826311">Superman: The Man of Steel Vol. 2</a> (#37-38)</li></ul>', '1984', '63', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/68065/7701746-0aa.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3316', 'The New Teen Titans', 'Shadows in the Dark!', '10', '<h3>Marv Wolfman''s run in order:</h3><ol><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans/4050-3036/" data-ref-id="4050-3036">The New Teen Titans</a> Vol. 1 (#1-40)</li><li><a href="/tales-of-the-teen-titans/4050-3324/" data-ref-id="4050-3324">Tales of the Teen Titans</a> (#41-58)</li><li><strong>The New Teen Titans Vol. 2</strong> (#1-49)</li><li><a href="/the-new-titans/4050-4014/" data-ref-id="4050-4014">The New Titans</a> (#50-130)</li></ol><p>This series ran concurrent with the latter for a few years.</p><h2>Collected Editions</h2><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Volumes</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-9-volume-nine/4000-678516/" data-ref-id="4000-678516">Nine</a></td><td>1-9</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-10-volume-ten/4000-702817/" data-ref-id="4000-702817">Ten</a></td><td>10-15</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-11-volume-eleven/4000-763259/" data-ref-id="4000-763259">Eleven</a></td><td>16-23</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-12-volume-twelve/4000-823029/" data-ref-id="4000-823029">Twelve</a></td><td>24-31</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-13-volume-thirteen/4000-956316/" data-ref-id="4000-956316">Thirteen</a></td><td>32-40</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/new-teen-titans-14-volume-fourteen/4000-956317/" data-ref-id="4000-956317">Fourteen</a></td><td>41-49</td></tr></tbody></table><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Omnibuses</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-3-volume-3/4000-407166/" data-ref-id="4000-407166">Three</a></td><td>1-6</td></tr><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-4-volume-4/4000-728310/" data-ref-id="4000-728310">Four</a></td><td><span>10-31</span></td></tr><tr><td><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-5-volume-5/4000-826309/" data-ref-id="4000-826309">Five</a></td><td>32-49</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Also in:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans-the-terror-of-trigon/4050-41564/" data-ref-id="4050-41564">Terror of Trigon</a> (#1-5)</li><li><a href="/crisis-on-infinite-earths-companion-deluxe-edition/4000-708088/" data-ref-id="4000-708088">Crisis On Infinite Earths: Companion Deluxe Edition Vol. 2</a> (#13-14)</li></ul>', '1984', '49', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7220110-2997223990-42600.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3317', 'Omega Men Annual', 'Heaven And Hell Waiting In The Wings', '10', '<p>Series of annuals for <a href="/the-omega-men/4050-3199/" data-ref-id="4050-3199">The Omega Men</a>.</p>', '1984', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21322-3317-23774-1-omega-men-annual.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3324', 'Tales of the Teen Titans', 'Baptism of Blood', '10', '<h4>Marv Wolfman''s run in order:</h4><ol><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-new-teen-titans/4050-3036/">The New Teen Titans</a> Vol. 1 (#1-40)</li><li><strong>Tales of the Teen Titans</strong> (#41-58)</li><li><a href="/the-new-teen-titans/4050-3316/" data-ref-id="4050-3316">The New Teen Titans</a> (#1-49)</li><li><a href="/the-new-titans/4050-4014/" data-ref-id="4050-4014">The New Titans</a> (#50-130)</li></ol><p><strong>NOTE</strong>:</p><ul><li>#41-58 take place before The New Teen Titans Vol. 2</li><li>#59-91 are reprints of The New Teen Titans Vol. 2 #1-31 and their Annual #2</li></ul><h4>Related Issues</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tales-of-the-teen-titans-annual/4050-3325/" data-ref-id="4050-3325">Tales of the Teen Titans Annual</a> (#3-4)</li></ul><h2>Collected Editions</h2><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Volumes</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-7-volume-seven/4000-616150/" data-ref-id="4000-616150">Seven</a></td><td>41-48</td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-8-volume-eight/4000-647920/" data-ref-id="4000-647920">Eight</a></td><td>49-58</td></tr></tbody></table><table data-max-width="true"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Omnibus</th><th scope="col">Issues</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-5-volume-5/4000-826309/" data-ref-id="4000-826309">Five</a></td><td>41-49, 91</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Also in:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="/who-is-donna-troy/4045-50167/" data-ref-id="4045-50167">Who is Donna Troy?</a> (#50)</li><li><a href="/judas-contract/4045-40760/" data-ref-id="4045-40760">The Judas Contract</a> (#41-44)</li></ul>', '1984', '51', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21668-3324-24172-1-tales-of-the-teen-ti.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3325', 'Tales of the Teen Titans Annual', 'The Judas Contract: Book Four - Finale!', '10', '<p>Annuals for the series <em><a href="/tales-of-the-teen-titans/4050-3324/" data-ref-id="4050-3324">Tales of the Teen Titans</a></em>.</p><h4>Publishing History:</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-new-teen-titans-annual/4050-3118/">The New Teen Titans Annual</a> (#1-2)</li><li><strong>Tales of the Teen Titans Annual</strong> (#3-4)</li></ul><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/new-teen-titans-7-volume-seven/4000-616150/" data-ref-id="4000-616150">New Teen Titans Volume Seven</a> (#3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/tales-from-the-dc-dark-multiverse/4050-125285/">Tales From the DC Dark Multiverse</a> (#3)</li><li><a href="https://comicvine.gamespot.com/the-new-teen-titans-omnibus-5-volume-5/4000-826309/" data-ref-id="4000-826309">The New Teen Titans Omnibus Volume 5</a> (#3-4)</li></ul>', '1984', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21985-3325-24532-1-tales-of-the-teen-ti.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3335', 'Captain America Special Edition', 'No Longer Alone!', '31', NULL, '1984', '2', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/41255-3335-46562-1-captain-america-spec.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3340', 'Elektra Saga', 'Book One: The Wall', '31', '<p>Elektra. The first woman ever loved by the Daredevil, the man without fear. Her touch was warmth. Her simile was light. Then, her father was murdered., and a soft heart became as stone,. She left this country, driven by rage and grief, to study the many arts of killing with an order of ninja called The Hand -- until she betrayed them. Forced into exile, she came back to the land known as America; now as an assassin-for-hire. And for her crimes, thes tragic, haunted woman is hunted by the one man she has ever cared for, remembered through years of loneliness and denial -- Daredevil. When Elektra confronts her last love, only death can follow.</p>', '1984', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/4/21502-3340-23975-1-elektra-saga-the.jpg', '0');
INSERT INTO volumes (id, name, firstIssue, publisherId, deck, startYear, numIssues, image, numLikes) VALUES ('3342', 'G.I. Joe Yearbook', 'Operation: Lady Doomsday', '31', '<p>Four issue mini-series.</p><h4>Collected Editions</h4><ul><li><a href="/g-i-joe-yearbook-1-tpb/4000-418548/" data-ref-id="4000-418548">G.I. Joe Yearbook</a> (#1-4)</li><li><a href="/g-i-joe-the-complete-collection-5-volume-5/4000-460982/" data-ref-id="4000-460982">G.I. Joe: The Complete Collection Vol. 5</a> (#1-2)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/g-i-joe-the-complete-collection-6-volume-6/4000-471981/" data-ref-id="4000-471981">G.I. Joe: The Complete Collection Vol. 6</a> (#3)</li><li><a href="https://www.comicvine.com/g-i-joe-the-complete-collection-7-volume-7/4000-489926/" data-ref-id="4000-489926">G.I. Joe: The Complete Collection Vol. 7</a> (#4)</li></ul>', '1985', '4', 'https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11/110017/2232584-g.i._joe_yearbook_01___00___fc.jpg', '0');